column41: SIT
During the period of falling in love, each time that we met and á especially when we had not met for a long time.
When I was involved in a traffic accident.
When I was driving home after  several days of hard work, there á was a motorist ahead of me who was driving at 50 km/hour and á refused, despite his low speeed to let me overtake.
When I lost the person who meant the most to me.

The time I knocked a deer down - the sight of the animal's á injuries and helplessness.  The realization that the animal was á so badly hurt that it had to be put down, and when the animal á screamed at the moment of death.
When I did not speak the truth.
When I caused problems for somebody because he could not keep the á appointed time and this led to various consequences.
When I got a letter offering me the Summer job that I had applied á for.
When I was going home alone one night in Paris and a man came up á behind me and asked me if I was not afraid to be out alone so á late at night.
When I was talking to HIM at a party for the first time in a long while and a friend came and interrupted us and HE left.
When my friends did not ask me to go to a New Year's party á with them.
When I saw all the very drunk kids (13-14 years old) in town on á Walpurgis night.
When I could not remember what to say about a presentation task á at an accounts meeting.
When my uncle and my neighbour came home under police escort.
[ On days when I feel close to my partner and other friends.  á When I feel at peace with myself and also experience a close á contact with people whom I regard greatly.]
Every time I imagine that someone I love or I could contact a á serious illness, even death.
When I had been obviously unjustly treated and had no possibility á of elucidating this.
When I think about the short time that we live and relate it to á the periods of my life when I think that I did not use this á short time.
At a gathering I found myself involuntarily sitting next to two á people who expressed opinions that I considered very low and á discriminating.
When I realized that I was directing the feelings of discontent á with myself at my partner and this way was trying to put the blame á on him instead of sorting out my own feeliings.
I feel guilty when when I realize that I consider material things á more important than caring for my relatives.  I feel very á self-centered.
After my girlfriend had taken her exam we went to her parent's á place.
When, for the first time I realized the meaning of death.
When a car is overtaking another and I am forced to drive off the á road.
When I recently thought about the hard work it takes to study, and  á how one wants to try something else.  When I read a theoretical á book in English that I did not understand.
When I found a bristle in the liver paste tube.
When I was tired and unmotivated, I shouted at my girlfriend and á and brought up negative sides of her character which are actually á not so important.
When I think that I do not study enough.  After the weekend I á think that I should have been able to have accomplished á something during that time.
When I pass an examination which I did not think I did well.
When one has arranged to meet someone and that person arrives á late, in the meantime one starts thinking about all that could á have gone wrong e.g a traffic accident.
When one is unjustly accused of something one has not done.
When one's studies seem hopelessly difficult and uninteresting.
When one finds out that someone you know is not at all like one á had thought, for instance friends who steal and things like that, á quite unwarranted.
When one has been unjust, stupid towards someone else.
When one has neglected or been unjust to a good friend.
Passing an exam I did not expect to pass.
When I climbed up a tree to pick apples.  The angle of the ladder á I was on did not enable me to get high enough.  This implied á that the ladder was not very stable.
Friends who torture animals.
[ Same as in anger.]
Friends who torture animals.
[ Same as above - friends who torture animals.]
[ When excuses are necessary and I get out of doing it myself.]
When I had my children.

When my 2 year old son climbed up and sat on the 7th floor á balcony with his legs hanging out.  He was holding on tightly to á the upper railing of the balcony but he could have easily lost á his balance when he sat down.
When my partner was attacked and lost three teeth.
When I see children on T.V from areas devastated by drought and á war.
When I nearly walked on a blindworm and then saw it crawl away.

When I saw my 18 year old son grab an oxygen mask as he had á breathing difficulties.  I had a bad conscience because I had not á stopped smoking.  Medication for the dilation of his breathing á tubes also caused a sense of guilt in me.
I experience a sense of guilt as my middle son cannot express á himself like other children, neither verbally nor in writing.
When my child was born.

It was winter/spring and the ice was melting.  I was far out on a á jetty and I poked the ice with a long branch to try and break it. á  The branch went through the ice and I fell in, the water closed á in over my head.
Unjust accusations directed at me and my way of acting, by á someone close to me.
Failing an examination.
A drunkard fell, started bleeding and wet himself.  Disgust that á turned into sadness-unpleasantness.
When, as an adult I have been caught lying or behaving badly.
When I am in an environment or with a person much worse off than á me, I realize how privileged I am.
When I saw a person I had not seen for a long time.
When, as a child, I was nearly knocked down by a car.
When I heard on the radio that the football match in Belgium had á ended in a catastrophe, and several people had died.  I could not á  understand how normal people could behave in such a way.
When I feel lonely, perhaps because I have to study a lot and I á am shut up in my appartment.  Nothing happens in particular á because there is no time for anything else.
When one learns through the mass media all the wars and killing á going on in the world.
I lied, to be precise I cancelled a meeting with a good friend.
When one lets friends down
When I was accepted for a course on finance and accounting.
A bus drove over my right leg.  The event itself was not very á frightening but when I had to wait in the emergency ward for á three hours and then my leg began to swell, I was frightened.
At my Summer job, nobody looked after me in particular and I had á to learn all on my own.
When I was not accepted as a student in finance and accounting.
When I had just moved into my new appartment I found a ventilator á in the kitchen.  I was going to clean it when I found that the á drum was full of mud and slime.  I felt disgusted.
My elder brother and I have not always had a good relationship á and I feel ashamed of myself as I do not call him to talk to him á nowadays.
At my Summer job a new caretaker had been employed who was my age á  but I preferred going out for lunch with the accounts personnel á rather than with him.
Passed an exam by 2 points.
In a cottage in a large forest, I was alone for a while in the á dark.
When I spoke to Jan-Erik Wikstr÷m on the telephone.
Railway station good-bye.
I saw a cripple in rags with small children in Italy.  He was á probably an imposter.
I told a friend that I was going to a party and he would not á enjoy himself if he came along.  He understood  that he would not á have fitted in and there was something in that.
I was the reason behind the break-up of my friend's relationship á with his girlfriend.  She finished with him.
I passed an exam that I was absolutely certain that I had failed.
On the way back from Denmark with a friend on a small yatch, á there was a storm and my friend was blown overboard;  I was very á scared till I managed to get him back onboard.
I locked myself out.
I missed the last tram home and had to walk in the pouring rain.
I found some worms in the food and I had obviously eaten some.
My friend was so intoxicated that the police came and took him á away, and they later contacted his parents.
I hapened to overhear something which I was not meant to hear.
When I won a trip to Greece in a competition.
When I am out in the dark and a suspicious looking character á comes towards me.
At work, when an elderly man complained unjustifiably about me and á distrusted me.
When I had not understood anything after a lecture.
When an alcoholic stood dribbling over a food counter.
When my friend and I were discussing the good looks of a guy we á realized that he had been listening.
When I complained about a colleague to the manager and he told á her that someone had complained; this colleague came to me á believing that I liked her.
At a friend's birthday party with some of my closest friends.  It á was all very pleasant and one could say that I was happy to have á such good friends.
On the way home one Friday night in the heavy rain the car á acquaplanned.  I lost contact with the road surface for a few á seconds.
Mad at my dad.
A case of unrequited love.
A bad smelling cucumber.
Nearly caught masturbating.
I do not help out enough at home.
I felt very happy when I won the football pools.
When I flew from Athens to Copenhagen after a holiday.  The plane á was caught in a storm and it began to shake and I thouhght that á we were going to crash.
When someone stole my bike.
[ I sometimes quarrel with my mother because she blames me, á though I have not in any way been connected to some events.]
After hearing about the death of my grandfather.  First I could á not believe it, but later I wept and felt the situation was á hopeless.  I felt lonely and wanted to be consolated.
In the evening, while I was watching TV, my little brother came á in and started eating food he had brought from the kitchen while á I was trying to concentrate on the program.
My little brother was arrested by the police at the railway station after á he had drunk some beer.
At my temporary job, I have to restrict  others' actions and make á them obey me, and this very often gives me  a feeling of guilt.  I á wish there could be some other way of acting.

I met a dear friend of mine after a long time.  I expressed my feelings á in our own usual way, by mutual scolding and abusing (with á complete understanding) and by touching, patting and taking the á hand of the other person, etc...

I felt fear of the purest kind after a car accident.  The á incident and images of horror kept coming back to my mind.  I á wondered what could have happened to my sister, my friend and me, á though nothing very serious actually happened.

Two boys whom I know were telling me, in an indecent manner, how á they had teased a young and shy girl I know.  They had despised á her conviction, scorned and touched her.  I got very angry and á did not try to conceal it and gave it back to them.

My sweetheart left me, or rather we decided to break it off by á mutual consent.  The consequences were - unrestrained weeping, á feelings of loneliness, hopelessness and disconsolation.  I felt á that I should find a friend, to talk to joyfully and to forget.
Out of sheer curiosity, I went to see a pornographic movie in á Copenhagen.  The room was full of men, who panted and á masturbated.  Very disgusting.
After having quarelled unnecessarily and without any reason, and á having been stupidly cross in every way.
[ Do not know.]
Forced to fill in a questionnaire.
When I won a tennis match.
When my dog ran out on thin ice last spring.
When my tennis match was interrupted because a kid cycled right á into the court.
[ No response.]
[ No response.]
[ No response.]
[ No response.]
Celebrations on the graduation day with the orchestra playing in á the garden ( I am a part of this orchestra).
Risk of being involved in a fight after a party.
I was driving and a deer suddenly appeared in front of the á car when there was a lot of traffic behind me.
I saw a report on T.V news on apartheid in South Africa.
[ No response.]
[ No response.]
[ No response.]
[ No response.]
When my girlfriend became pregnant.
When I nearly collided with another car.
The time when someone let the air out of the tyres of my cycle.
When I read a lot and did not remember anything.
[ No response.]
[ No response.]
The time that I had to put my dog to sleep.
[ No response.]
[ No response.]
[ No response.]
Long illness.
When I passed an exam.
When I was travelling by tram, I tripped and fell against the á door.  I thought that I was going to fall out.
When I missed the tram after having run for it.
The inability to read a book at college.
If a guy one is not interested in makes advances.
I drink wine too often.
I do not study enough as I do not understand it properly.
I worked at a lawyer's office during Summer and I got a very á good reference from him.
I had been watching a triller a dark night in the country and I á had to go the outside toilet on my own.
When I am accused of something I have not done, I get unbelievably á angry.
When I began to read a thick book, which I had a limited time to á read.  Also when I have a lot of work to do and I cannot keep up.
Someone vomited on the street.
I can not think of any incident when I have felt very ashamed.  á There are small incidents that I am ashamed of, for instance, á not sending money to the children in Ethiopia.
I had lunch with my ex-boyfriend and did not mention it to my á fiancee.  I felt guilty despite the fact that I felt nothing for á my ex-boyfriend.
When I was finally qualified for my profession.
Someone attacked me with a knife.
Someone drove into my car and then denied that it had happened.
When I was told that my friend's wife had cancer.
When I saw a dog which had been knocked down by a car.
When I boxed my child's ears.
When I was fined for speeding.
I stopped working (had a boring job).
I was going home by car late one night when it was cold, dark and á windy.  I became rather panicky on the way to my house.
Quarrel in the family.
When I am alone in a room with no contact with anyone - á loneliness drains me.
When I was on holiday someone vomited in front of me.
Emptied a bucket of water in a hospital.
When I feigned sick leave from work.
When I get a hug from someone I love.

I was driving very fast on a small road and I met an oncoming car á in a right handed bend.  The other driver was on his own side of á the road and I had to skid out of it to avoid a collision.  It á was dark.
My car had been towed away by the traffic police because it had á been wrongly parked.  However the sign had been put up only after á I had already parked.
After an operation I had to stay in bed for a long time.
I was forced to stay in the canteen and eat the food that I had á not asked for but got it anyway.
When I did not buy what I had promised to.
By mistake I took a book from the library which was not supposed á to be loaned out.
When I won an unexpected sum of money.
My 2 year old daughter disappeared in a moment of inattention; I á was responsible for her.
A colleague asked me for some advice and as he did not have á enough confidence in me he asked a third person.
I wanted to be pregnant and did not succeed, so I was depressed    á at every menstruation.
In a warm bus full of people, someone vomited and the whole bus á stank.

I complained about a colleague's behaviour as she goes back on á her word, is often absent and is irresponsible.  I found out that á she was an alcoholic and was trying to fight againt her á addiction.

I spoke to my mother on the phone.  She had skin cancer and was á waiting to be operated.  I forgot to ask her the date of the á operation and just before finishing our conversation she gave me á the date in passing.
When I was at a party I met an old friend from an adult á education course.  We had not met for 2 years but had both thought á a lot about each other.  A wonderful experience.á
When I was cycling through the park late one night, two people á jumped out of the woods and tried to stop me.  There were á shouting something at the same time.
When close relatives tried to dissuade me from studying á Psychology because of its low status.
I had a long discussion on politics with an acquaintance.  He á was more knowledgeable than me and I failed to explain my point á of view and was misunderstood so I felt depressed and left.
When I read a newspaper article on a young girl who had been á raped and assaulted one night by several men when she was unconscious.
My mother revealed personal details about me and the á negative aspects of my character to other people when I was á present but unable to defend myself.
I was unfaithful to my partner once when he was working abroad á for a long period.
When I recently got an appartment in central Gottenburg.
When I saw a large spider crawling up the wall.
My employer took too many aspirins for a bad back and also drank á an enormous amount of spirit.  This was dangerous  and he did á not understand that he had done anything wrong.
When I left New York, and all my family and my friends behind me.
When I slept with a guy because my best friend wanted me to.  á He had never had intercourse with anyone and had a terrible á complex about it.
When I dated a close girlfriend's boyfriend a few times. He told á me that it was over between them and I accepted it.  When she á found out she finished our friendship.
When I broke off with my boyfriend after three years.  It was á quite unexpected for him and there was no particular reason for á the break up, such as someone else.
When my son returned from mountaineering - healthy in body and á soul.
When one meets new people with whom one is forced to collaborate á with.
The sports fishermen who catch gulls instead of fish with their hooks. á   It is often a mistake but it makes me angry.
I feel sad about an event I can not influence.
When a member of the family complains about the food that is á served, it disgusts me.
[ Cannot recall any incident when I felt shame.]
I have chosen to put my son in a private school were the á examination marks are low.  Every time that he gives me his term á results I am left with a sense of guilt.
When I was informed that I had been accepted as a student of á Psychology.
When I was in a little fishing boat and we ran into hard weather á in the open sea.
When I found out that the guy I was dating at a particular time á had a steady relationship going on with someone else for a long á time.
I felt sad and depressed when I heard that our cat had died.
When I was working as a nurse in a mental hospital, a patient ate á up the contents of another patient's spitoon.
At primary school, when I vomited in front of others in the middle  á of a lesson.
I arrived an hour late for an important meeting ( I had á misunderstood the time).
When I was acceptted as a student of psychology.
When my son has a pain in his leg (for no apparent reason).
When, after a week at school, a teacher sent a note home saying á that my son was inattentive and unable to do his lessons.
When I thought that it was going to be impossible for me to start á studying (due to wrong information from the student advisor).
At a certain person's lack of cleanliness, at home and á personally.
When I made the same mistake that I had accused someone else of, and á this was obvious to a third pereson.
When I lost something that was valuable to my sister.
When my son was born.
When I nearly drowned in icy water wearing ice skates.  It was á difficult to get out.
When I was pointed out as a problem child in primary school and á my mother took the teacher's point of view.
When I was accused of neglecting work for the wrong reasons.
My parents attitude towards each other when they should become á reconciled, despite my father's long-time addiction.
When I was caught stealing money from my father.
I stole a coconut cake from a reception table and when I put á in my mouth I realized that the host was watching me.
When I was reprimanded by the manager of the hotel where I á worked during Autumn 1984.
When my parents drove me to a nearby place and went home á immediately instead of waiting a few hours.  They could have á easily waited.
When my ex-girlfriend and I discovered that there was a certain risk á of her being pregnant.
When I was about to clean the draining board and saw it looked á underneath the sink (I live in a students hostel).
When my mother caught me masturbating.
As the only person in my family into academics, I ought to have á looked after my younger (and only) sister better, with respect to á her education and life experiences.
When my older sister told us that she was thinking of joining the á rest of the family for the winter sports holiday.
Slept in a chapel and in the middle of the night I realized that á there was someeone else in the chapel.  I never discovered who á it was and why he was there.

When we were in high school a few guys sometimes provoked a á friend of mine.  They called her a pig and then grunted.  This á irritated most of the girls.  Once, one of the girls got angry at á my friend and said something nasty and this made me terribly á angry.

I talked to my boyfriend on the phone when I was in high spirits á and had a lot to tell him.  I had been looking forward to this á conversation and he did not listen to me to the extent that I á had anticipated.
A mother who shouts at her child for nothing.
When I complained to my mother about how untidy the kitchen á loooked, she boxed my ears ( this had never happened before).

As I could not be home before midnight I called home at 11.30 and á asked them to leave the door open so that I could get in.  I á actually woke up the whole family by calling them so late.  My á mother could not go back to sleep, besides she had a conference   á the next day and really needed to sleep.
When I got through the first day here at the department.
When I was cycling past a parked car someone opened the door and á nearly pushed me off my bike and into the traffic.
When my boyfriend sat up half the night playing computer games á with a friend.
When I had to leave my mother and my sister after a week's visit.
When I saw a big spider from very close.
When I asked a friend to return the money that I had loaned her á and then remembered that she had repayed me in several ways.
When one of my parents insinuates something about the other á (they are divorced).
When i was asked to be a child's godmother.
On the way down a ski slope which was difficult and steep.
When my mother interfered in my life.
When I was left alone one week-end without being prepared for á it.
The first time that I saw a surgeon cut off a leg and put it in a á black rubbish bag.
When I forgot about a meeting at work.
When I demand too much from my friends.
When my husband suddenly came to see me at my new job and á brought some flowers and cake with him.
When I was nearly attackad by a man who had been chasing me.
When my father asked me if I was a communist, at the same time he á made it clear that I should no longer see myself as his daughter.
When I applied for a job which I thought I had a good chance of á getting, I was not even granted an interview and did not get the á job.
T.V features showing the violation of defenceless people.
When I as a child of 9 or 10 I was playing doctor with the á neighbours boys their mother caught us.

When my husband talked about the restrictions he will have to á accept in his life to make our marriage work.  I felt that it was á directed at me as it was me who had demanded the changes.  We á were with a marriage counsellor then.
When we were able to afford a new sofa - a leather one which cost á SEK 20000.  I had waited for it for 2-3 years.
Vertigo - standing on a ladder and painting the house.
When my boss enrolled in a course to satisfy his own ends - to á trample on his associates.  I have the misfortune to have one of á my superiors in my course.
When I argue with my mother about the way she treats her two á children differently.
Spit and vomit.
Spots on the seat covers of my husband's car.
Not speaking to my sister-in-law due to lack of interest in a á relationship on my side.
I was within a hair's breadth of knocking down a drunkard who á suddenly ran into the street.  The fear came later when I     á realized what could have happened.
When my friend, as usual, forgot the tickets at home for a á performance.  We missed it.
When I was appointed to position of trust in a group set up to á change the working environment.
I was alone in a cottage I often stay in.  I was woken up by a á rustling sound in the middle of the night.
When I tried to explain to a plumber, face to face, that the á toilet was broken and he did not believe it (it had been mended á ten times).
When the result of a project work was treated nonchalantly á intead of being criticized by the teacher.
When programmes on violence or pornography are shown on T.V.
When I talked maliciously about a colleague at work to someone á else.  Immediately afterwards I felt ashamed.
When I decided to take a week s holiday without consulting the á family first.
After my girl and I talked things over our relationship changed á and became positive.  A diificult time turned into pleasant one.
When we could not land our plane and we knew that the fuel was á running out.  Bad weather had already frightened us.
When I read about Reagan's tactical decision concerning the á South African boycott.
When my half brother became seriously ill with cancer and died á later.
A film were a woman was attacked and raped.  One did not see the á worst but it had the desired effect - very strong.
I made a comment and it was interpreted completely differently á from what I had meant.  When I said it I realized how my mother á had understood it.
I had promised to visit my girlfriend but for different reasons á could not make it.  I rang up later to tell her that I could not á come.
When I was offered a high position of trust, which I later á accepted.

I had the window open and the door was shut so that the kitten á would not go out.  My partner came in and started talking about á something and I forgot about the window and suddenly I saw the á kitten hanging from the window frame. I was rigid with fright á till I got hold of her.

Some noisy guests arrived at the hotel.  I had been slightly á irritated earlier.  At night when I was trying to sleep they were á having a party so I went and yelled at them.  I wanted to sleep á as I had to get up early the next day.
When I was told that I had not been successful in getting the job I á had been expecting.  I was sure that I was sufficiently á qualified.
When my cat vomited and a worm came out which was still alive.  I á was forced to wipe it up.

When I was a child it was found out that I had taken off my á clothes outdoors.  It was summer and my friend and I were out á in the woods.  It had felt exciting at that time.  My parents á discovered that my trousers were back to front and I felt á ashamed.
When I stole money from my mother and she asked me later if I was á responsible.  I never admitted it.
[ Cycling in the spring sunshine gives me such delight.  á Happiness is to be healthy, my wonderful finance.  Simply being á here on earth.]
When my relationship with my family is very poor I often fear á being excluded from the group, a fear which is stronger in á situations when an argument is on hand.

Recently when my sister, who is four years younger than me and á very spoiled, shouted at my mother for no apparent reason .  The á heart-broken expression on my mother's face made me feel very á angry.
Disgust is a feeling that I have never experienced with peoplie á but , on the other hand, it has been with repulsive animals, i;e á snakes on T.V.
When relatives have acted strangely, and unfriendly towards me.

When ,due to hunger and tiredness, I became generally irritated á with my fiancee and made cutting remarks which really hurt him.  á Later I realized that my unfounded irritation had hurt the person á I love most on earth.
On a boat trip to Denmark, 14 of us had a lot of fun and we á spent SEK 10 each on one armed bandits and against all odds we á won the jackpot of SEK 1000.
A rainy day, I was cycling downhill and a car door suddenly á opened and while trying to avoid it the back wheels of my bike á got caught in the tram tracks.  I somersaulted but had no á injuries.

On the way home from Marstrand I was driving behind my father's á car.  Another car tried to push in front of my father and he was á forced to swerve and he thus collided the car with a pillar.  The á other car drove off without even seeing what had happened.
My girlfriend who had spent 6 months abroad broke off our á relationship by letter.
At the police centre a man between 40-50 was brought in.  He was á very drunk and in all likelihood had not slept indoors for a long á time and had relieved himself in his trousers.
A customer at the shop where I worked came in and asked if the á goods that he had ordered had arrived.  I had totally á forgotten about this order and I tried to offer weak excuses.
I was 4-5 years old when I hid the bicycle keys of a not very á good friend.  After a few hours I pretended that I had found á it.
When I was at the end-of-term party last week and had fun - was á happy and sang and drank only soft drinks.  It is possible to á have a good time without alcohol.
Last Summer I was walking along the beach in a bikini and an á awful man came cycling after me.  He was shouting and I ran as á fast as my legs could carry me.
In a course I thought that I deserved good marks but I only got á ordinary marks with no justification as to why I was given these á marks.
When I crashed my car and it had to be scrapped then.  It was my á fault and I feel depressed as I miss the car.
I had some sort of a stomach virus last week and  I vomited in á college in the morning, then in the cake shop, three times during á the trip home and again when I got home.

When I was an evening school teacher it was my job to make the á coffee but I was not able to get the coffee ready on time and I á thus arrived half an hour late to the class.  On top of this the á coffee was undrinkable.
Many years ago a friend wanted me to with her to southern Europe á and I preferred to travel alone.  I felt guilty because I wanted á to go on my own.
When I felt that my love was returned.
When I was convinced that someonne had broken into my flat and I á woke up and heard sounds that frightened me.

When it became clear that a man had used many people sexually á and psychologically, despite the fact that many people looked up á to him.  I understood that one could not trust him and I was á forced to hide this for a while.
When I feel helpless after having tried to help someone without á any result.
When I think now about the way my father behaved when filing a á divorce.
When as an 8 year old, I wet myself in school.
When as a 7 year old, I stole money from my mother.
When I recently got a very positive answer from a clinic telling á me that they would willingly assist and collect data for me for a á clinical pilot study.
Every time I meet a certain dog that has once bitten me.
When after a lot of provocation my child threw a plate on the á floor.
When I realized that I could not communicate properly with my á closest friend.
When I tried to explain to my child as to why there were á magazines wiith naked girls on them at the kiosk.
When I stole a packet of cigarettes from a neighbour  and the á next day I owned up and returned it.
When I was forced to decline the invitation to my mother's 70th á birthday because of my work committments in another area.
When I began dansing, the teacher came and told me that I was á very good and would soon get into the ballet academy.
A late Saturday night I found myself locked in the central á underground station of Stockholm with a group of 50 hard rockers á who were drunk and equipped with various kinds of chains, etc.

When I was forced to call the telephone company about a bill á concerning a disconnected phone belonging to my landlord.  The á bill was four months overdue and in the meanwhile he had been á using my phone, he seemed to have no intention of having his own á phone reconnected.
Whenever I read or think about the way people treat animals and á nature.
When I saw a T.V programme on animals in the film world á (mistreated and used).
When I was 13 years old I wrote passionate love letters to my á boyfriend and I later found out that his sister had read them.
When my 6 month old son is happy and well.

I had an implicit agreement with my sister about meeting her, á however she had not understood the situation the same way so she á did not turn up.
I realized that the girl I loved had to leave me.
In the bus I was sitting next to a colleage who was drunk and á behaved in keeping with his state.
I had promised to help out with domestic chores and I forgot á about it.
I had promised to call a girl but I did not do it.
When I unexpectedly received birthday greetings from a person I á like.
I returned home late from a party last night and I felt afraid á trying to anticipate the reaction of my father.
When I learned that my brother had spoilt an LP of mine.
When I came to know that a girl I was fond of already had a á boyfriend.
A too eager approach by a dirty drunken person in a bus.
I made a major mistake while learning how to use a computer programme á and the teacher criticized me.
I reproached my mother's cooking and criticised her á personality, and she felt hurt and depressed.
I shot the decisive goal in an ice-hockey match.
When I got lost in New York city a late friday night with a á friend of mine.
After having quarelled with a relative of mine about politics.
The death of my grandmother.
When I noticed that a nice person was being exploited á economically.
I slandered a person behind his back and he got to know about it.
I had quarelled with a friend of mine and I later realized that á it was also my fault.
I passed an exam which I was not sure at all to pass.  I rejoyced á at the result because the possibility of continuing my studies á depended on it.
In the traffic with a car, I nearly got crushed between a bus and á a tram.  The attention of other drivers saved me at the last moment.
I was disappointed and angry at the bad quality of a documentay á program on TV.  In my opinion, the topic was important and the á program should have been made with seriousness and consideration.

My father had a heart attack when I was not at home (I was still á living with them).  He recovered relatively well although he had á to retire (which implied relief from the stress of a small scale á enterprise).
At my grandmother's detestable and selfish conduct towards my á elder sister, although her behavior was due to senility and lack of á understanding.
I arrived late at a seminar concerning my major subject at á university, although I had been appointed to formally oppose the á paper which was being presented.

I had asked the Salvation Army to take away a piece of furniture á of mine, but I forgot to cancel the agreement (a friend of mine á took it) and I thereby caused the Salvation Army people some á unnecessary work.
On the cliff by the sea, the silence and the sudden voice of a á bird.(swans of the bay)
A dark night when I had to go to the outdoor lavatory.
When I realized that I was far behind the others in the language á course and I could no longer catch up with the others.
The long lasting illness of my grand-mother, and the changes in á family relationships caused by it.
Spoilt, smashed and molded potatoes in the fridge, and having to á clean up the dish later.
A truth expressed unthinkingly at a coffee party.  I realized á later that I had been inconsiderate, at a wrong moment and the á wrong place.
I did not go to the exercises, without any adequate reason.
When I got home from my job, I found a letter from the university á telling me that I had been admitted to begin my studies.
While watching TV (a war movie), I felt a strong fear of death, á threat and fear of loosing people close to me.
I was angry with a friend of mine who behaved in an affected á manner.

I made a long-distance call to people rather close to me and I á thought about the sad incident that had happened to them in the á near past; I knew that they were thinking about it too when I made á the call.
My parents inherited an appartment and this made them behave in a á peculiar manner.
When my friend let my personal matters be publicaly known.
When I think about my family (parents, brothers, sisters) guilt á is a part of my feelings.
I unexpectedly met a girl with whom I have always got along well. á ( I had not seen her for several months.)
When my father was very drunk and raging at home.
When I did not find the rack used for beating up rugs, in the á yard.
When one of my cat died of a disease.
I felt disgusted at the environment while getting back to my á student lodging. I did not see anything in the suburb which had á been planned by taking people's comfort into account.
My girlfriend was away visiting another city and I brought á another girl home. Next morning when I started getting sober I á felt quite ashamed of myself.
I got 100 FIM too much when I changed money at the bank.  They á soon called me at my job and the situation was embarrasing for á me.

In Sweden, a friend and I lived in an appartment owned by a Finn. á  One day, this man came back to the appartment heavily drunk á (hashish and alcohol).  He was quite dizzy and he broke down, and á I could not foretell his reactions.  However, nothing happened.
I had an appointment downtown, and the person in question was á half an hour late.
The death of my grandmother.
In the army, I had been in hospital for two weeks and as soon as á I returned to the company, a sergeant ordered me to fetch a load á on the tractor trailer.

On the way back from a Summer spent in Sweden, I drunk with a man á in the train.  I had drunk so much that when I got home I fell á asleep in the entrance hall.  I have never drunk that much, á neither before nor after that incident.  I was ashamed because my á mother and my sister had to see me in that state and my father á had to carry me to bed.
While at primary school, I did not let a friend ring a bell á although he would have liked to do it.  Afterwards I felt bad.
I got a fairly large amount of my taxes back.
I was jogging in the forest, in the central park area, when I saw á a man hiding behind a tree.  I got frigthened, turned around and á ran out of the forest.

I was coming home in a taxi with a fellow worker of mine.  He was á criticizing my earlier conduct towards him, which to my mind was á unfounded.  When I reached home, I ran out of the taxi and á slammed the door.
I had had a farewell party at the place where I had been working á for a year.  That night I could not fall off to sleep.  I was sad á thinking that I would not see my nice fellow workers again.
I was travelling in a local train when a drunkard, smelling á terribly, entered the same carriage and started eating fish that á was stinking.
While quarelling with a fellow worker of mine, I was vehement and á irritated and I told him what I thought of him in plain language.  á I was ashamed of myself when I met him the next day.
I was working as a secretary.  My boss was to go to give a á lecture, and wanted me to give him the exact address of the á place.
A sunny Autumn day, after a long rainy period.
Years ago, on my way to school by the forest path I came across á an exhibitionist.
A person close to me mistook my good intentions for bad, and á therefore associated unpleasant traits to me.
[ A person close to me told me that his positive regard depended á on my conduct.]
When an untidy and heavyly drunk person made endeavours to á approach me.
As a little girl, I was sick in the middle of a school day and I á vomitted in the basin of the classroom.
I lost my self-control and raised my voice at a child.
I got to know that I had been accepted at university.
I had been watching a TV-program on paranormal phenomena.  At á night I could not fall off to sleep as I feared that humanoids á were on the move.
My superior blamed me for some neglects at work in front of á others.  In fact, the task in question was not supposed to be á done by me.
My father suddenly fell ill and died.
When a friend of mine got drunk and started to blame and scorn my á other friends and me.
When I forgot a promise made to a friend of mine.
It was my turn to cook dinner.  I forgot a dish (the favourite of á the family) in the oven and it got burnt and was uneatable.
My joy was the joy of meeting again.  My husband came home after á having been away for weeks (for work).  I was on the railway á station to meet him.

A relative of mine had come to see my husband to talk to him á about a problem concerning his sister and me.  I was angry á because this relative of mine did not dare to speak to me and á instead spoke to my husband.  I got to know about it later the á same day.
The death of my father, even though we had not been very close to á each other.
The male friend of my mother (a widow) moved in to live with us.  á I did not like the man.
The death of my father made me feel quite guilty, because my á attitude towards him had been cold and indifferent.
My mother, sister and I were thinking about old times, our á childhood, and we had a very happy time.
My husband had gone to drive a strange, broken car.  At the á agreed time, he had not returned, and I feared that he had had an á accident.
I am a school teacher.  One of the classes does not obey me at all, á keeps on talking, does no work.  One afternoon, everything went á wrong, and I got exceedingly angry.
A young, close relative of mine died, leaving behind a baby a few á months old.

A series about Freud was shown on TV.  In it, a tampon had been á set in the nose of a woman, and forgotten there.  After great á pain it was taken off (close-up picture), the woman was bleeding á from the nose and the mouth.
I had promised to lend something to my mother-in-law and I forgot á it a couple of times.  When she asked me about it the third time, á I was ashamed at my absent-mindedness.
A borrowed car broke down while I was using it.  It was not my á fault, nevertheless I felt guilty.
I started a new branch of studies after having failed a former á one.  When I got back my exam papers I was very happy to know á that I almost had full marks.
I was diving below the ice, in a cave, at a depth of 26 metres.  á Visibility was almost zero and the oxygen level decreased á threateningly.  There were three of us divers on one safety rope.
My mother carried on using mental pressure concerning something á which was serious and a real burden to me.
My grandfather died, I went to the mortuary and saw the corpse.
[ The same as in anger.]
As a child when I was blamed for peeing in the swimming-pool.

A friend of mine was drunk and having an argument on the street á with a woman, appparently his girlfriend.  I was walking on the á other side of the street and thought that I was not supposed to á interfere.  Later I heard that he had shot himself that evening.
My girlfriend sent me a letter with a shiny picture in it.
I was about to begin a journey in a car with an acquaintance of á mine.
On the TV news I heard that Nicaragua had complained about the á increasing threat of war with the USA.
My girlfriend gave me the mitten (left me).
Watching a violent movie.
The morning after a wild party.
I feared that I would have to describe my sexual life to an á older, strange woman.
When I moved away from home.
The inflammation of the ear of my child got cured and the doctor á said that the ear was completely all right.
My husband suddenly fell ill seriously and during the medical á examinations we did not know what would follow.
The housing council asked the city to cut 40 linden trees so that á the inhabitants of the lower floors would have a view to the sea.
My child, unexpectedly started acting in a restless and á disturbing way at school.  In addition his performance at school á weakened.
On a trip abroad, a lady-like member of our group turned out to á be an alcoholic.  She spoilt many days of my holidays because of á her behaviour and paranoia.
I failed an exam which I thought I would certainly pass.
I had been guilty of gossiping and blaming others, and one of my á superiors at the workplace made a formal reprimand.
When a student of mine (at music) performed and played remarkably well.
When climbing up the stairs to the top of a ski-jumping hill.
My boy-friend came home late one night without having told me á about it before.
The breaking up of a long lasting relationship.
When I noticed that a person I found attractive had seen me á picking my nose.
When I think that I have been too stict or narrow minded towards á my students.
When I made up with a girl-friend of mine after having been on á unfriendly terms with her (my fault).  I cried with joy that á evening.
While cycling in the country, I came across a large herd of á cows.
When I heard that my step-mother had treated my mother in a wrong á manner.
When my friend did not pass the high school graduation á examinations.
When I heard about the advances an acquaintance of mine had made á to my friends, who did not approve of them.
When after having had sexual intercourse with a friend, I thought á that he had told about it to a friend of his.
When I promised a male friend of mine to visit him, and did not.
During lectures, I sensed an unexpressed understanding with a boy á I did not know.  We exchange glances ; I think he likes me, and I á like him too.  Perhaps he has fallen in love with me .........
At night, I walk home past a forest.  Once, somebody got stabbed á in the forest.  I imagine someone attacking me and I hurry up.

In a tram, the ticket seller was commanding, taking the role of a á leader, trying to emphasize her non-existent authority with undue á strictness towards a good-humoured drunk who could not find his á ticket at once.
A relationship in which I had put my trust, broke up.  I was sad á when I realized how easy it is to forget something that one had á once regarded as great and significant.
A nightmare.  I was dreaming about bloodsuckers, which I tried to á shake off from my body, they are everywhere, they get glued, they á suck.  And there are a lot of them.  I panic.
I told evil lies about a close friend of mine.  I was evil in á order to sound jolly, to charm a person whom I wanted to impress. á  I sold my friend, I was despicable.
I met my ex boyfriend by chance.  We separated a few months ago á and I am now with a new boyfriend.  My ex boyfriend looked á depressed, and I know I am not to be blamed.
[ During inter-rail-trip, after troubles, I met my little á sister.]
Traveling as the only female in a railway carriage in the middle á of the night in Italy.
A male, Honduran acquaintance of mine despised my opinions.
When our dog died.
While walking on the street with a good friend of mine, we met an á acquaintance of hers.  My friend started showing off and telling á false stories about herself and praising herself.
I was dishonest to my boyfriend concerning something that is á important to our relationship.
A parking fine.
After having at last finished my master's thesis, I felt great á joy and relief.  I had been haunted by the thesis during the á whole of my studies.
While preparing my master's thesis, I was scared that I would not á accomplish anything as the subject was rather difficult.
During the Summer, at my workplace, a person kept interfering á with my tasks and making unfounded remarks.  I felt hatred for á him but it stopped when I realized that he just longed for attention.
The last time I felt sad and disappointed was when I did not do á as well as I had hoped in one of the final exams.  As compared á with the earlier exams, the questions, I think, were unjust.
After the first of May, I detested my fiance's friends, who had á piled on to our party and spoilt it completely.
After our sad first of May party, I felt ashamed because the á friends who had been invited had to suffer.  We, the organizers á of the party, did not drive the intruders away.

At my summer job, I was responsible for making various orders.  á It was not me who had ordered some seasonal merchandise, but when á much of it was left over and had to be thrown away in the Autumn, á I felt partly responsible for the much too large order.
When I met a good friend of mine after a long time.
I was camping with a friend of mine and we spent the night in the á forest.  I could not fall off to sleep and could clearly hear á noises from outside (steps ?) approaching our tent.
When I quarelled with my parents.
Being away from a very close friend, I was away from Finland á for a year as an exchange student.
When I saw a spider.
While playing I urinated on grandma's floor and did not go to the á lavatory.  My cousin told grandma and she came.
While travelling in a bus with an invalid ticket, I got caught.
While having a discussion with a colleague of mine, I realized that her á conception of man and work were similar to mine.
While he was drunk, my life partner tried to hit me.  I felt á scared and fled to the bathroom.
I could not meet my love, after having waited for a month, due to á illness.
Once again, my life partner came back home drunk at midnight.
My love and me rented a room in a hotel one evening.  We stayed á there a few hours and when leaving the hotel, I felt ashamed.
[ I had, by being silent, disapproved my love and made him á unhappy.  He had not been able to keep his promise.  I thus was á thinking about my own conduct towards another person.]
I had just moved to the town where I study and I got a postcard á from a good friend (from my home town).
They had returned much less of my taxes than I had expected.
After my boyfriend and I had separated.
In the morning, the cat of my landlady had vomited on the floor, á near the staircase I take to go to the bathroom.
My boyfriend's mother, whom I had not met earlier, made an á unexpected visit.  I was lying lazily on the bed, reading a á newspaper and my boyfriend was studying.
The cat of my landlady escaped through the window which I had á left open.
I got a letter from my best friend, whom I had not heard from for á a long time (a good letter).

Someone knocked on the door when I was alone at home (though á there was a door bell).  I looked through the peep hole but it á had been covered.  I called my sister but she could not help me á as she was hundreds of kilometres away.
My parents put pressure on me to buy clothes, when I would not á have liked to do so.
When my grandfather died, I saw my grandmother crying against my á aunt's shoulder (I had never seen my grandmother cry before).
At school, I detested the spinach gruel which had lumps of flour á in it.
I told some acquaintances of mine something that I regretted á later.
[ I speak harshly to my parents though they only mean my own á good.]
When I got a letter from home.
While cycling in the country a dog started running beside me, á growling and barking, and trying to bite my foot.
Disagreements with mother.  When I moved from KankaanpSS, she had á promised to help me move but broke her promise because of some á hindrance.
When I had to move away from home to study, and I knew that I á would not be coming back home for a long time.
When I noticed two spiders running on the floor in different á directions.
When I realized that I had been wrong about a person close to me, á because of pre-set ideas and prejudices.
When I reproached my friend because I was myself low-spirited and á disappointed.
I found myself a place after looking for one for a long time.
[ In an aeroplane.]
I was angry at my boyfriend who had promised to come to see me á but did not because he spent the evening with his pals.
The breaking up of a relationship.  We decided that the á relationship could not carry on, so it was no surprise to me. á And anyhow, I had known it would happen sooner or later.
The disgust I feel towards a certain person.
After an event in which I felt that I had acted unfairly.
At my job, I got disproportionately angry with a child.  My á reaction was not as it should have been.
I went to see the entrance examination results at university.  I á rejoyced at my success.
I borrowed a car which was supposed to be used for a long journey á a few hours later, and one of the tyres burst in the middle of á the town and I did not know what to do.
An utterance, which I had intended to be a joke, was taken as an á offence.  In my opinion, this was stupid, and I got angry.
My best friend had a relatively severe illness.  I was sad á because she was suffering.
A man tried to have sexual intercourse with me, though I had á communicated my unwillingness.  Later on, I felt disgust at that á person as well as myself because I had partly submitted.
I told my friend about how I had calculated my salary by cheating a á little.  When my friend remarked about it, I understood that it á was wrong to do so, and I felt ashamed.
I am going steady with a boy, but I had sexual intercourse with á another one, and I felt guilty about it afterwards.
A good report card (a scholarship) in primary school.
I was walking home with a friend at night along a quiet street.  á Something started rustling in the bush : it was an exhibitionist.
I got angry at a friend of mine whom I caught reading my notebook á (almanach).
When my grandmother died of cancer.
In a lift a drunken, fat and untidy man tried to make advances at á me.
[ Sometimes I have by accident said to another person something á in which it is easy to read a negative attitude.]
For the sheer pleasure of it, I quarelled with my boyfriend who was trying  á to be especially kind to me.
When I made the acquaintance of a certain person.
When abroad, while driving a car along a dark, winding road.
When my sister took my things without having asked for my permission á first.
When my grandfather died.
When I was working, I got treated in a way which I felt was not á democratic.
While working as a domestic helper, one day I had not cleaned up á very well and they made a remark about it.
When I decided to move away from my parent's home, my mother told á me that it was as if a part of her had been torn out of her.
When I went to a job interview, I met a person who was very nice, á and his attitude made me glad.
My episode of fright happened when I came to study.  I had to á stand in front of my still unknown fellow students and talk about á myself.  My hands shook, I flushed and became tongue-tied.

I felt guilty when I spent a night at my boyfriend's place, á particularly because I had been harsh and spiteful when I had á left home.  The reason was that I feared a possible discussion on á the subject and I wanted to leave defiantly.
I was in a restaurant with my boyfriend when I saw my best female á friend after not seeing her for two weeks.  We rejoyced, hugged á and had a long talk.

One evening, while going to meet a friend of mine, I had to cross á a meadow by a dark road.  There were bushes on the other side of á the road.  The weather was damp and a bit foggy.  I heard steps á behind me and kept speeding up my steps all the time.
My brother told me that a person (whom I know) had insulted him.  á I am very fond of my brother, and as he himself can not get angry á or hurt, my protectiveness was aroused and I got angry.

My guinea-pig had been ill for a couple of days.  One evening, á when I came home I enquired as to how it was doing.  My mother's á expression told me that it had died.  My knees refused to support á me and I began to weep convulsively.
I happened to see two boys fighting, one of them fell down and á hurt his head.  The other one used this to spank the head of the  boy on the ground.

I had been away all night without having told my parents about á it.  In the morning when I came home, my mother looked tired.  á She said that she had been awake all night because of me and that á she was angry and disappointed.

I had not written to, or called my grandmother, who was lonely, á for a long time.  My mother asked me to call her on her behalf á and when I did so, my grandmother was delighted and she told me á that she had been waiting for some news from us.
When I was sick my husband bought me a piece of cake.
I saw a man who had had a heart-attack and who was being á treated for it.  I feared that my own father could have been á there.
When I saw a big man hit another one, and nobody did anything.
When my sister left to go home, in Sweden, after the Christmas á Holidays.
I feel guilty as I am not working, and even my studies are not á progressing.
When my red-cheeked, content child runs to meet me in the yard of á the kindergarten and gives me a moist kiss on my cheek.
A neighbour's girl had disappeared and many people were looking á for her.  Someone had gone to notify the police.  Something had á certainly happened to her.
Without my permission, my son had made popcorn after coming back á from school.  The consequences were a spoilt kettle and chaos in á the kitchen but what could have happened with the hot grease ?
The death of a close relative.
One of my fellow students used questionable and unfair means to á advance her studies faster than others.  I detested her.
My friend told me in a fairly loud voice the blunders she á committed last night.
I stopped my car in front of a pedestrian crossing as a child was á crossing the street.  The car driving in the next lane did not á stop and the child got hurt.  Had I not stopped ...

After my vacations, one day after a lecture it occured to me to á buy a rose for my mother.  We went together to a pub and my á mother told me that she would be getting married next Spring.  I á did not known about it and so was all the more glad.

I work at a day care centre, and one day when the children were á outdoors a four-year old boy disappeared from the yard.  I was á not looking after them then, but as the manager it was me who was á responsible.
I was on my way home by bus.  A man who had drunk a fair amount of á alcohol started talking, trying to hug and pat a woman sitting á next to him.  Fortunately it was not me.
I gave a wrong answer at school.
When my little brother asked me to play with him, I told him that á I had no time and that I would play with him the next day. á However, the next day I said the same thing.
When, after a long time, I saw a girl with whom I was in love.
When I was walking on a fairly out-of-the-way street.
A friend of mine had promised to arrange me some tickets for a á concert which I considered important.  He could not get them the á way he thought he would, so he gave up the whole thing.
I was sad when I saw that a beautiful girl was not attainable.
While attending some affairs, which were taking some time, with á a bank officer, I felt that my clothes and appearance were out of place, too á raggy.
One evening I went out with some friends of mine, although I was á supposed to stay at home with my little sister who is 11.
While watching an entertainment program in which there was a clever  á and amusing sketch.
When I was in the army, a room mate of mine came back from á furlough and threatened another fellow with a knife.
The last day of school is traditionally celebrated by singing a á song about all the students who are leaving.  In the song á about me, there were things which irritated me a lot.
I worked for seven months in a factory, and made friends with a á fellow worker.  Later, I visited my former fellow workers and was á told that, while in the army, my friend had shot himself.
The behaviour of a fellow towards me and some others in the army á was really mean.  I detested this.
I tried to date a girl, but she refused.
While doing some calculation exercises, I neglected a part of it, á though I had marked it as done.  By chance, I was asked to á demonstrate this very part on the blackboard.
In the army, my result at the shooting exercises got á me a three day furlough.

When I was 8 years old, I would usually come home from school á with my mother in a car.  For the first time I had to take the á school bus, and I mistook the bus stop and found myself two á kilometres away from where I lived.  I was very scared, wondering á how I would get back home.

I read in the newspaper that the Student Lodging Fund was going á to build new appartments for refugees (in my opinion this is the á state's affair).  This is when only a fractoin of the students á can find an appartment.
I lead a rather secure life.  The only thing I can remember is a á song from the nineteenth century which is against alcohol.  Both á the melody and the word (although naive) effected my emotions.
Yesterday in the elevator a man started smoking, this is á something I just can not tolerate.
In primary school I once faltered while answering a question and á the others started laughing.
[ Generally when I am shopping I feel like I were guilty of all á the thefts through the year (I have never stolen).]
When my favourite football team made a goal and was about to á win the Cup of England.
I was less than 10 years old when our neighbour's dog chased me á to the roof of a small shed and there seemed to be no hope of á getting away from there.
While playing a ball game, I was just about to make a goal when I á was thrown off my feet, and I failed to score the goal.
When I heard about the death of Frantois Truffaut, the French motion  á picture director, on the radio.  I had planned to go and see his á last film.
I had misbehaved at a party and did not wish to meet the person á in question later.
While playing a ball game, I made a mistake and we lost the game.
When I was in the sauna bath.
I had a dream in which I was an African elephant.
When I came for the lesson, it was cancelled and I had to fill in á a questionnaire instead.
When my car froze, and I could not start it.
When I saw our computer teacher.
When I was going downhill on skis, and fell down twice the first á time.
When I was involved in a car crash.
I passed an exam which I thought I had failed.
My mother had not come home at midnight.  She had forgotten to á tell me about it.  I was very young and all alone at home.
My girlfriend started singing (she cannot sing) and did not stop á despite my asking her to do so.
When my grandmother died of cancer.
When I was still a child, I saw a horror film on TV in which á there was a rotten human skull.
As a small boy, I took a coin from an empty taxi cab.  My mother á saw it and told the driver about it.  I even knew the driver.
When I betrayed my former girlfriend.

New Year's Eve party in the country, I hardly knew a person; my á partner spent most of the time at the bar. I had little á opportunity to get to know people because our table was separated á and my boyfriend's parents were present.
Christmas Eve: there was a tension between my parents, they did á not even try to restore a harmonic atmosphere. Mother stayed in á her room almost the whole day. I felt alone and was very sad.
Father said: If you are pregnant, you will have to procure á abortion. I was filled with disgust against my father.
I had an intimate relation with my boyfriend, but unfortunately á we had sexual problems; therefore I deceived him, but I was á ashamed when I told my friend about it.
I work at a commercial house from 7 to 10 a.m. On a very cold day á in winter I was late - and let a fellow worker stand in the cold á for half an hour.
After one year of searching, my friend and I have found a flat we á are able to pay for.
Car accident in the middle of the night.
At the weekend I wanted to be absent from school because of a á sports event, but my teacher refused to give me the day off á because he didn't like me.
When I was six years old, my favourite cat died.
A gigantic spider climbed over my face and what is more - in my á own flat.
I was very fat and felt absolutely unwell. I was afraid of á leaving the house and getting to know new people.
I was said to be responsible for my mother getting ill and á growing thin. I did not realize that it really was my fault until á several weeks later.
I won a car in a prize-competition. The moment I was informed á about it, I felt joy.
My sister had to undergo a very complicated operation, her á eyesight was at stake.
I had a quarrel with my parents; I was convinced to be right.
Scuffle in a carriage of the underground in Vienna, three drunk á men thrashed a man in a wheel chair - I watched the scene from á another carriage.
I put an end to a friendship with a girl - I had only pretended á love and affection to be able to sleep with her.
A young girl tried to put an end to her life because of lover's á grief; not until she was in hospital I heard that I had been the á reason for her action.

In order to be admitted to my final examination, I had to pass á two examinations. As I had not studied very much, I resigned á myself to be left behind. Nevertheless I succeeded in these á examinations.
I had not told my parents about my bad marks in school. One day, á my father wanted to speak to the teachers. Fortunately I could á influence my parents to take it easy.
I wanted to go to a friend of mine who had a party; at the moment á I wanted to leave, my father said I couldn't go because he needed á me for some work in the afternoon.
A friend of mine, who had repeated a year at school once before, á did not pass the final examination and had to take it again half á a year later.

Eco-activists demonstrated against a project to build a power station á at the Danube in the middle of a lowland forest (Hainburg) and á the government decided to delay it for another year. When my á father heard about it, he said that we needed another Hitler.
There was a time when my room looked terribly untidy; just at á that time my aunt came to see me; fortunately I could prevent her á from entering the room.
I was supposed to fetch some friends at the bus stop, but I did á not do it because my father was in a bad mood and I was afraid á that he would grumble.
My boyfriend returned after a long absence.
My car skidded on the wet street.
I wanted to see a friend, I had been looking forward to it and á had certain expectations, but he did not pay any attention to me, á played cards with other people.
A good friend quitted me after he had behaved in a strange á manner.
In broad daylight I saw an untidy old man pissing and playing á with his penis in the middle of the town.
Somebody who knows me very well discovered that I had told him a á lie.
When my boyfriend was away, I flirted with his best friend; I á felt guilty the next day.
My favourite horse died. We had tried our best to save him, but á it was hopeless, he had to be shot.
I read a book about the sexual phantasies of women; I read about á a woman having sexual intercourse with a dog.
In our flat the bath-tub is in the kitchen. At the beginning I á had very intensive feelings of shame when I had a bath and people á were in the kitchen.
I had to take care of the plants of a friend of mine for several á weeks. I watered them, but let them stand in a cold room so that á two of them perished.
When I met a good friend after a long time. We had had a quarrel á but after two weeks I was really glad to see him again.
When we stayed in Vienna with our class, my friend and I behaved á incorrectly. Our teacher threatened us with exclusion from á school.
When I lost my driving license because I had been driving while á under the influence of alcool.
My mother's death.
When I entered the dissecting room for the first time. I think I á felt disgusted mainly because of the bad smell of formaline.
I think I felt ashamed for the first time when I entered a night á club.

During a ski tour with a friend, we two had drunk too much. When á we went down the slope on ski, I lost my friend who had lost his á way. I thought that something must have happened to him (he á finally arrived but after a very long time).

My father stayed abroad for one year. He does not like to write á letters because he makes ortographic mistakes. I never had a good á relation to him. He wrote me a letter in which he said that he á loved me.
When I was a child, I was always afraid of my father. Just when á he looked at me, I felt frightened.
A colleague asked me to study with her. I could not explain á things as perfectly as she had expected. So she reacted in an á aggressive manner.

During the Christmas holidays, I went to see my parents and á stayed with them for two weeks. After two or three days, we had á the same conflicts we had had ten years before when I had lived á with them. They were glad when I left.
Old man in hospital, hollow-cheeked, only one half of his nose á and glass-eye, rattling breath.
When my father came into the bathroom and saw me standing there á naked.
I live with my boyfriend, we have a close relationship, I fell in á love with another man.
When I met my girlfriend - I had not counted on that.
One night I had a feeling that somebody was stealing my car, á but I was too frightened to go and see.
When we rearranged furniture in our flat and got stuck in a á chair.
A person died (not really a friend).
Several weeks ago, I had problems with friends, I felt disgusted á by a friend.
When I was a child, I thought that I had to be ashamed when á asking and doing certain forbidden things.
When quarreling with friends.
In Southern Tyrol, I was gathering apples, it was a fine day, I á was not thinking about anything, I felt an overwhelming joy.
My girlfriend and I slept in a lonely hut (we had drunk alcool). á Suddenly some soil fell on us, then some water. Although we tried á hard, we could not find out the cause.
I helped my little sister (13 years) learning mathematics. á Obviously she did not want to understand what I explained and á started to cry. I grew angry.
When my girlfriend told me that she wanted to leave me.
On a trip I passed by a cellulose factory. It was a fine day, á beautiful landscape; I observed this factory with disgust.
When I went to a sauna with my father for the first time (I was á 16). When I entered the sauna naked, I felt ashamed for a short á time.
I came home from a discotheque at half past four in the morning, á although I had promised my parents to come home at midnight. From á 3 a.m. I felt guilty towards my parents.
A friend I had missed very much came to see me unexpectedly.
On my way through lonely streets I met with a huge stray dog. It á stopped at some distance and looked at me. I tried to ignore it á but I was very frightened.

A friend of mine tried to persuade me to go at her place to act á as a model because she felt too tired. It was a quarter of an á hour before the appointed time, I had just lied down and did not á want to go because it was too late anyway. She said that I only á was talking about looking for work, but if it was possible I á would not accept it. I was angry about this unjust judgment.
After I had lived with my boyfriend in a foreign country for half á a year, I saw that it was impossible for me to stay with him (for á economic reasons). We separated although I loved him.

In a certain book I read about cruelties and violence in prison á and souteneur circles; I felt especially disgusted when I read á detailed descriptions of physical and mental torture of less á powerful people.
When I talked to a psychotherapist for the first time, I started á to cry; first I talked to him but he did not say anything and á after a while I was crying.

I went shopping with my mother and sister (17 years old). Mother á always told my sister what she should buy. Instead of assisting á my sister in defending herself against mother's interference, I á just behaved aggressively towards my sister.

It was on St. Claus Day when I was five years old. St. Claus and á his Devil Servant came to see me. St. Claus' Devil Servant á rattled with his chain and bowled terribly. I was so frightened á that my parents had to ask him to leave.

A friend called me and told me that she wanted to come and see á me. She lived in a village at 50 km distance fom my home town. á Next morning I expected her but she didn't arrive. As I got á impatient I called her but her parents told me that she had gone á skiing. I was very angry because I had cancelled an appointment á to be able to see her.
When I was eight years old my father was run over by a car. When á I saw his body I was sad beyond words.

A friend prepared a soup with chicken heads and invited me to eat á it. I saw the eyes staring at me and the tongues hanging out of á the bills. I was so disgusted that I felt nausea and had to leave á the room.
When I had to go to the gynecologist and to sit on that special á chair, I felt ashamed.
After a terrible quarrel with my family, I withdrew in my room. I á felt guilty because I had caused this scene by my aggressive á behavior.
I had the unexpected possibility to see a friend I like very á much.
I was afraid of a certain examination although I was relatively á well prepared.
At the hairdresser's, I got two stains of dyestuff on my new á trousers. These stains are not removable, so I cannot put on the á trousers again.
In 1977, my grandfather, to whom I had a very close relationship, á died.
A drunken man forced me to kiss him.
A friend started to insult another person without reason and I á felt ashamed of her behavior.
I had to call somebody between 12 and 12:30. As I had no á possibility to call him at this time, I did not do it until 3 á p.m.
After a one year's stay abroad, I returned home. I was even more á glad to see how much my family was pleased to see me.
I went home all alone from a restaurant. It was dark, I went very á fast. Behind me, there were some drunk men who shouted at me. By á chance, I met some friends who accompanied me.
A friend who shares the room with me, opened the window in the á morning and left the room the whole day. When I came home in the á evening, the room was so cold that I couldn't stay there.
When my aunt, whom I had loved very much, died. When I heard á about her death, I was not as touched as at the funeral. I really á became conscious of her death at that moment.

A friend told me how he managed to win the sympathy of as many á people as possible. He said he first listened to what they said á and then he tried to only say things they would like to hear. á He would never express his own opinion. I felt really disgusted á when he told that.

In a restaurant, I made the acquaintance of a boy who always told á the same things in a very loud voice. I laughed and said to him á that he always repeated the same things. Some time later I heard á that he had undergone a complicated brain operation.
After closing the front door I realized that I had left the key á inside the house. I felt even more guilty since it was not my own á house but the house of people I hardly knew.
When I was informed that a short story I had written had been á accepted for publication.

Some friends and I were crossing a street when one of my friends á was seized by a car and thrown aside. I had seen the car coming á in our direction but I did not have enough time to react and á prevent the accident.

I wanted to clear up a misunderstanding with a friend that I had á caused. A third person meddled in our conversation, turned my á efforts to ridicule so that I did not succeed in what I had á intended.
Death of my grandmother.
In school I had difficulties mith mathematics. When I had to work á for an examination, I really felt disgusted.
I played in a stage play. Suddenly, in front of 200 people, I á could not remember the words I had to say.
One night I did not come home without telling my parents and I á did not want to speak about it afterwards. My mother cried. I had á a bad conscience and felt guilty.
After 3 weeks I saw my girlfriend again.
One evening, in the tramway, I was afraid of two drunk men á molesting my girlfriend and me.

During the Christmas holdidays I wanted to invite my brother, his á girlfriend and their child for dinner. When I said to my á brother's girlfriend that I would like them to come at my place á for dinner, she refused and never mentioned it again as if I á had never asked her.
Several years ago my brother died in an accident. When I heard á about it, I was very sad. It took years until I resigned myself á to it.
I read a book about the situation in South-Africa, about the á terrible violations of human rights. I was disgusted with the á white population.
My P.T. instructor also works as a masseur. He wanted to massage á me, therefore I had to undress. For the first few times this was á not easy for me; I got gradually used to it.
Some time ago I took the driving test. I did answer the á theoretical questions very well, but I failed the practical á driving test. It was my fault because I had not enough practice.

When my brother came back home after staying in hospital. He had á undergone an operation which had been a matter of life or death. á When he came home I could see him smile for the first time after á may weeks.

After a short stay in Marocco we missed the ferry-boat back to á Spain and we had to look for an accomodation. By chance we met a á man who offered to take us to a camping site. While I was sitting in his á car I was terribly afraid because I had heard of people being á robbed in Marocco.
After an exhausting day I came home and wanted to take a bath to á relax. My father wanted to take a bath first and when he had á finished after an hour, there was no hot water left for me.
I met some nice people during my holdidays. When they left I knew á that I would never see them again.

A drunk man attacked his wife and wanted to humiliate her by á insulting her. Then he turned violent and started to beat her in á front of her child. She left it happen without saying a word in á order not to make things worse. I watched the scene and tried to á calm the man, but without success. Just because he was stronger á we had to comply. From that day I detested him.

For a medical check-up, we - boys and girls - had to take off our á clothes with the exception of our underwear. Then we had to go á into another classroom where older pupils were sitting and á staring at us.
I allowed my little brother to clean the bathroom in his own way. á My mother came and saw the floor overflowed with water, slapped á my brother in the face and told him to go to bed immediately.
One day I did not feel very well and I wanted to talk to á somebody. A friend invited me for dinner and I was very glad.
I was driving my car and it was very misty. It was in the night á and I was alone in my car. I felt totally insecure, nervous and á overstrained.
My mother treated me unjustly as if I was a little child. I said á mean things. I was unable to defend myself adequately.
When my uncle died whom I had loved very much. I was very sad and á I felt totally helpless.

When I was a child I was afraid of big dogs. One day when I came á home a big dog was laying in front of our door. I was so á frightened that I did not dare to enter the door and I waited á until somebody passed by.

I share my small flat with my friend. On her birthday we could á not see each other until evening because we had to stay at the á University all day. In the evening I left a lecture before it á finished to be able to buy flowers for her. When I was at home á she called me to tell me that she would stay the night with her á boyfriend.
