When I was a child I had a grass-parakeet I liked very much. His á legs were crippled so that he could not move very fast. Once I á came into the room, did not notice him and stepped on him. A few á days later he died.
When I was younger I often saw my father come home drunk (he had á big problems at that time). Once he woke me up in the middle of á the night and shouted at me.

At school I was bad in mathematics. Although my teacher had á admonished me to do my homework, one day I had forgotten to do á it. When my teacher noticed it, I blushed and was ashamed to be á rebuked in front of the other pupils.á
When I was a child I often quarrelled with my younger sister. á Once I became so angry that I slapped her in the face. She cried á and shouted so that my mother came in and scolded me.
After a weekend at a seminar I saw my husband again. I hurried á home hoping he would be there. We embraced - I enjoyed feeling á his body.
One evening I stayed at home all alone. As we lived on the ground á floor, I was often afraid of burglers.
One day, when riding on a bicycle path, a car coming from the á opposite direction forced me to get off my bike although I had á the priority.
My father died unexpectedly at the age of 53 years. He certainly á would have liked to live longer. I was also said because I was á confronted with the fact that I would die one day too.
One day, when I was twelve years old, my brother took some slimy á substance swimming on the surface of a pot of vinegar made of á cider and threatened to throw it at me.
When I was ten years old a classmate laughed at me because I had á told him that my father had retired.
I felt guilty because I had not accomplished a thing as well as I á had wanted to.
A party with friends on New Year's Eve.
When I was hitch-hiking and I went with a man who drived like a á madman.
I met again a very good friend after a year and realized that á there had grown a certain distance between us.
When I listened to a conversation of friends talking about the á power of money.
When my grandmother died - at her funeral.
I read about a monk who had been murdered and put into a barrel á which was filled with blood of pigs.
I went for a walk with a very close friend; we were talking about á our problems, I told her lies.
I had to tell a collegue the time for an appointment with another á collegue. I told her the wrong time - it was obviously my fault.
I went to buy a bicycle with my father. When I wanted to pay, my á father took his purse and payed.
My mother had fallen down from a ladder when she had been á gathering cherries. Her back was hurt. Just when I arrived, I saw á people of the life-saving service giving her medical care.

I was waiting behind a car which was going to leave the parking á place, because I wanted to park my car there. Because of uncoming á traffic I had to wait for a short time - another driver placed á his car on the place.
My partner left me after we had been together for a long time.
At a weekend's seminar my trousers suddenly burst, therefore I was á prevented from participating in several activities.
When I was driving my motorbike I went into a bend incautiously á and fell down. I was slightly hurt, the motorbike was slightly á damaged.

Before Christmas I got to know a girl but our relationshop could á not consolidate before the holiday. Therefore it was a big á surprise to get a carefully hand-made present from her. - Our á relationship grew closer.
When I was a child, I fell into a cellar (when playing) and could á be freed only with big difficulties.
I was angry about several drivers who showed an aggressive and á dangerous driving habit.
When my grandmother died. I had a very deep relation to her (I á lived with her for several years).
Some time ago a girl tried to make me up without any action of my á part. She used all possible means. Although I behaved refusingly á she did not give up for a longer time.
When I went to the sauna for the first time and there were men á and women.
When I was parking my car I was not cautious and bumped into á another car. I caused considerable damage. The driver of the á other car was very angry and I let him insult me because I felt á guilty.
A person whom I had not seen for a long time called me and á invited me for a party.
When I was walking on the street, a group of drunk, bawling young á people approached.
When I was house-hunting: Another person got a flat that I would á have liked, too, because he heaped a floot of words on the á letter.
When my grandmother died.
When I shoplifted a pair of earrings from Coles and my Mum caught á me with them in my bag.
When my mother was tremendous on the phone and we talked for á hours. She was in a good mood.
When I saw a good male friend unexpectedly after a year, as I've á just returned from overseas. I was feeling tired, looking a mess, á and nervous.
When I wanted to talk to someone I liked and whom I have been á told likes me (by his brother and even by himself) however he á avoids any confrontation, and is vague.
After having left the company of someone who gave me a lot of á support and made me laugh, found myself alone for days on end.
When a boy had continued to use foul language and swearing in á front of a group of my friends.
When I was about seven or eight I was caught having stolen a á doll's dress from my next-door neighbour.
Feeling guilt after greed, buying chocolate and pigging out to á the point of feeling sick, especially as I am fat.
When planning to marry.
No really strong such emotion. Just falling off to sleep when I á caught sight of a 5 cm diameter spider crawling onto the pillow á beside me.
My feelings towards would-be in-laws for their participation in á recent broken relationship.
Recent break-up of seriors long-term relationship, helped along á by would-be  in-laws.
After failing a second attempt at Med 4, following a number of á difficult personal circumstances.
Failure to complete medical course as a result of failing fourth á year twice.
When Wayne and Sue (close friends) were announced our guardians á at ther wedding.
Car accident nearly occurred between us and drunk driver coming á in opposite direction it missed us by approx 1 m and collided á (after rolling twice midair) into nearby scrub.
When boyfriend lied to me.
When my boyfriend took me to his father's grave.
On boat trip - saw mother giving young child (aprox 6-7 years) á cigarettes.
When harassed by this boy - it was sexual (refer to GUILT).
When in grade 3, late home from school every day for weeks á because of harassment from a grade 7 boy I lied to mother about á why I was home late.
Getting a part-time job.
Small car accident. Black ice on the road - cars in front of us á started zig-zagging and so did we. Car in front did a 180¦ turn we á followed and ended up in a gully.
People hunting animals.
When my grandfather was sick, and died I felt more sad, though, á when he was sick.
People spitting in railway stations.
Falling over.
Eating too much I felt guilty afterwards because I knew I á shouldn't have overeaten as I'm putting on too much weight.
When my last year's second semester results came through - I was á ecstatic.
I was sleeping in my room but woke in the middle of the night to á think I could hear noises and see shadows moving. I felt that á someone was in the house.
At school, a couple of years ago, a so-called acquaintance told lies á about me to a teacher I was told about it by friends who overheard á the conversation.

My grandfather died. He lived almost as a recluse not caring for á himself as well as he should - Dad and we all helped as much as á we could, but it didn't save him from himself. It was an á unexpected death. His second de facto wife was lucky she wasn't á jailed.
In my penultimate job I was responsible of a sections with á several employers, after several years of dedication I was á dismissed by a new chef, saying that I was incompetent.
I assisted to a scene where the police attacked a person that á didn't have his documents. The savagery was too much, and the á attacked person bleeded to much.
In a party of friends I got completely drunk.
Once in my homes yard, I was plaing football with my cousin and á in a certain quick the ball went on uncontrolled putting down a á bird-cage, killing it.
When I get something that seemed very hard like getting a job, a á boyfriend, etc. A specific sutuations, was when I started to date á a boy whom I liked for a long time.
When I had to assume a position which I didn't expect.
When I was dismissed unjustly from the firm where I worked, á because there where persons that didn't have problems, and á wouldn't miss in the jobs they occupied if they were dismissed.
I felt very sad when I had to give up something that by right was á mine and although I didn't get it, a kind of suvenir that people á don't give you the right to have.
The acts of brutal violence in generally disgusts me. Fights, á phisical aggrssion, etc.
I felt ashamed when in a certain occasion I had to read a text á and didn't stop stuttering.
When I was reproved eighth grade of high school.
When I talked with a teacher yesterday who, to say the least, was á rude and unwise and had irrelevant opinions about a friend.
The loss of the woman who loved me most till today.
In a sexual experience with an unknown woman where after the á sexual act I only could go away without looking backwards.
When I wanted to kiss a friend and didn't succeed, I felt shame.
On a telephone talk where I was agressive and stupid without the á least, reason or better motive.
When I succeed in writing something I felt and doing it I felt á well and very happy for being able to express to myself something á that was suffocating me.
When I crashed my car.
When in a difficult moment I couldn't express myself correctly á and my thought came out with distortions bringing about highly á negative and distorted results.
When I heard about the death of somebody I liked very much and I á was not present either to see the person or to try to share my á emotions with other friends.

When I saw a woman subjugated by money and not being able to hide á how she hated herself for not having the will power to get out of á such a situation because it was convenient, according to what she á told me.
When somebody suddenly said something (about me) at a wrong á moment and I didn't agree (at that exact moment I was needing an á extremely positive word).
When my mother surprised me while masturbating.
I forgot to water the flowers in our flat and was rebuked by my á friends who share the flat with me.
After my final examination at school I was glad that the á examination was over and that I had passed it.

When I was a child, I had a nightmare. At that time, I was not á yet able to tell anybody about it, so I was very frightened. I á could not explain myself all that and I had to deal with it by á myself.
I was angry with a person who behaved terribly at a ball á offending her relatives.
When my grandfather died. When I heard about his death, I had a á bad feeling in my stomach and I felt as if I had lost something á very precious.
My brother caught a spider and let his frog eat it.
Once I spoke without thinking very much - it was quite a á nonsense.
I was not sure whether I should help an old woman going down a á flight of stairs. I just watched her and saw how difficult it was á for her to do it.
For about one year I had a rather bad relation with my father. á Last Christmas Eve he invited me to stay withhim and I was very á glad about it. It was a fine evening.

I live outside Graz - so I have to go by bus. One day I went home á from the bus stop alone. It was dark, I had to go through a á forest and there was a dark figure behind me. I was very á frightened.
My sister had promised to help me to do a translation from á English into German. But the day I needed her she told me that á she was busy - I was very angry.
Several years ago my mother died. She had been ill for a long á time, but nevertheless her death came unexpectedly. I did not and á I still do not want to believe that it is true.
I have a horror of spiders and snakes. On a walk through the wood á I saw the body of a slow-worm (without the head).
I came home from a party rather drunk. I said things I would á never have said normally. Next morning I was terribly ashamed á about what I had said.
An accident happened to my little cousin because I had not taken á enough care of her. She fell on the floor and her hands were á hurt.

I had a little cat which was very sick. As I liked it very much I á went to a veterinary with it. He told me how to tend it and it á really recovered its health. Everybody said that I had saved its á life.

When I was a child, I had a terrible nightmare with St. Nicholas' á Devil Servant. I asked my mother if he really existed and she á said yes. The following nights I could not sleep and a á light had to be left turned on.
As I usually do not start learning until a short time before an á examination,, I once made up my mind to try to work for a longer á time. But once again I did not do it - and got a bad mark.

A friend told me about his cousin who is my girlfriend. He said á she had treated him in a mean and nasty way. I was surprised á because in front of other people she had always treated him in a á friendly way. I am very sad about it.
I went out with my sister, her boyfriend and his friend. I did á not like this young man. But suddenly he overcame me and kissed á me. He was very strong so that I could not defend myself.
During the oral part of my final examination I made a mistake in á speaking so that all the teachers laughed at me.
There was a time when I did not get on well with my sister. I á always grumbled at her and said bad things about her to my á mother. So my mother always scolded her.
When I passed my final examination at school.
When I was on a cave excursion with friends, I suddenly lost them á and was afraid of losing my way in the cave.
When I felt being treated unjustly by a teacher.
When my grandmother died; I had a stronger relation to her than á to my mother.
When I was molested by an old drunk man.
When I had a Latin examination in school.
When I had drunk too much and nearly got an alcohol poisoning.
When I met my girlfriend again in another town after a long á separation.
When I went home alone early in the morning, I had to go through á a wood.
A friend was unpunctual, we wanted to prepare ourselves for an á examination.
When my grandparents moved to another part of the town.
At the butcher's I saw an animal which had just been slaughtered; á blood was dripping on the floor.
In school I was very bad in running long distances and my á class-mates laughed at me for this reason.
I had to take care of my little brother. When I met a friend I á did not pay attention to him for a certain time and he was hurt á while he was playing.
On my birthday, an old friend of mine sent me a card. I had not á met him for a year and I was very glad that he had thought of me.
Once I spent a night with a friend at the secondary school. We á told each other horror stories and suddenly we heard uncanny á noises. I was terribly frightened.

When we still attended school, my brother and I usually went to á see our aunt and to show her our term's report. She rewarded us á with money. Although my reports were as good as my brother's, he á got more money.
My friend was pregnant, but lost her child during the second á month. I went to see her at hospital - she was crying. I felt á very sorry for her.
When I attended school, our class visited an institution for á mentally and physically handicapped persons. Although I tried to á control my feelings, I was disgusted.
After a party I spent the night with a friend. We both were á drunk, the morning was disillusioning. A friend was me leaving á the room and I felt shabby and immoral.
I had to take care of a neighbour's child. I did not look after á it all the time and the child fell down and was hurt. I felt á guilty.
A very good friend of mine had been away for three months. When á we met again, we ran up to each other and embraced.

One evening my father told me to go into the cellar and get him a á beer. I was terribly frightened at the idea of a man sitting in á the cellar and assaulting me. For my defence I took an empty á bottle with me.
I had stolen a bottle of rum from a person who knows me well. He á threatened to call the police if I did not pay 500 Shillings.
When my uncle died I saw a funeral for the first time. All people á stood around the open grave and cried.
At a party I met a girl who drew me to her, told me some nonsense á and always wanted to kiss me.
I put my head into the pullover of a girl to see her breasts. The á girl looked at me so that I felt ashamed.

My uncle had promised to buy me a bicycle. As time went by and I á had not received it yet, I asked my father to buy it for me. á Later I heard that my uncle had wanted to offer me the bicycle on á my birthday two weeks later.
Several days after my final examination at school, I was sitting á in an airplane on my way to Greece. I enjoyed that moment very á much.

One night I was lying in my bed awake but I had my eyes closed. I á saw figures with terrible faces and black frocks bending over me á and touching me. I opened my eyes but I could still see them. I á had the feeling that somebody was in the room. It was terrible. á Only when I turned on the light I was able to go to sleep.

I had arranged with a friend to go with him to Carinthia by car. á We had arranged a place where to meet. I was a bit late and my á friend had left already. I had no money to go by train. I nearly á started to cry because I was so angry - it was very important for á me to go to Carinthia.
Our dog had to be shot because he had killed a roe. I liked him á very much and so I could not resign myself to that. I hated the á hunter who shot him.

I was sitting in a station-hall and watching a lavatory á attendant. She was very dirty. She started to eat something out á of a dirty cup - it must have been something like lard. Then she á took some breadcrumbs out of the pockets of her apron and ate á them. I had to leave - I felt like vomitting.
I had to go to the doctor's because of a veneral disease. I told á the doctor that I must have been infected by my boy-friend. This á was not true, but I was ashamed to tell the truth.
When we were playing, I hurt my little sister, but towards my á mother I did not admit that it was my fault.
My neighbour was not able to set his car in motion because it had á snowed heavily. I helped him - he was thankful and invited me.
I was skiing with friends and they wanted to ski-jump. I did not á want to be left behind, so I braced myself and followed them.
At an examination I got a bad mark just because of a small á mistake. When I went to the lector and wanted to talk about that, á he did not listen to me but sent me away.
My cut was run over by a car. After searching for a long time I á found her lying in a kerb. I was rather shocked and angry with á the driver.
When I watched a report about El Salvador on TV, I saw people who á had been murdered by terrible methods.
At a cross-country race I wanted to take a short-cut (which is á not allowed). I was caught and disqualified. All my friends had á observed that.
During a discussion I reacted very aggressively and so I made it á impossible to continue discussing.
On my birthday I got a present that I had desired for a long á time.
When I am discussing something with a person and I realize that á the other person is thinking over her own argumentations instead á of listening, I become angry.
When we were on holidays my girl-friend had to leave me after 4 á weeks and I had to stay in Turkey for some more weeks because I á had a job there.
I studied medicine for several semesters. I was always disgusted á when we had the dissecting-course. I cannot understand why some á persons like this course.

Some time ago we had a tournament in our tennis-club. For á tactical reasons I was chosen to play against a much weaker á player than I am. Although it would have been enough simply to á win the game, I defeated him extremely. This would not have been á necessary.

I had a discussion with my girl-friend. After some time we á started to quarrel and at least - to get the upper hand - I said á that she was not as important to me as she might believe. Some á time later I apologized for that.
On New Year's Eve I went in a disco with friends. I amused myself á and got to know many other people.
I had to go to the dentist's. When he touched my tooth with his á drill, I was terribly aftaid of the pain I would feel any moment.
I was very hungry and just wanted to start eating when a friend á called me who usually talks for a long time. I was angry because á I was prevented from eating.
My sister, whom I like very much, asked me for a favour which I á refused her for some flimsy reason. Some time later I felt sorry á for that and something like sadness.
On my way to a concert I went with a man who tried to molest me. á At that moment I did not care much but now the impression fills á me with disgust.
I asked my friend to come with me to a disco because I wanted to á be with a person I know well. But when I amused myself with á others I let my friend sit alone, although I had asked her to á come.

I called my little sister to make her pick up her toy from the á floor. When she still refused after I had asked her for the á fourth time, we began to quarrel. At last the whole family was á involved in this quarrel and trouble was brewing.
I had a singing-lesson, but I was not very good. The last á exercise was singing scales. I did that very well and my teacher á seemed satisfied.
A teacher wanted to instill a certain opinion and a certain á behaviour into myself, what I refused. I was afraid when I saw á him.
A friend had promised to call me at a certain time. I expected á his call impatiently but in vain.
Years ago on Christmas Eve I felt very sad because I realized for á the first time how I missed my father who had died at Christmas á Years ago.
A man whom I like, was drunk and tried to molest me.

It was the time when everybody spoke about and discussed á Hainburg. I was also asked for my opinion. I was ashamed because á I had no firm view of the whole thing and therefor was not able á to join the conversation.

I had got a bad cold. My father said I must be crazy to go by á motorbike at those temperatures. When I answered him that I did á not care about a cold, he said that if I did not care for á anything I could leave him (it was for the second time he said á something like that).

I was at home alone when I realized that a young roe approached á our house. I hid because I did not want to frighten it. It á limped. Some time later, when I thought that it had already run á away, I saw it lying on our terrace. I came nearer and saw that á it was terribly wounded. I informed the ranger who said that the á roe must have been attacked by dogs. He had to shoot it.

Several years ago I stayed with friends in the mountains for one á week. We lived in a hut and had to cook for ourselves. One day my á friend did not succeed in preparing spaghetti. That dinner was á terrible - nevertheless we all ate rather much and had an á improper and unsavoury conversation.

My mother and my grandmother were talking about one of my á grandmother's friends whom I hardly know. I gave some deprecatory á comments on him whereupon my grandmother told me that the man had á died recently.

When I still went to primary-school, I went on a ski-trip with my á family. After skiing we went to a restaurant for lunch. Suddenly á my father said that he had forgotten something in the car. He á gave me the key and asked me to go and get it. I had difficulties á with the key which was already bent. I asked my mother to help á me. When she tried to turn the key it broke. We had no second á key. My mother was blamed for all that and I did not say a word.

I had not studied very much for my final examination at school, á so I had to take an additional examination in French. The oral á examination was not very hard for me - the more I was glad when I á heard that I had passed it.
When I was 8 years old my tonsils had to be operated on. This is á not a complicated operation, but just before it started I was á very afraid so that I will never forget it.

My parents are divorced, father pays alimony for me. Two years á ago my sister who lives with father, suddenly asked mother for á money. As she considered the amount of money my mother offered á her too small, she brought an action against mother. I was á terribly angry with my sister.

I arranged with a friend to go skating the next day. He asked me á to wake him up by telephone at twelve o'clock because we had come á home late in the morning. Next day I called him - he was not at á home. As something like that had happened to me several times á before, I came to the conclusion that one cannot rely on anybody á and I felt very sad.
Whenever I see a spider or a snake I feel disgusted.

When I had slept with a boy for the first time I felt ashamed for á three reasons. First, because I was only 13 years old, second, á because I did not really like him, third, because he had caught á me napping.

I had been together with my boy-friend for two and a half years, á when he got to know another girl and not even tried to conceal á that from me. I drew my conclusions and left him - I also felt a á bit guilty for what had happened.
My boy-friend told me that he would take me to the training of á the life-saving dogs.
I was in a dark cellar and saw a glowing red point. I thought á that it was a person with a cigarette - but it was only the red á switch.
A man treated his dog very badly - he insulted and beated him á until the dog kept lying on the floor with his tail drawn in.
A horse which I had liked very much was taken away.
On TV I saw a report about church in Amerika. A priest was shown á who was performing miracles in front of the camera - I felt á disgusted.
When I was a child, my uncle came to see us. I spit at him and á ran out - I do not know the reason for that. My father came after á me and insisted on my apologizing.
I quarreled with my boy-friend. He said it was unfair that I á always started crying so that he had to give in.

To be able to prepare myself better for an important examination, á I did not spend the nitht with my girl-friend but in the á students' hostel. I had not done that for months. The day when I á had the examn, somebody knocked at my door at seven o'clock in á the morning. My girl-friend who likes sleeping late, had come to á be able to be with me.

I studied medicine for several semesters and at that time I á developed a great fear of examinations. I was most afraid of my á examination of anatomy. While other students were examined, I was á dissecting. I was able to hear everything and was waiting with á fear until it was my turn.

When I come home in the evening, the first thing I do is to sit á down and smoke a cigarette. One day I found the flat in a totally á desolate state. My girl-friend had wanted to tidy up but had not á finished.

My son's mother told me that she wanted to move to Vienna and á take the child with her. This means a rather long distance for á me. My whole family was sad and dumbfounded so that my own á feelings were intensified.
When a very near person got into an awkward situation but showed á only helplessness and indecision.
I spent an evening with my girl-friend. When we wanted to go to á bed I was totally drunk. Next morning I felt rather ashamed.
I threw away an object, which belonged to a friend, because I did á not know what to do with it. My friend was very sad about that á and I felt guilty.
After a long time I saw my boy-friend again.
My first public appearance in front of a rathe big audience.
I was angry about how the government acted concerning Hainburg, á especially when I saw a discussion about it on TV.
Death of my father; he died of laryngeal cancer.
When I got indecent offers.
When I bought new skis; I was ashamed to tell the assistant that á I am not good at skiing and therefor bought racing skis.
My schoolmates were teasing a pupil who was not able to defend á himself very well; I should have taken his part.
I thought that I had failed an examination, but when I was á informed about the mark, I saw that I had passed it.
Before an examination: I had the fealing that I had not learned á enough.
Once when I was playing table tennis I was already sure that I á would win , but at last I lost the game.
My grandfather's funeral.
In cinema I saw a film which showed how a person was torn out his á guts when he was still alive.
I was sitting in a restaurant with friends. They asked me á something which they thought I should know. Actually I know it, á but at that time I was not able to remember it.
I had an appointment with a friend. I promised him to meet with á him, but at last I did not without having informed him.
When I had a psychical crisis, I met a girl, who told me that she á had had almost the same problems and how she had finally overcome á them.

I had climbed on a cherry tree alone and there was a thick á caterpillar beside my fingers. I feel disgusted by caterpillars á and snakes. I was terribly afraid of the caterpillar crawling on á my fingers. Out of the fear I was almost unable to climb down.
A friend of mine told other people that I was a slattern (because á of an occurence that had happened some time ago). When I heard á about that I was very angry.

My grandfather was seriously ill, he had only a few days left to á live. I had always loved him, but never told him. When I saw him á for the last time, I had the feeling that I had omitted so many á things I could not do again. - There was a fly sitting on his á forehead and he was too weak to drive it away. I was very sad á when I saw that.

Normally my father never tells vulgar jokes, we do not speak á about sexual things, too. But once he told such a vulgar joke, á that I was really disgusted. He did not tell me, but some of his á friends, but I was present.

When I was 6 or 7 years old, I pulled down the trousers of a á friend because I wanted to know what she looked like. My mother á watched that and (as a punishment) sent me into the house. We á never spoke about that; I think it was as embarassing for her as á it was for me.

When I told my boy-friend, who loved me very much, that I wanted á to put an end to our relationship. a long time before I told him á that and also a long time after that I felt guilty, because I had á hurt him so much.
Unexpectedly I met some persons who I like very much. á Spontaneously they invited me and integrated me within their á group, although it was late in the evening.

After a footballmatch I went home by car, a friend drove. I did á not realize that he was drunk until we were in the car. He was á madly racing. Several times we were in dangerous situations and I á told him to be cautious, but he did not care.

A friend of mine uses butter instead of oil when he is cooking. I á am always angry about that, because it is an unnecessary luxury. á Recently we both were cooking and he wanted to use butter again. á When I had already put the oil into the pan, he poured it out á again and put the butter into the pan.
After some friends had come to see me. They had stayed for á several days and we had got on very well. When they had left, I á had a feeling of emptyness.

I had a quarrel with a friend who lived with me in the same flat. á He moved out. Before he went he invited me and some friends for a á drink. At last he was totally drunk and smelled disgusting. á Besides, he told lies about us and behaved as if he was to be á pitied.

I went to see a friend. There were other people, too, and á everybody brought some present. I was the onlyone who brought á nothing. My friend was very hospitable and did not show anything á - although I knew how he felt.

With a group of handicapped people we went to a party. When we á wanted to leave we were not able to find one of these people. I á had told his mother that we would leave at 4.30 p.m., actually it á was planned for 3.30 p.m. Therefore there was a delay.
I had a quarrel with my fiancT. When he admitted his fault, á everything was allright. It was then for the first time that he á surprised me with coffee and cake and a bunch of flowers.
After my boy-friend had beaten me for the first time, I always á trembled when somebody knocked on my door or when I heard steps á coming nearer.
I had not eaten anything for 2 days to be able to pay the fine á for my fiancT. But he stayed in another town and spent one á thousand shillings in the restaurant during the same time.
I had to give up my love, because it did not work out well.
I was insulted without a reason by a drunk man.
My boyfriend had drunk too much and beaten me. When I had to show á the letter the door, which was almost crashed, I felt ashamed.
I spied on my fiancT and was terribly jealous. Later I saw that á there was no reason for that.
My sister had a daughter. I saw the baby for the first time á through a pane of glass and she looked at me.

My mother, my sister and I were sitting in the sitting room and á watching a film on TV. My father came home drunk and told us to á turn off. When we did not do that he switched off the fuse and á started shouting. We were sitting in the dark and I was afraid á that he would do us a harm.

I bought an aquarium which made me much pleasure. I was watching á the fish when my father came in and asked me how much I had payed á for it. He said he would not pay for the current that it would á require.

When I was 9 years old, I got a cat, but after 3 days he died. I á was very sad, because I had nursed him and taken him to the á veterinary's - but in vain. Although I had had him only for a á short time I had liked him very much.
When my grandmother was about 80 years old, she lived with us for á several years. I saw her illness. I did not even want to breath á the air that smelled of her presence.

I am left-handed. When I attended the first form, we learned to á write with pens. I smeared everything I had written. All my á friends had written well and wanted to know why the teacher was á looking at my note-book. I was ashamed.

When I was 4, we spent our holidays at the seaside. My sister and á her friend wanted to go to a bay on an undangerous way. I wanted á to arrive before them and went on a shorter, but more dangerous á way. When I arrived, I found nobody there. I waited for a long á time, but nobody came. On my way back I met my mother who had á been searching for me desperatly. She did not scold me, but I saw á how much she had worried (herself).
A friend breaking up with her boyfriend.
Accidentally seeing a friend in a compromising situation with a á stranger.
Parents finding out I smoked.
Not thanking relatives for a favor done.
Emotional reassurances by spouse.
Movement in bush late at night while camping.
Heated discussion with spouse concerning new house.
Loss of close relative.
The price I was charged for work on my car.
Caused fault in V.C.R. by not following instructions carefully.
Losing my temper with my spouse.
A night spent with a group of friends.
A car came very close to hitting me whilst I was crossing the á street.
A friend whom I had gone out of my way to do something for did á not bother to acknowledge my efforts, and treated me badly á thereafter.
A girlfriend ended our relationship in an abrupt and unexpected á manner.
A friend once reacted childishly (he is 23 yearrs old) to my not á responding in his favour to a request, that is: he asked me for á some money I refused, and his reaction was quite childish.
On one occasion whilst engaging in horseplay with my girlfriend, á I caused her to be physically harmed.
I borrowed money from a friend and did not pay back the debt when á I said I would.
Getting a phone call from a very old friend.
Before giving a seminar to a rather large audience.
Being stopped by the police for a traffic offence which I don't á think I committed.
Death of a parent.
At a social event when none of the guests would help to serve á food or clear tables. It was all beneath them.
The mother of a small child found me shaking the child in á exasperation, because I couldn't get it to sleep.
The more than satisfactory result of a recently-completed á university subject was communicated to me by phone.

I was a passenger in a jumbo-jet which was accelerating down the á runway and almost at the point of take-off, when the pilot á suddenly braked and put the engines into reverse thrust, in an á obviously urgent attempt to stop the aircraft. The hostesses show á signs of concern and my first thought was that something was on á the runway in our path and that we were in danger of hitting it.

A person walking his dog allowed it to defecate on the footpath á outside my house. Although it had happened before, this was the á first time I had witnessed it. All the skills I had learnt from á PY 263 were thrown out the window when his indifference to my á protestation was obvious to me.

While walking through an old mining area, I unwittingly disturbed á a wallaby which, in its resultant flight, accidentally fell down á a deep mine shaft. On investigation it seemed uninjured, but it á was impossible for the wallaby to get out, and also for me to get á it out of the shaft. To prevent its suffering a slow death, I á shot it.

A colleague and I were sitting on a bench next to an old man in a á shopping centre. the old man coughed and spluttered somewhat, á then with his fingers removed the resultant phlegm and mucous á from his mouth, and transferred it onto the armrest of the á bench.
I had promised to contact a friend about a particular matter by a á certain date, then thought no more about it until the friend á reminded me after the date had passed.

A neighbour complained about smoke from my backyard incinerator á entering his house after a change of wind direction. I lit the á fire after originally checking that the wind would not blow the á smoke in that direction.
On my birthday, when a very close friend sent me a huge bouquet á of flowers.

When I heard that there had been some women raped at uni, just á near where I usually park my car and walk by myself at night. á Although I wasn't in danger it unnerved me for days and I was á fearful whenever walking through the area.
When the person I am going out with let me down in a situation á that I was depending on them, and didn't show respect or care.
When I found out that a person I went to school with had died in á a car accident.
When I heard about the way a parent of a friend had mistreated á him, and caused a great instability.
When I realised that I had become too emotionally involved with á the person I'm going out with, and when I began to like someone á else and questioned whether I really care about person I'm with.
When I came very late one night (or morning !) and my parents á were waiting, not so much angrgy as disappointed.
One of my friends and I had breakfast in a restaurant. It was á spontaneous and lots of fun.
I was walking home late at night from lectures and someone á deliberately started following me. It was dark and I was scared.
At one of my close friends saying she didn't like the way I am á nice to people I don't know, or who have been nasty to me.
Leaving Melbourne to move interstate - leaving relatives and á friends behind.
Disgust at a girl I know for continually feeling sorry for herself á and never acting positively to do something about her problems.
I am ashamed of the horrible way I used to treat my little á sister.
Often I forget to give my immediate family birthday presents.
I noticed that Meryl Streep and I had similar cheekbones and jaw á structure.
I do not recall being scared in the near past.
As for disgust.
Girl I was fond of did not initiate conversation as I expected in á tutorial.
I realised that someone was insidiously attempting to shit me off á I was disgusted with him for doing so, because I afforded him á with no excuse to do so.
I do not seem to feel emotion such as shame, guilt or fear - far á out !
I cannot recall feeling guilty in the near past. REMARK - SUBJECT MAY NOT HAVE TAKEN THE EXERCISE VERY SERIOUSLY.
When my mother was angry with me over my friends and boyfriend.
Anger towards my lover for being late.
The death of my twin sister - suicide.
Disgust with myself for consistently making foolish errors in á communicating with others (asking for 1/2 Kg of nuts when I only á wanted 50 g).
I had been rude to my mother at a time when she needed á comforting, not anger (death of my sister).
Guilt - because I had not written to my sister for months before á she died.

My current lover and I had been very busy with work and study and á had not had time alone together for almost a month until one á afternoon recently when we made love for hours and then showered á and ate together.
A workmate and I had been antagonistic with each other for some á weeks - he had reacted violently to my criticisms of his work á standards.
Blank.
After going through a glass door, I sustained a number of serious á cuts which were gaping open.
The mother of a person with whom we had been sharing a housing á accused me of trying to rip her off over payment of bills in the á house.
A girl with whom I was staying having sex with a person for about á 3 nights running, and then with his brother the following night, á and back again.
During an argument an acquaintance accused me of having insulted á her parents by having had sex in their house which they á overheard.
A girl whom I hadn't seen for a period of time told me that she á had been pregnant and had an abortion - I was the father.
When my boyfriend last told me he loved me after I gave him an á impulsive kiss.
When my boyfriend was leaving to go home one night, I had a very á deep sense of uneasiness and an unwarranted fear that I wouldn't á see him again.

Anger with boyfriend's best friend for alienating me and blaming á me for personality changes in my boyfriend and changes in my á boyfriend's attitude to him and his obvious egoistical attitude á himself in doing so. I also lost one of my best friends - his á girlfriend.
Death of paternal grandmother to whom I was very close - died of á cancer.
Disgust with oneself after being intoxicated enough to go to bed á with a stranger.

I feel shame every time I think of very dear friends of mine á abroad who were family to me for a year, and now 2 years later, I á have attempted, but have not actually gone through with á corresponding with them, to express my feelings and gratitude.

After being told that an ex-boyfriend had been hurt by my wearing á something he had given me when I was with another guy. I was á unaware of my actions really, as I had not considered the fact á that he had given it to me, and might see me. I still respected á his opinions of me.
When I thought that my high school love and I had a mutual á emotion.

I was on my surf ski. Rather large waves to strong current á separated me from my ski and we both began to drift slowly á (actually rather quickly) away to sea. The direction I was á drifting in was taking me straight over a reef on which rather á large sharks were constantly being caught. (I was alone with no á one to help me).

I was enjoying the company of bird life while I was eating lunch á in a park when a group of people began throwing sticks at some of á the birds - for no reason other than the satisfaction of seeing á them being scared away.

When I left my sister's house after staying there for a few days. á She has two little boys, and they are very warm people (the á family). At the time, I was in need of this sort of contact, and á I grew very fond of children (no, I'm not a paedophiliac).
When my father revealed inconsistent morals.
When I woke up after a night of drinking I couldn't remember and á discovered several untoward things had occurred.

Leaving home when my mother thought I had no reason to go and á felt that I was rejecting her. She is a constantly depressed á person (a bit of a worry-wort) and I felt guilty about having á given her this additonal problem.
I'd just got the top mark in an exam.

My brother and I were driving to Brisbane when he drove back onto á the road, perhaps cutting off another car but not noticeable - á this driver did his best to drive us off the road for about 1/2 á an hour.

I was at the corner shop, which I patronise regularly I had only á a $ 50 note and I purchased about $ 3 worth of goods that I á really needed - the keeper made sarcastic remarks to others about á people using him to cash notes.
My mother died of cancer after a 4 year illness - I think the á most pregnant moment of sadness was the next morning, just as the á sun rose.
A lecturer in great detail spoke about his sexual experiences.
I was walking outside the union refec after rain when I tripped á and fell.
I stole 5c from my mother's purse for a choo-choo bar - I was 6.
On a sailing boat at night, under a full moon, listening to Pink á Floyd, drinking good wine, with good company, the boat being á steered by autopilot, and a full eclipse of the moon.
Fear of sexual overtures from a close relative in the family.
When my rights to use a shared house had been usurped by á co-owners out of pure selfishness.
At rejection / being ignored by a loved person held in great á esteem.
Following heavy stirring / ridiculing a close friend who was á very vulnerable to such attack - inspiring fierce, defensive á counter-attack.
Guilt at having pressed another person to expose/explore his á personal weaknesses/faults, to the extent that the other person á was made to feel terrible/defensive.
Family member survived an operation.
I was walking to my car at night and thought that I was being á followed.
I walked in on a teenage patient of mine (I work in a hospital) á as he was going through my office drawers and he had removed á money from my purse.
Death of grandmother.
When I became aware that an acquaintance had stolen from friends.
Caught cheating on a diet.
I had shown anger toward my dog and he was killed later that day.
A close married friend has just had his first child.
Stranded in the north of Fraser Island with a submerged 4 WD hire á vehicle.
Not being alowed on a school camp with the class I'd been in for á 11 years (I had stayed down due to illness)
At the funeral of a friend about 20 years old, who was killed in á a hit-and-run motorcycle accident.
A female friend was violently ill on the return journey from a á wedding reception we attended. Getting her out of the car when á home took quite a while.
Cheating in a minor geography exam at school.
I wasn't able to see my girlfriend on her birthday and because I á was late arriving home from uni, I didn't phone her as arranged á at a certain time (she rang in the meantime).
Having received an offer to do post-graduate work.
Taking a trip to crocokile country I fell out of the boat and was á motivated by fear of being eaten to perform great swimming feats.
Last night - finding that someone in the house had eaten an á entire packet of almonds I had bought for a family treat.
The loss of my father as he died of a massive and sudden heart á attack.
When after a party celebrating a friend's 21st birthday - upon á leaving I found 10 people outside throwing up and further 4 á unconscious.
Having had a very heated argument with my sister - I began á hitting her about the head with a newspaper I was holding.
A situation where I stole a friends wife's wallet.
Winning a tight tennis match. One set to play, and the team was á behind by 3 games. We won the last set 6-2 and won the match by a á game.
When at school, I threw a duster at another child and hit him in á the head. The blow caused a flesh wound and I was afraid of what á would happen to me when the teacher found out the circumstances.
Finding that a subordinate at work was still not willing to á cooperate after discussions to try and resolve an attitude á problem.
Death of the family dog.
We had friends to dinner and one of them threw a beer bottle in á the air, and it bounced on an expensive table and damaged the á table .The person did not apologise.
After making a joke about a friend's marriage that was too á personal.
Carried out a vandalistic act on some windows at an old army á location.
As a child (i.e. 5-7) hiking in reasonably rugged bush and á becoming lost for a duration of 5-7 hours.
Following an argument with my brother, he broke my golf clubs.
Leaving the house myself and a female friend had shared for 6-8 á months because of the friendship which developed and our approach á to each other in occasional instances of several personal crises.
Discovering a good friend had lied to me, resulting in a á detrimental relationship with another person.
No specific instances - perhaps having lied as a child resulting á in someone else being blamed for the event.
Leaving University in 1982 following exclusion and lying to á parents/friends about reasons for leaving, i.e. lying about the á fact of having been excluded.
Going to a friend's wedding and seeing many of my old friends á whom I had known before I moved to a new district five years á previously.

Car accident. Travelling as a passenger along narrow bitumen road á at night - trying to overtake semi-trailer. The truck pulled over á onto our side and we hit the wet dirt, swerved back into the á truck, back onto the verge, over a guide post and into a ditch.
At school when I had a shouting argument with a friend over my á ability to carry out a particular duty in the correct way without á harming her.
Looking up end-of-semester results, and finding I'd failed three á out of seven (subjects).
When I found out some family friends were embezzelling the á company they worked for - using company petrol and food supplies á and claiming furniture and crockery.
When my best friend foud out I'd been lying about something I'd á been doing behind her back.
After having told an authority figure a very large lie I was told á she believed me, because she believed I had never lied to her.
After being away on a holiday for 2 months, a friend, who lived á interstate, had remembered when I'd get back and phoned to á welcome me home on the night of my arrival.
