To have a friend who I didn't see for months, and under the á circumstances that I met him made me feel happy, and perhaps á because it has been one of the good things that I learned with á this friend.
It was when a friend took me to a place and gave me as a gift my á astrologycal map with the explanations of a psychologist.
When I was dreaming that I was being chased, in the upmost of á horror the door of the closed felt down synchronicaly with the á dream scare.
When my mother slapped me in the face, I felt anger at that á moment.
When I deeply felt that I could lose the person I love best á because of my foolishness.
I felt disgust toward meat when I felt sick with the steak after á a week only on meat.
When I had to act alone a character for a public (40 people).
When I stared to much at a pastry that a woman was eating and at á the same instant the pastry felt on the floor.
In a day when at work, in school, and relationships came out as I á wanted, and I was recognized in my work.
When I woke up in the middle of the night because of a dream, it á wasn't a nightmare, it was an uninteligible dream in wich I woke á because of a certain end.
When I was robbed in a bus.
When I try to get closer at a person and she misinterpreted me.
When I felt the smell of industries that pollute.
When somebody I knew greeted me and started to talk with me and I á didn't know, I couldn't remember who he was.
When I unjustly accused a person of my family of something she á didn't really do.

I was travelling in the South of Brasil, near the end of the á year. I was well settled with 3 friends. At the evening of 31 M., á somebody, also with us, took from his purse pints of all colours, á and the 4 of us, and other friends, that were at the same beach, á painted each other and we went to the beach with champagne.

I was walking from my friend's house, a few blocks from my house, when a á car began to follow me. He waited I passed by it rotateed a little and á stopped on my way. I changed completely my way and the car went á on following me until I turned at a corner and running I hid in a á garden of a house, waiting for the car to pass by. I went back home á terribly afraid.

One day I lent my tennis I just had washed to my sister because á she asked it. I asked her not to soil it as I had just washed it. á Next day I looked at the tennis, and it was dirty with wax. She á could not have soiled it. It was lack of consideration. I felt á very angry.
The second time I went to the entrance exam to V.S.P. and á didn't get approved.

I was travelling, we were 15 person, one of them I met at the á travel and didn't like her. One night I was asleep while she and á her friends were talking too loud in the kitchen. I got up to ask for á silence and since that day I felt constant disgust for her.
The day my boyfriend saw and touched my breasts when I was á without my shirt, only with my pants.

One day my boyfriend put my hand on his penis and I felt well, á but after I felt a guilty conscience because I hadn't thought á about the consequences that this could have brought if I had gone á farther.
When people remember us and shows interest about what we do.
When I had to talk with an important person about a job.
When my brother went out with my new shirt that I adored, and á returned it dirty with grease.
I felt sadness when I notice that I'm not important for a á determinate person. We do many things for a friend, and we see á soon after, that he doesn't do anything for us, nor thinks of us.
When I needed another job and tought that a good and known person á (my employer) could help me. He simply said that he couldn't help á me.
When I arrived late at the job and met the most troublesome boss.
One of my pupils escaped from school to the street.

I received a phone call from a high school friend whose younger á sister studied with me at the University and gave me a lift every á moning. She was going to get married to a guy whom I knew too and á who had died when he fell from a building, I was afraid to lose á somebody since I had already lost a brother in an accident.
My grandmother is a highly authoritative person, who lives alone, á is independent, but doesn't know to live without commanding the á others. I hate this!

I am always sad when my boyfriend goes away. He lives and studies á in an other city. We have gone steady for 2 and 1/2 years and á everything is going very well, but sometime this situation makes á me feel bad and very lonely.
I felt disgust when I kissed a guy that I know. I was on the outs á with my boyfriend and this person appeared but he has nothing to á do with me.
I felt ashamed of my body in spite of knowing that it is more or á less beautiful and also knowing that my boyfriend considers me á beautiful, but this was only in the beginning.
I always feel guilty when I see my mother sad or fed up with á life. I really dont know the reason.
When I bought my car.
I was alone at home, a man forced the front door which was á locked, forced and tried to open a window.
When I had a serious argument with a dear person.
When I met my boyfriend with another girl.
When I was still a child I was told off in face of other persons á for having touched an object that didn't belong to me.
When I fought with my sister and said that she had provoked this. á She was very seriously scolded.
The birth of my daughter.
I should have given a test lesson to get a job. I had no courage. á I didn't make the test.
Discussion with my mother about the way to educate my children. I á felt anger against my mother.
When my grandmother died.
I was returning from the Universtity at night when I was accosted á by a boy who molested me, passing his hands on my body.
When a friend of mine visited me and my house was in a mess.

My daughter was a baby and was crying to be taken on my lap. I á felt very nervous and moved her away and went out. As soon as the á feeling of nervousness passed I was taken by an enormous feeling á of guilt, for having rejected my daughter.
I was in the dark room, it's insecure and has holes covered with á wooden sheets in the roof the establishment had already been á assaulted and could be assaulted again.

And she said absurd things, false things that filled my ears and á inflated my head which seemed to be caught in a carcass where the á heart wanted to explode and where the arm wanted to knock down á the world.
One day I heard from a friend that the boy I loved had gone out á with her and not with me.
I saw a magazine with photographs of dead and maimed people whose á limbs were separated from their body like a head on one side and á the leg on the other.
In the classroom we discussed with the teacher. He told me things á that affected directly in a negative way my job and my behavior á in the classroom in front of the other pupils.

The greatest guilt I felt and I didn't know if it was really á justified is that when I was a child I had a brother very close á to me. He  became ill, and asked me to see  him in the hospital. á I didn't go, when his situation became worse in the U.I.T. (Unity á of intensive therapy) I went and he died.
One of the greatest joiy was when I succeded in acquiring a á motorcycle through my own efforts.

I'm afraid of driving on the special seat of a mororcycle, mainly á with certain colleagues who by exces of self-confidence drive á beyond limits or measure in the traffic and the main victim is á always the person who sits behind the driver.
I felt much anger when my fahter interferred in my relations with á another person whom I liked very much, ending something that I á adored.
One of the greatest sadness was when my grandfather died, because á I loved him very much.
My main disgust is against codfish because I detest even the á smell of it.
Sincerely I'm a very timid guy and so even in very simple á situations sometimes I am ashamed.
The only guilt I considered reasonable was my reproval at the end á of the semester at the University.
When I got a stereo walkman from my father when he had finacial á difficulties. I thought that although he promised to give me that á present, he was not obliged to do so.
That someone would discover whom I really love.
When a colleague was rude with me because she didn't understand á the subject about which I was discussing.
For not having succeded in getting the job as a translator that I á wanted.
When I saw a man who hadn't the lower .... in a car á exhibition. He was passing a handkerchief from inside to outside á of his mouth.
When I went out with a friend of mine to meet her ex-boyfriend á who didn't know that she was engaged to be married.
When I passed the whole weekend with my boyfriend, coming back á home on Sunday afternoon he met my parents for the first time.
When there was a fight at home and my father threatened to throw á a chair on my brother.
I felt anger against a person who told bad things about me in my á absence.

After a disagreement between my parents, when I was alone with my á father and my sister, the aggression continued, when my father á tried to put me and my sister against my mother revealing facts á that had happened in the past like a talk between my father and á his mother in law where she told him that my mother was not quite á save.
When in my childhood we were forced to take cod-liver oil.
I feel ashamed when I am praised.
When I provoked a fight with my mother, hurting her feelings very á much.
I was in the living room at home with an ex-boyfriend, it was á nearly a year that we had separated, during the talk he began to á remember our courting and gave me a long kiss.

I was with a friend in a stationed car when, suddenly a man á appeared on my side and an other with a gun on his side the á hold-up lasted a few minutes but it was terrible. I had never á seen a gun so close.
I was on a farm with a few friends and during the talk I á discovered that a friend of mine, was being betrayed by her á boyfriend and a 3rd friend of ours.
I was watching television. It was about midnight when a very dear á friend called saying that his father had died in an accident.
I was working in a classmate's house with a group. A girl began á to graze her foot against mine under the table.
This feeling comes frequently when I go out at night and tell my á mother that I shall come back early. But then I get home a 5 or 6 a.m.
Always when I meet the person I love.
When I and the person mentioned above had a suspicion of á pregnancy.
When I left after the examination to enter the University, and á even though I had studied the whole year I made a bad exam.
When I thought for an instant that a very good relationship with á a person had finished.
When I heard the bad news about the death of a close person.
When I tried to hide a fact from a person for irrelevant reasons á and considered such an attitude childish.
It happens sometimes in connection with certain persons with whom á I have frequent relationships but nothing special.
When I entered in the University after a year of struggles.
Practicing wind-surf my body was caught under the sail. On trying á to get out my leg was caught in the lashing. I was afraid of á dying by asphixia.

In the University we were convoked to a stroll like a freshman I á was still innocent about the manipulation. On seeing the goal of á the exaltation to poor character people, I felt anger on feeling á myself mass of maneuver.
In a social situation I became interested in a woman. We talked, á we laughed, we enjoyed each other. She desappeared for a few á minutes, and a little after appeared with an other man.
I saw a man falling on the walkway. He seemed half dead, and was á immobile. I felt disgust for the people who passed by without á doing anything to help.
In the traffic I insulted a man who crossed my way. Afterwards I á paired with him, and felt shame because of mine lack of pacience á and ridiculous attitude.
A great friend of mine travelled with the intention to change his á life. He didn't succeed and returned depressed. I had not power á to support his frustration and his behavioral change.
A friend of mine travelled very far. I miss her but feel joy too á because fer life is taking the right direction as she wants. So I á feel joy for her mainly.
I feel sadness when I only imagine that I could lose a close á person. Some time ago I lost a man whom aI greatly respected.

A similar feeling I felt quite recently while travelling in a á taxi. The driver treated me roughly and dishonestly - he chose á the longest route, he overdrawed almost one lev more and he tried á to be intimate with me.
Some days ago I fell down at a public place, I came into notice á but thank God I was not mocked at. Though it hurt badly, at the á first moment I felt shame, not ache.
I felt guilty because of the pain I caused to a very close á friend. But over the feeling of guilt, my conviction of being á right dominated.
When my nephew was born. The birth was hard, it was a big baby.
Late one night I was pursued by gipsies who had no good á intentions.
My brother accused me undeservedly before my parents. I was not á guilty. He was misled by his wife.
When I left my boyfriend. I found another girl at his home but he á did nothing to relieve the situation.
I found a big black beetle in my coffee cup. It was alive big and á it was moving its limbs.
When I had to prepare and read a paper to my fellow students but á I didn't cope with the task.
I had thrown with the ashtray a still lighted cigarette in the á plastic wastepaper basket. It had burnt out and my landlords made á me a row that I might had set their flat on fire.
Some time ago I was present at the wedding party of two close á friends of mine.
I was crossing the street together with some colleagues of mine á when I suddenly found myself almost under the wheels of a truck.
Someone stole my ski at Vitosha and of course I was the one to be á blamed. I left them without supervision.
I got separated form my closest friend. He went to work abroad.
A drunk man had fallen in the street and he was shouting obscene á words.
I had borrowed some money and I exceeded the time-limit.
I couldn't fulfill a promise.
An encounter with a man whom I love, after a very long á separation.
I woke up in the middle of the night of a nightmare, I was alone, á it was very quiet and very dark.
A shop-assistant behaved rather roughly with me though she hadn't á the slightest grounds for it.
I saw a friend of mine who had suffered a very heavy contusion á after an accident.
I caught a glimpse of a black-beetle.
I was made a very sharp remark at a rehearsal.

I couldn't fulfill a request of a girlfriend of mine, though I á categorically promised her and I believed there wouldn't be any á hindrance. It was partly for objective reasons but also because á I couldn't organize myself.
At a success of mine, at a real achievement.

I was looking after a dying patient at work one night, a young á woman, my colleague was talking to her relatives and .... to á offer them any support emotionally, physically and then sent them á down to the coffee shop to have a dinner rather than offering the á facilities available for their use cause it involved her having á to do some work. Seeing them again I felt disgusted at her á attitude.
I put on a lot of weight in a few months and every time I met á someone I knew would avoid them, usually by hiding because my á self image was low and I was ashamed of what I had done to á myself.
For the first time in my life telling someone I loved them.
When I was ringing up a guy who was my teen idol, and was in á Auckland. I was really scared, I didn't know what to say or do.
When my mother decided to clean out my room and throw out what á she thought was junk, without my knowing about it, so I returned á home to find half my stuff gone.
When I couldn't find my dog which was missing.
I was disgusted with a friend's behaviour when she got absolutely á drunk so that she vomitted all over my house.

I was taking place in an anti nuclear protest and was shouting á protest loudly to some American sailors of the U.S. Texas á submarine. A guy came up to me and said that's your brother á screaming at, I felt shame and I realized screaming at another á person isn't good protesting. Now I'm a silent protester.
I felt guilty after getting really angry with a friend and having á an argument. I was being stubborn and proud, and selfish, because á my friend let me down, through no fault of her own.

When I met my boyfriend and we discovered that we shared the same á ideals and goals in life, and that we could share all our á feelings and thoughts and felt that the world's not so bad when á you have someone really close to share your life with.
I had called a boy who had dated me, and told him that I was ill, á while, actually, I didn't want to go out with him, later on, he asked á me if I was feeling better, then I felt ashamed.
When I hurt my parents in one way or another.
When I passed the driving test after three failures.
When I nearly caused a traffic accident with my car.
When playing a football match, there was one player who made mean á tackels, kicked at everything and did things having nothing to do á with football.
A close friend decided to stop with his study and to go back á home.

We had a birthday party with 5 friends. One of us frequently used á hard drugs. On the party I discovered that the other 3 friends á also used them. While we agreed we would help the big user to á stop using it.
During a family reunion, they started talking about me wearing an á ear-ring.
It was my mother's birthday. My father and I used to buy a á present together. However, now I had bought something together á with my girlfriend and I forgot to ask my father.
For instance when a girl is interested in me and likes me.
Walking at friday night through Nijmegen, going to a pub or a á disco.
I felt dusgust with a self-iterested person who ruined the life á of another by means of utterly unfair methods.
I didn't do an important job and it had an adverse effect on á other people.
I stroke a person undeservedly.
I sensed this feeling when I passed successfully the second tour á of a competition.
I felt fear when my mother was heavily ill.

I felt anger against a colleague of mine during a rehearsal in á acting. He hadn't learnt the text of an opera act in the course of á several months and thus making difficulties for the rest of my á colleagues.
I felt sadness when I had to get separated from the woman I loved á who had to leave for her motherland.
I feel shame mixed with anger with the behavior of some á incultivated people because my fiancT is a foreigner.
I felt guilt because on account of my ambitions I nearly turned á my sister out of my parents home.
That was what I felt when I was finally accepted in the Bulgarian á Conservatorie after I had applied a couple of years.

I experienced this feeling when the doctors found a nodule in one á of my mother's breasts. It turned out to be an occlusion á resulting from continious sucking but for a few days I was not in my á reason.

I had an accident with a trafic police car that was packed at a á curve without any visibility and against all traffic regulations á in a strong snowstorm. As a result I still cannot repair my car á because of the missing spare parts.

A sudden doubt made me run for a long time in a rainy autumn á night. When I reached the intended place I saw my beloved in á another man's arms. A sudden blow, grief, I cannot qualify it, it á is painful for me to remember about it.
I felt disgust with a man I had trusted and respected, to whose á problems I had always shown deep understanding.
I was given the task to learn a page of music text for a small á part. But I had forgotten all about it and I felt quite awkward á when I had to show what I had prepared.
Some time ago I slapped my son without trying to understand who á the real culprit of a damage was. After that I felt guilty and á bad but it was too late.
My boyfriend made me a proposal.
I was to be given an audition to get a role. I had a competitress á and I wasn't well prepared because I was ill.

A whole crowd of us went to a folklore festival. The instructor á of the cast where my boyfriend played was traveling with us. We á decided to catch the train that leaved early in the morning á because we had business on the following day. The instructor á tried to get the upper hand and made us catch the train in spite á of everything, all the time he made me angry.
When I quarrelled with my boyfriend.

I am disgusted with the fact that bad singers play at the opera á (and not only there) only because they are protegTs or lovers of á an important felow while at the same time some young and able á singers work in a quite different field of life.
I feel shy to show all my worth when I work for the first time á with a conductor or a producer unfamiliar to me.
I offended my mother.
When I heard what mark I had got at the entrance examination and á I realized my admittance to the University was almost certain.
Once I was alone at home. I suddenly felt unwell and there was no á one to help me and call First Aid.
When I was admitted to a Language school. On the day when I was á informed by a message and my parents congratulated me.
When diving deep into the sea to reach the floor I felt á breathless. I was cautious but I doubted I should be able to come á to the surface and inhale.
When my friend (girl) promised to help me go to the hospital and be á examined by good experts and she deceived me.
When I had stayed abroad for a long time and I had remembered á about my friends and relatives. I felt sad and I wanted to see á them as soon as possible.
I felt it when I saw our headmaster blushed ingratiating himself á with high ranking officials.
When I shouted and quarrelled and for no reason I had been rude to my á mother and when my behaviour had been influenced by other outward á factors.
When you are satisfied with something, when you achieve something á you have striven to.
One fears many things, for example one fears going to the á dentist. but as far as I am concerned this feeling is connected á with the examination session.
When you are unjustly assessed at something you are sure to have á been right.
For the loss of a close friend or relative, but you feel grief á when you are away from home, too.
They wanted something to happen but I didn't.
I couldn't be with a girl on whom I was very keen.
I and my friends got acquainted with a guy from Sofia who turned á out to be gay, but we found that out only after 2 or 3 days.
My first girlfriend. I had the feeling that she was going out á with me only because of my defect.
Years ago I ran away from home which disappointed my parents.
Having passed an exam.
Having a car accident.
I shared a secret with a friend and it later turned out that he á had revealed it to another person with whom I didn't get along very well.
The loss of a very good friend.
Negative statement concerning me of a friend before strangers.
Adultery with the girlfriend of a friend of mine, of which he á learned.
Adultery with a friend's girlfriend.
I'm glad when I have good relations with my colleagues and most á of all when we are at a party.
I experienced it once when we were on a drive. Our car passed by á the one comming from the opposite direction at an incredibly á small distance.
I get angry with people who attain certain status without á deserving it, only with the support, authority and influence of á other people.
I feel sad when I see things done against men and nothing could á stop it - at least I think so.
I have experienced disgust with some people - usually double á dealers.
I am ashamed when I am not prepared in a subject and I have to á answer in the presence of the patients.
I feel guilty when I should have done something at any rate but I á haven't done it.
I experienced it when I was accepted at the Medical Higher á Institute.
I felt it when I sat for my exam in anatomy.
I experience that feeling when I am unsulted without deserving á it or when someone deceives me.
When my grandfather died.
I feel disgusted with toadies, hypocrites, chameleons.
When I do something unworthy.
When I offended my parents without wanting it.
After each successfully passed exam I am happy.
A friend of mine gave birth to a child. Very dangerous delivery. á I was afraid for her and for the baby.
I stayed for several weeks with a friend of mine before she moved á to live with her husband. One evening he came drunk and made an á awful scene, which I still remember.

In the past I experienced this feeling almost all the time - á wherever I went, in different sutuations. I was small and I had á to be taken to kindergarten, but me the fool didn't dare to tell á exactly where, finally as a result I was late.

My roommate got married and invited me to share a flat with them. á But with a young couple there should not be a third person. I am á to blame for not following the advise of the others, but it is á not late still.

I experienced this feeling when I was accepted as a student. á Because everything turned out different from my expectations. á Although I passed the exam successfully I was accepted as a á student only when I didn't expect it at all, namely at the á beginning of September.

In the real sense of the word I experienced fear in my first á months in the army. During my first night of duty. The cause for á all this was a bear. I became panic sticken (may be for the first á time) and even forgot that I had a gun.

When I was a soldier I quarrelled with my commander and may be in á revenge for this he detailed me on duty two successive nights. á Naturally he checked me up on the second night and found me á asleep for which he sent me to the cells.
Sometimes I experience sadness for the Sports High School and for á my unrealized dreams in the sport. Anyway there I spent six years á of my life.

Sort of awkward. I'd introduced (a lover) but introduced as a á friend to some members of my family, and my niece Yavanna who's á six was home from school and at Mum's and Dad's and was really á silly and at first it was ok, but it went on and on - yukky pooh! á You eat your snot, etc. and I felt cross she wouldn't stop. But á she had an audience and was in one of those moods. Once I'd á accepted it was something everyone does at time I felt better - á it was partly having my friend there.

In my 20s - and was going out to dinner to celebrate a friend's á birthday. Her (older - in 30s) cousin, really wanted me to get á drunk cos I'd visited their (cousin & wife) place quite a bit, á but had always been very careful - brought up to believe in á moderation in drink (but not guilt repression etc). I mixed á drinking with smoking (which I rarely did) and got drunk and had á to leave the table to get sick in the loo, and later went home á and was sick again; have never felt so awful in my life. And I á didn't want to face or tell my other flatmates, or family.

I used to pinch change from my father's mantlepiece (never my á mother - she didn't get enough housekeeping) and then I'd feel á when we went to church as a family I'd felt awkward cos I felt á I'm expected to go to communion and I would but I was afraid and á guilty 'cos I committed a mortal sin.
Spontaneous picnic with sister and friend and children - great.
Can think of no time that I have felt fear.

Teenage neighbours smashed my letterbox for the fifth time in a á couple of months. It was a deliberate action of kids who had á stayed in my home, had meals there yet took a dislike to my á daughter.
Guy I cared for went back to Canada to live.
Bus driver driving roughly - old man fell off seat into aisle - á driver wouldn't stop - disgusted with her behaviour.
A boy I look after for the probation service deliberately á offended to provoke a reaction from the police.
A young visitor to the house stole money from an elderly á visitor's purse. It wasn't noticed for some hours.
I had to leave an important function early because of family á commitments. Someone else had to complete my job.
I was seriously injured in a road accident. The very first steps á I took with only one crutch to support me I felt so good. I enjoy á being alive.
I was attacked, standing in a doorway, by a pack of 5 dogs, á alsatians and farm dogs with my escape route blocked by a shut á fence.

In the house where I live there is a new flatmate. His friends á unfortunately are the dirt of society, intelligent, fashonable, á rich and bored. At a party recently they were doing things I á didn't like done in my house. I felt angry at them.
I was driving near my girlfriend's house and I decided to keep á going because it was late and I would be back in the next few á days anyway. The next day she was killed in a road accident.

My girlfriend came home after a business dinner at the most á expensive place in town drunk as a skunk. Whats more she drove á home and couldn't remember doing so. I was disgusted by her state á and her actions.

A good friend of mine told me in comfidence that once he had á tried to commit suicide. To meet him you wouldn't think so. I á told another friend of mine about this when she was feeling á depressed about her twin brother's suicide. I broke a bond of á confidentiality.
When I was young I stole something from a shop and got caught, á then I was taken to the police station and my parents had to come á and get me.
When I found out that a set task (i.e. 2 essays and a test), the á thought of which had oppressed me, were not on the date I had á thought.
When confronted and in my opinion hassled by the police.

Disgust - no. Maybe it is more precise to say revultion at a worm á or a snake. But I mean it in a social aspect when somebody had á behaved like a scoundrel to you, when by his actions he has made á you change your attitude towards him but I thing this feeling the á way I meant it, is not typical for the people interrelations.
When you betray the trust you have been given. This is connected á with copying at a class-work at school.
When I have forgotten to warn somebody for something, or when I á have forgotten to bring something I have been asked for.
When, for example, I was in my eleventh school year and I learned á I had been classed for the Bulgarian Language and Literature á National Olympiad.
When, for example, my grandfather fell seriously ill. It was á necessary for him to be operated and I felt great fear of losing á him because he is so dear to me.
When, for example, I was not approved to continue my studies at á the Moscow University, no matter that I had the highest marks and á in general the best records of all the candidates.
When, for example, I left for the first time my parents and I á went to live in Sofia.
When, for example, someone is calumnating.
When, for example, I fail in my undertakings.
For example, when I have promised something but I haven't á fulfilled it.
Some time ago a close relative of mine got off cheap with the á worst.
The last time I felt it was when I was coming home late at night.
I haven't often felt this feeling. Once someone stole my garment.
Recently I happened to remain alone for a long time.
I don't remember about a situation when I have experienced this á feeling. Maybe it was when I saw a drunkard in the street.
I lied to my best friend and I wouldn't reform what I had done.
It happens to me quite often. I can't describe a particular case.
Realizing one's desire, an experienced feeling of satisfaction á from the realization of one's desires and aims.
Fear of the loss of a close friend, of feeling the ground slipping á from under my feet.
Feeling unable to preserve one's ideas and ambitions as innocent á as they are when you are young.
Attitude to a related family.
Exaggerating certain circumstances, wrong attitude and evaluation á of these circumstances.
Low evaluation of other people's cares.
I won a sport contest.
If a close relative's life is in danger.
A close person lied to me.
Getting separated from my girlfriend.
Encouter with a prostitute.
A theft committed by me.
Lack of respect for my parents.
When my son was born.
Before an examination.
Unjust punishment of a friend of mine.
After the loss of a close relative.
When somebody behaves like a scoundrel. Recently a colleague of á mine used the name of another one for his own benefit.
I travelled on a bus and I forgot to punch the ticket. A ticket á collector came in and I had to pay the fine. I did it with a feeling á of shame.
I forgot to convey an important announcement.
Meeting a loved man.

I felt a physical fear, if I can call it this way, today, in the bus where á I was sitting on the first seat. While turning the driver didn't á see the tram which was making a dash towards us (coming from the á side I was), and whose driver intended to cross in yellow á light.
At an unjust, or to be more precise, at a bureaucratic treatment á of one's personality.
When one is alone and knows that all the others are celebrating.
At the sight of an insect, such as the black-beetle.
When not fulfilling any of my obligations to a person whom I á respect.
When something unpleasant happens to a friend or relative of á yours and you are at the bottom of it.

I sensed such a feeling when I understood I was admitted to the á University. I was at home, the atmosphere was still, though I á myself was full of suspense. I tried to do different things. When á the telephone rang and...! Yes, of course there were other á situations when I felt a similar feeling but I was unmindful of á them.
This feeling I sensed quite recently. It was arisen by the á terrific thought that I might lose the man I loved !

Anger I felt when my boyfriend told me he didn't mind breaking it á off with me, i.e. each of us to take his own road. Because until á that moment, he deliberately restricted our dates. The motives á were brought to my knowledge later.

Sometimes, when I'm alone I am seized by this feeling. But it á always helps me to come round and at the same time to judge if it á is worth. Very often this feeling is caused to me by people - á friends who I love and respect.
Such a feeling springs up in me sometimes when I have meals at a á catering establishment. It is a result either of the look of the á food or when watching the way some people eat.
This happens to me when I am not prepared in a given subject.

Quite unconsciously I offended a girlfriend of mine. It was á really worthy to pass this fact over in silence, but I acted so, á because I believed I was right. In fact it often happens to me to á feel guilt, after I have already done the deed.
When I was admitted to the University.

I had to have my tonsils out. I had been making up my mind almost á for a year - I was afraid. But during the two hours in the á hospital room, while I was waiting to be called for the operation I á felt a real fear - of the pain, of what they were going to do to á me, of the unknown.

In a conversation my boyfriend expressed definite and quite á pretentious opinions and he took up an attitude towards a theory á which he himself had never known. His information was from á fortuitous sources.

Summer, heavy rain, storm - I was standing with my face stick to á the window: the childhood, something was going away forever this á summer, I was leaving my home, I was going to study in another á town, for the first time I was leaving my parents, friends, I had á to manage myself, a long and loved period of my life was over - I á was crying.
I saw in the street a man spitting.
I talked with a man who stammered and without controlling myself, á I started to talk imitating him.
Always, and this happens often when I do not keep my word.
When I understood that I was admitted to the University.
I felt this feeling when one day my landlord's cat had crept á under my bed and I couldn't cope with it during an hour and a á half.
I feel this feeling when I am to fill in a questionnaire or a á form.
When the man I loved decided to leave me forever.
I have felt this feeling when a person whom I believe and respect, á lied to me.
I feel shame when sometimes, (unconsciously) I behave unethically á and without understanding the problems of the man I love.
When I offend somebody unfairly.

A quarrel was followed by the decision of leaving a person close á to me. Several days later my regret was great. I was beside á myself. Quite unexpectedly he came and the conflict was calmly á solved. I was glad at the possibility to be with him.

One evening I was watching the news on TV. Again they were á talking about the danger of war. Suddenly I imagined what it á might mean for me, for my friends, for the people close to me. I á felt it a very near and possible event.
Unfair and unjust attitude toward a person close to me, what I á was the witness of, caused anger in me.
The thought that I'll never sit at the school desk again, caused á a deep grief at the end of my eleventh form.
I felt disgust with a person whose behaviour was out of the á elementary human norms.
I had not punched a ticket in the bus because I had a card. But á when the ticket-collector came it turned out that I had forgotten á it. The shame I felt was great though it was not done on purpose.

At a moment of affect I offended a person very close to me. He á had given me ground for that but it was a trifling in comparison á with the way I insulted him. A moment later I felt a sense of á guilt.
When I understood I was admitted to the Sofia University.

The doctors from Belogradchik town determined a wrong diagnosis á to my son. A month later, after some complex examinations at ISUL á (A medical institute in Sofia), the diagnosis was categorically rejected.
My son lives with my parents in the country and I feel this á feeling always when leaving for Sofia, but the last time it was á quite strong.
A colleague of mine asked a lecturer to put him a higher mark in á order to keep his good mards and thus to continue getting a á scholarship for an excellent grade.
I felt this feeling during the exam in higher mathematics.
My son drank four pills of diazepam every two hours instead of á amidophen.
Before an exam in logics.

My husband and I were invited at the house of our nieghbours then á we got an invitation on the part of my parents which we had to á refuse. A a result they called me by words that provoked my á anger.
My son lives in the country. I feel sadness when I see mothers á having walks with their children.
The behaviour of a colleague of mine, which doesn't correspond to á my norms of behaviour.
I was to take part in a cocktail party on the occasion of our á national holiday as a servant.
I ignored and offended my parents on the eve of the New Year.

The sense of joy comes to me always after a period of depression, á as an organic feeling for an upsurge. I don't exclude the á situative feeling but in this case the reason is not in me, it's á out of me.
I bet that I would jump down from a window. I was sure that I á would jump but before I did it I rather felt fear.
A lie on the part of a person close to me.
I thought I had taken a decision but I hesitated.
I feel this feeling most often before me not before the others. á My outside is iron but actually I'm wasting away.
My son was born.
I had a car accident.
I was drawn up a statement for an infringement of the traffic á ordinance. In fact I was innocent.
I lost a close friend.
I saw a film about the nazi concentration camps during the war. á After the film I felt disgust.
I was nailed. I lied in connection with a book which I took from á the library, because I had to keep it for a longer time.
I didn't give back in time some money that I had borrowed. My á friend relied on them.
After 10 days of hard work and having suffered many changes I á passed my last exam.
Before going to the dentist.
When I am made to do things in which I see no sense and I waste á my time. Some time ago I had to participate in a sociological á investigation and then I got really angry.
When I feel I must be with somebody, to talk with somebody - but á I am alone.
I am ashamed when I am not ready for my seminar in internal á diseases, simply because the assistant professor is a person who á deserves high respect.

We had promised, with a friend of mine, to take our friends to a á restaurant and after having looked for a place for hours without á finding one, and not being helped by the others we had to give up á the idea.
When I am with friends and I do what pleases me this often á happenes.
When I have to go in for an exam and the examinor is a person á with a whimsical character and unsteady requirements.
I unfairly got a low mark on an exam and I failed to win a grant, á since then I don't have much confidence in myself at an exam.
It happened that I was alone - with no contacts with friends.
I met three drunk boys, almost children, they didn't look like á normal people.
I was totally unprepared for a seminar conducted by an assistant á professor whom I highly respect.
I got back too late after a Sunday going out without having á called up home to tell where I was. my mother hadn't slept the á whole night.
I was happy when I understood that the girl I liked was in love á with me.
I am afraid before an exam or colloquium.
I get angry when my smaller brother misbehaves and talks with indecent á words.
When my dog was stolen.
I experienced long ago when I was sightseeing Bulgarians in a á foreign language.
My mother developed hipertonia and I think I too am to blame á bacause with her it is a stress disease.
When I met with friends that I hadn't seen for a long time.
One evening a friend of mine was telling a fearful story, nobody á took it seriously but I got frightened.
I got angry with a stranger in a train who behaved impertinently á and immorally
When I failed at the first entrance exam.
The event which got me angry got also an aversion in me.
Once I was not ready for a seminar and I was asked to leave.
I felt guilty when once I made my mother angry.

Six months ago when I got acquaintanced with a person whom I á trusted infinitely and from whom I expected help and friendly á feelings. With him I found much in common - in our views and in á our fate.
Few days ago I really experienced fear. It was connected with á unexpected actions on the part of a group of people. This evoked á in me many negative emotions.
I always get angry when somebody deceives me, or tries to conceal á his lie skilfully and this offends me even more.

Sadness - this is an emotion which I have felt very often á recently. I can't remember a concrete example. I will describe my á general impression from severl situations which evoked this á feeling in me.

I became disgusted with the man on whom I had counted, who I had á trusted, the man who should have been my mainstay - my father. á I could hardly make myself (and the others) believe in this á emotion. It has cumulated after events and deeds. Everything can á happen in this world.
I am ashamed of the way my father behaves with my mother and á sister, and with me too.
I didn't keep a promise I had made to a man, and in this way I á lost his esteem and confidence in me. I caused him a lot of á trouble.
When I was accepted as a student.
I was a bit frightened when it was found that there was something á wrong with my liver. However it turned out that it was not á serious and I need not worry.
With the girl whom I may be loved truly. When she refused to come á with me to an occasion (she was from another town).
For the girl who halped me go on living and made me happy - when á I don't see her even for two or three days.
For a drunk man (about 20 years old) that I met one evening, and á who behaved impudently with the girls standing by.
I was embarassed at the exam in microbiology. I was ashamed with á myself - how little I knew and how good was the examinor. I á rarely become ashamed.
Recently when I made a slip and blurted out indecent words in my á mother's presence.
I felt it when on duty in the hospital I understood that I was á not afraid to face death, that I also helped a little to relieve á the pains of a patient.
Fear overwhelmed me when right against the car I was in I saw á another one, as if out of control of the driver.
I felt it when a girl who was dear to me lied to my face. I got á angry with the fact that she knew I didn't believe her but she á kept on telling lies.
Sadness, no, I felt something much stronger when my father died.
I got disgusted with a man who was beating a woman in the street. á I just happened to be there but I was abhorred by the rudness.
I was ashamed of the way I deceived that I could not help a á friend, although it was absolutely possible for me. Nothing was á revealed but I haven't called up this person since then.
I had an appointment with a colleague of mine to give her my á lecture notes. I couldn't go and I didn't send them, and so the á girl missed a day for the preparation of her term exams.
When I knew that my husband and I were going to have a child.
Two years ago I saw a film on the TV. Even now it makes me á afraid.
When my husband stays late at a meeting and I have to be alone.
The loss of a person I loved very much.
Deception from a person I loved very much.
I didn't tell my parents that I was going to Sofia. I told them á that I was going to a seminar. My mother knew that I was lying but á she didn't stop me.
The assistant professor saw me cheat at the preliminary á examination.
I was very happy when I got the message that I had been accepted á as a student in medicine.
I felt something close to that when I saw that there was a man on á the terrace of the flat.
I got angry when I learned how short a time we had to prepare for á the term examinations.
I felt sad when my first boyfriend and I left each other. It was neither á his fault nor mine.
I felt it today when the bus driver shouted rather indecent words á at a man without any reason whatsoever.
At an exam in pharmacology I tried to prompt a coleague (she á asked me something) and the assistant professor made me a sharp á remark.
My grandmother has been in a hospital for a week and I still á haven't had time to see her.
When I learned that my parents were going abroad and leaving me á alone for a few years.
I was at the seaside and my brother disappeared for a couple of á hours.

We were at a football match and when we were leaving the stadium á (the stadium was packed with people) and I lost my shoe in the á crowd. Our attempts to find it didn't give any result and I had á to go home without one shoe. In other words to cross the whole á town !

I felt guilty last year during the winter term exams. A colleague á of mine asked me to give him my lecture notes (I had very good á notes and I had passed my exam in advance) but I still don't know á why I didn't give them to him. That colleague failed and he was á on the verge of not passing it at the supplementary examinations.

When I was admitted to the Institute. I had problems with many á people about my applying for this institute and I decided to á prove that one can pass excellently without visiting any á preparatory couse. That is - I proved what I could do on my own.
Once as a child I dreamed of a fire. Since that time I hadn't á wanted to sleep in that bed and had feared the night darkness á (and so it is now).

A chief was unjustly punished on an autumn brigade and the one á who was really guilty kept silent. I stepped in front and told á the truth. The guilty chief called me in after the roll-call and á threatened me.

Years ago I fell in love for the first time. as natural for every á school-girl I was day-dreaming. Later (after 3 years) we left á each other. No one was to blame but I felt deep sadness. Even now á I remember about it quite often.
It was at a comsomol(??) meeting, the last one because we were to á graduate. The way one of my fellow-students behaved made me feel á disgusted.

I was at a children's camp abroad. The people (the leaders, my á coevals) were very king to us. One night we smeared our foreign á friends with tooth-paste while they were sleeping and then we á roused the whole camp by our shouts. Later I was so sorry. I á didn't utter a word for two days, then I went to apologize.
When I learned I was admitted to study what I wanted most - á floriculture (this is a narrow specialization from the general á one).
I was walking on the pavement when a white car rolled on it and á directed towards me. I was quite near the house wall when it á rolled by and hit me.

My grandmother's brother had taken active part in the resistance á movement. He had been in prison many times and there he lost his á health. He became an invalid. When we phoned to First Aid the á nurse on duty behaved quite unkindly when she understood how old á he was (79).
My boyfriend is a soldier. He was on a leave. I felt sad when we á had to get separated again.
I felt disgusted about a teacher who had rejected all that was á human in her. She refused to accept the flowers we gave her for á the eighth of March and asked for a foreign parfume instead.
I was examined by a teacher I greatly respected. I was well á prepared on the subjects but he put some side-issues to me and I á couldn't answer.
I had undertaken to help my sister for her class work but some á unexpected circumstances prevented me from doing that.
I was very glad when I learned I was a student already. I heard á about it over the phone, I didn't believe it at first.
I had worries about a certain illness.
When my first boyfriend left me. I tried not to let him á understand I felt miserable.
I hate hypocrisy. My friend (girl) tried to intrude into my á affairs with my future husband. After that she behaved as if á nothing had happened.
I feel shame when I have made a promise, I can't keep it and this á has negative effects which are caused by my behavior.
I felt it when I came home after the examination session and I á said I had not passed my last exam.
I felt glad when I took the rather difficult organic chemistry á examination.
This was what I felt when my boyfriend went to Bourgas to study á there. I had the feeling I would lose him. Anyway the distance á Plovdiv-Bourgas seemed to me so great.
I confronted with this feeling at the Institute quite recently, á the pedology lecturer was the cause.
This feeling was quite deep when my friend (girl) died in a car á accident.
I am disgusted with the behavior of a car driver whose car would á run over me and my friends during our autumn brigade.
I felt shame when I discontinued my education for eight months.
The sense of guilt came over me too, when I interrupted my á studies. Why ? Because I felt guilty before my parents ! They á believed in me though this event did not make them disbelieve me.
I sensed a strong feeling of joy when in the plant, at my working á place, I got a message that I was admitted as full time student at á the Higher Agricultural Institute.
Fear when fulfilling my obligations on my first night fatigue á duty as a soldier.
When on a car journey a fellow student crossed our way with his á own car and we had to bump into a roadside trunk.
The loss of a close relative who was ill with cancer.
I am disgusted with a nieghbour who is looking for all sorts of á quarrel with my parents and me. He feels we are hampering his á living close to us. This has been going on for quite a long time.
Some time ago I promised to meet an acquaintance of mine and to á carry him some promised papers. I haven't done it until this day. á Now I feel quite awkward when I meet him.
A sense of guilt before my parents when I had to discountinue my á studies in the first year because of unpassed exams.
After a difficult exam. When I had not hoped to take it and had á got a high mark. When you present someone with something and he á feels glad.
Fear from the unknown. I felt fear when I sat for the entrance á examinations.
I feel angry at people's indifference at our ability to be á present at an event and to stay partial to what happens.
When you are far away from relatives and friends. I feel sad for á my early years, for the freedom and the carefree years of á childhood.
I feel disgusted with the bootlickers, with helpless people.
I feel ashamed when I act dishonestly toward somebody.
I didn't visit a very close friend at the hospital and some days á later he died.
I was sitting for an exam in biochemistry, I was very excited á because it was a supplementary examination. I passed the exam á very well and was glad because I recovered my selfconfidence.
Students fear many things but we seem to fear the examinations á most of all. I remember I was horror stricken before my á microbiology exam, because it was a decisive one.

It was necessary to organise a competition in connection with a á celebration. Everyone was to be present at that event. It turned á out that there was no audience at all because everyone had á pretended to be very intelligent and no one had come. I got á furious.
When I part with my friends I feel always sad for some time. I á can't remember a concrete example now. For example I have just á parted with a friend of mine and I am feeling sad.

In autumn I had to move to another lodging. My landlords, quite á intelligent people, warned me I had to move in the nearest á future. But I had difficulties in moving my luggage because I á couldn't wait for a car to come. How amazed I was to hear them á threatening me they would throw our my things. And at that my á luggage was well packed and did not stand in their way. I was á quite  disappointed and disgusted.

During our last exarcise in agricultural machines we went out in á the yard to examine a row of machines. But we seemed not to have á fulfilled our task well, because when our teacher came and asked á me a question I was unable to answer. I felt awkward because he á didn't deserve it.
I remember about an unpleasant event in relation to my mother. I á felt guilty before her.
When I succeded in establishing a contact with a girl (who is now á my girlfriend).
I fear before each exam.
When my bosom friend tried to lie to me.
When I quarrelled with a very close friend of mine.
When I see the acts and deeds of a blind drunk man.
When I wasn't well prepared for a terminal exam and the teacher á tried to give me a three by asking me some very easy questions. I á burned with shame then.
When once my mother asked me to do some work for her at home á because she was busy and moreover this work was to be done by a á man. But it remained undone.
I feel joy usually after each taken exam, the last one was in á February.
It was not long ago when I and two of friends of mine got quite drunk á and one of them began to rave under the influence of the alcohol. á I felt fear of what could have happened.
I felt anger at my last exam, I felt angry with our teacher, á because he did not rate me objectively and I failed.
I met a girl some time ago and I cared very much about her but it á happened so that we left each other. I felt some sort of sadness, I think á I can call it so.
I had a very good friend (boy) and I thought I could rely on him á but he behaved badly with a girl who used to trust us completely.

Immediately after the New Year holidays I happened to visit a á party where there was a lot of alcohol and I became drunk. On the á next day I felt sort of ashamed when I remembered what I had said á and done on the night before.

Last year I put off an exam for the autumn session without á knowing if there was a supplementary examination session. When I á came home with my exam unpassed I felt guilty before my parents á when I remembered how much they had done for me.
When I was admitted to the Higher Institute.
I felt fear when I fell down and broke my leg into pieces and I á could not feel it at all.
I felt angry when I failed in an exam about which I knew quite a á few things and I did not deserve to be plucked.
When my mother and father were on an excursion in Chechoslovakia á and I was at a student camp and I heard over the radio about the á events that were taking place there.
I felt disgust with alcohol in general when a close friend of á mine got so drunk that he didn't realize what he was doing and it á was quite shameful.
I felt ashamed when my parents found out that I had deceived á them.

I felt guilty when I had taken the car keys and I had an accident á but as my parents did not know who was to blame, they punished my á brother because I had no driving licence and they thought it á impossible that had driven the car.
I felt joy when I was admitted to the Higher Agricultural á Institute.
I feel fear quite often but this feeling was very strong last á year when my husband was quite unexpectedly sent to the hospital.
That was what I felt with a teacher who put down quite unreal á marks.
I felt sad when a friend of mine died and I felt that something á had irrevocably gone away from me.
I felt disgust with a lady teacher who used to nag, to mock, to á interrupt everyone of my fellow students each time we had a class á with her in our first year.
That was what I felt when I told my first lie and then was á cought.
I felt guilty when I failed to take an exam though I had had á enough time to read for it but I hadn't made use of it.
I was for the first time on a brigade this year. At that time my á sister was to bear a child. I was mad with joy when I opened the á telegram from my parents and learned I had a nephew.
It was some years ago when one evening some people came home and á told us my father was badly injured in an accident.
I faced this feeling when I realized I wasn't admitted to the á institute in the first classifying, in spite of the high mark I á had got at the entrance examination.á
Always when I get separated from my friends and relatives from my á home town.
I feel disgust with my first boyfriend who made fun of our love á in an abominable way.
I have always felt ashamed for some people's behavior to their á too old parents. I have felt hurt and shy when they have left á them to the mercy of fate.
I feel always guilty before my parents when I come home and have á to tell them I have failed an exam.
Naturally when I got myself discharged this was my second á birthday.
When I failed my first exam at the Higher Institute.
A nuisance used to live in our flat a month ago. I experienced á this feeling when I tried to chase her out.
After my father's death.
With an alcoholic.
Once I had dinner at an elegant restaurant and I did not have á enough money to pay the bill. There were a lot of people there á and I felt quite awkward.
Something very unpleasant happened when I was a soldier and I was á directly involved in it.
I felt the greatest burst of joy when after being heavily ill for á a long period, my father came back home.
I was terrified during an axcursion in Italy. I was lost and left á alone in this unfamiliar country.
I took part in a football match. The referee was extremely á partial to the opposite team. This stirred up my discontent and á anger.
When my first girlfriend an I left each other.
During a summer holiday at a bar I happened to see a dead to the á world woman.
When I first had a sexual intercourse.
I remember when I was a little boy I broke a Swiss dinner set á quite involuntarily.
When I got a message that I was employed as a nurse at a á kindergarten.
When I first sat for an entrance examination.
When a teacher though pretending to be a highly cultivated á teacher and a man, slapped a classmate of mine in the face quite á undeservedly.
When I got separated from my first love.
Many times, when my father used to come home drunk and maltreated á physically me and my mother.
When for the first and the last time I tried to crib and the á teacher was with her back to me but right when I was taking the á materials out she turned round and saw me.
When at times unconscienciously I speak to my mother in a high á tome but after that I am sorry and I feel guilty.
Being invited out by a person I wished to get closer to. He á telephoned and invited me to go out with him the next night.
Watching a horror movie with friends.
The breakup of a relationship. After the event I was upset/sad á then angry maybe 2/3 weeks later.
The funeral of a friend who was killed in a car accident. She was á of my own age, there were many of my own friends present, as well á as her family etc.
Disgust for a person who treated me badly, and has treated other á people similarly - including lying, hiding facts, being á deceitful, unfair, etc.
Losing my temper and allowing myself to act childishly by yelling á and screaming at a person who I felt had done me wrong - in á effect lowering myself to their level.
Guilt at often being unable to visit a close relative in hospital á after her death I felt very guilty and wished I had done more.
Achievement of a task by a friend who had begun a new job. She á wasn't confident of handling the situation so was thinking  of á leaving the job only after 2 days employment.
Walking home at night after university - part of the way, there á are ano lights and I am walking down a thoroughfare with the á thouth of no one hearing me if I have to scream.
When my son omits to carry out certain duties at home that he á knows needs doing.
When I saw my niece (5 yrs) crying in the hallway for her mother á who had passed away about a month ago.
With a woman who had walked into my place of employment and á urinated on the floor in front of everyone.
When I had lied to a friend/son about some things we had á discussed and I had to be one better.
Felt joy a few years ago when I was away on holiday. And sat very á close to my best friend looking straight into the eyes.

I had to tell someone that I was interested in remaining celibate á and alone. And that my spiritual master strictly prohibited á sexual relations outside of marriage. This caused great fear á through lack of conviction afraid to hurt someone's feelings á despite my own being hurt in the process.

In a sociology class I felt very angry towards some members of á society for exploiting the Polynesian people, dawn raids by á Police (Martin Luther King, Blacks in S.A.). But this was just a á reflection of my own shortcomings.
Felt sad about some street kids in QUEII square, Aotea square. á Because they had been sniffing glue and some were very young. I á went into the role of a performing clown.
I was disgusted by my paranoid attitude towards myself, my á homework at university and disgusted about my lack of retention. á Especially in learning another language.

I felt shame at the hurt I caused to my family especially my á parent father, shame of hurting people emotionally. A misconceived á self-blaming that didn't do me any good. Shame at being myself as á I am.

I felt guilty at being part of the successful people. Felt guilty á at being a student when other people were not. Guilt about being á a potential success in various areas of society. (So stupid this á emotion)

When I meet old past pupils of mine - and find they are all doing á well - I feel joy. Yesterday I met a young woman (20 yrs) I'd á taught her at 6 yrs, then at 12 yrs and hadn't seen her for last á 3-4 yrs; she was no longer a waitress but a meter maid for á Council.
A sour looking man was beating his thin dog in Remuera.
I told Mr Winter of Downtown Fashion to go to - when he did not á accept my Visa !
When I accepted a lunch invitation from a past male friend.
When my daughter was born.
When my mother entered surgery for a quadruple heart bypass. I á felt intense fear at the time she was actually wheeled away.

When my husband got picked up in our new car for drunken driving. á We had made a pact the other would not drink and so therefore á would be the driver for the evening etc. I was not present at the á time.
When my grandmother died very suddenly without warning.
When the N.Z. rugby union announced that they would proceed with á a rugby tour of South Africa.
When I was unable to respond to a welcome in my indigenous á language of Maori at an important function where I was the only á woman in the group and it was expected of me.
When I made an excuse to get out of participating in an important á family occasion that I should not have missed.

This feeling of guilt really applies to moral/religious views. I á (being Catholic) went against what I was brought up to believe in á and had a sexual relationship with my boyfriend. Many months á later, when I was doing some deeper self analysis I began to feel á guilty and realized that I had gone against what I wanted for á myself and my future.
My mother along with some of my friends gave me a surprise á birthday party - they invited a large number of my friends along á too.

My mother did not come home till late at night (Ages ago). Anyway á if I don't know where my parents are and when they'll be back I á start thinking that perhaps they have had an accident and are á perhaps dead.

Because I am the Captain of a basketball team I usually organise á a roster system so that everyone in the team can have a turn at á doing either a duty or a ref. A lot of the time the girls can't á be bothered or just forget - I usually have to fill in.
So as to be closer to the university I have left home and moved á into Auckland. It now seems as if I have left home - especially á my family - forever.
A friend of mine goes out with this guy. She sleeps with him but á is quite happy for him to play around - as well as herself.
NO RESPONSE.

I did not attend a social studies observation class for 1 whole á week (I am a student trainee teacher). Anyway the other teachers á thought this was okay because the teacher I was supposed to á observe was not well liked. The teacher was in fact really nice á to me - but I wanted to get out of teaching a hard topic he had á given me.
Passing my pharmacy exams which meant my tertiary education for á pharmacy completed.
When I was in a car with my parents and friends and we had to á back up (reverse) pass a river which when I recall it (I was only á about 5 yrs) seemed we were going to fall in and drown.
When my boyfriend wouldn't dance with me on my graduation night á because he thought I could dance with my friends who were á friendly.
When my sister (really my niece) died of cancer at the age of 2 á yrs after I took her to the doctor at the age of 1 and he á diagnosed it.

The landlord had selected a new lodger on her own, while we used á to do that it was not what she had done, but how she did it that á made me angry.
It was a complex situation concerning a relationship with a á boyfriend, I had broken the relationship for some reasons. á Meanwhile, as I felt it, I had most sorrow.
I saw a terrible accident happen and I laughed a lot of the á fright and because I was nervous.
My mother wants to talk very often about her life. I dislike this á because she always talks negatively about the same people á whatever I do it doesn't help.
At the moment when I heard the result of an examination and it á proved that I succeeded the second year of my study.
I have a fobic anxiety for elevators. This anxiety is worst at á the moment when the doors have to open. I have it often in the á elevator at our university.
When someone accuses me without reason and is not willing to á listen to me.
My boyfriend decided to make an end to our relationship.
A person I know who tells lies and so pretending to be better á than she is.
When I am in an auditorium with people and I ask a silly question á so that everyone starts to laugh.
I moved to Nijmegen for my study. Soon after this my mother had á to be admitted in hospital because of cardiac compliants. I knew á that my moving was an important reason for this.
I can't give one description here. I often feel joyful when I á have done things good in relation to other people especially when á my friend says he loves me and I also tell him that I love him.
I was afraid when my first boyfriend threatened to make an end to á our relationship because he didn't love me enough while I loved á him very much.
A good friend deceived me. Because of that little quarrel our á relationship finished, mainly because she was not honest. I was á very angry about that.
I was very sad when my first boyfriend finished our relationship.

I was once raped (one year ago) by a man who was a lot older than á me and whom I just met. Maybe it wasn't rape but the man wanted á more than I wanted to give him since there were other people in á vicinity.
I felt shame when I didn't study enough for my exams and as a á result I failed. I then invented idle stories to talk it good for á myself and the others.
I felt guilty when I once went out with another boy and made love á with him while I had a close boyfriend.
When my boyfriend came back after being away for 10 days.
When I was sitting in a car next to a man who was masturbating.
When my mother told things to my sister, which I told my mother á in confindence.
Tonight in bed when I realised how bad my relationship with my á friend was.
When I was in Eindhoven on an Exhibition of Hernan Nitsche, who á made paintings with real blood. There were also photographs about á the killing of cows.
When I made an end on a relationship after three years.
That I didn't want my friend to leave on holiday for 10 days á because I thought I would miss him. I was constantly trying to á persuade him.
When I was making music together with my friend. It sounded very á good and we were very satisfied.
When my cat ran under a car and came home wounded. He could á hardly walk. I didn't dare to go to a veterinarian because I was á afraid he would kill him.
I had to unscrew something on my car. I didn't succeed after two á afternoons of trying. A feeling of anger built up itself.
Losing my girlfriend who made an end to our relationship. By this á I lost an important source of support, certainty and joyful á moments. I cried very intensly when that happened.
A few days ago I saw two dandy girls of my age. I disliked their á clothes and their way of doing.
During carnaval I danced for a few minutes normally I don't dance á because I am rigid in my moving around during a dance, I stopped á very soon.
I had a girlfriend which I used to call regularly. Then I didn't á phone her for a while. At a certain moment I felt a little á tension which became worse.
At an important moment in a volleyball game we made a point and á by this we won a set from a much stronger competitor.
When I went out with my dog in a forest late at night when we á were on a camping.
I had an appointment with someone at a certain time. The other á person didn't appear.
When I entered the operation theatre and underwent a difficult á operation.
When my friends left without waiting for me, after we had arranged á to go out together.
When they gave away my dog to other people without my knowledge.
When I had to eat scraps from a dust-bin, because of a bet.
At the airport, eighty beer cans that I was carrying in a á bag spread all around while I was going through the metal á detector.
When I took a car which was not mine, and suddenly it stopped á working.
When the Real Madrid team of basket ball qualified for the final á of the Europe Cup at Athens.
On the scenic railway at the fairground.
At having an argument with a stranger, in the street.
[ The same as in guilt.]
When I entered a toilet in a bar and it stank.
The day I finished my military service.
When I was a child, one day, I was going home late at night and I á did not notice an uncovered man hole and fell in it.  I was in there for á several minutes.
One day, when I was a child, my grandmother shut me up in a room.
The day I left my first girlfriend.
One day I was in the countryside with several friends, and we á began to eat figs, after we were all full we noticed that all the á figs were full of worms.
When I got my fingers stuck in one of the side holes of the door, á in the tube.
I ran over my dog with a bicycle when I was carrying him tied to á the handle bar.
When I won the first prize in a cross country race.
I found myself involved in a fight in which a person died and I á had to intervene with some risk.
An argument among friends in which my opinions on the way to á spend spare time were disapproved.
I was forced to leave an unforgettable friend.
I saw the gare of a prison.  This gare and the building were in á deplorable condition and were full of rubbish.
A mishap suffered on misinterpreting a girl's proposition.
I thought that I could have avoided the above situation (the one á in fear) if I had concentrated more on my work, which I hate.
When I passed the last exam, which I had doudts about.
Before I had a tooth pulled out.  I was very upset and ill.
When the Real Madrid football team lost against the inter in the á U.E.F.A cup.
When my dog died.  I had reared it for nearly three years.  It á had been ill for several days and had not eaten anything.  One á morning I found it dead.
On a trip to Santander a child sitting beside me fell ill and á started to vomit, seeing this made me feel very bad.
I fell down in the bus when it braked suddenly and everybody á started looking at me.
When I finished a test type of exam and did not dare to answer á any question, I doubted whether I would pass the exam  or not.
When I was back home after a long time, meeting beloved people á and close friends.
When I heard about the treatment of a friend in jail. Really á inhuman. I never realised that such things also happen in the á Netherlands.

I cannot remember a situation in which I felt ashamed. I was á eating with some people and a little boy I took care of. I warned á him often not to knock down his glass of mild. When I took á out his chair I knocked down my own glass.
My mother always took my side. That brought about quarrels with á my father. I knew she didn't like that and I felt very sorry for á that.
When on holiday in Greece I called my best friend, she told me á she passed the examinations and that she had been admitted to the á study for speech therapy.

Together with a little brother I biked on a lonely road in the á Polder. Then we were annoyed by a boy on a motorbike: he á took over, stopped, took over, etc. Then we saw he had something á in his hand, we turned until we came across a man, who á accompanied us.
We lived with 3 persons in the loft of a house. It often occurred á that other persons again and again climbed the stairs with much á noise. When I was studying I couldn't concentrate and got angry.

I was shopping in Utrecht with friends, we also ate some chips á and snacks in a snackbar, then we saw a shabby fellow. He took a á cold half eaten croquette (a snack) from a rubbish bin and eat á it.

I had subscribed for this test. We were informed by our á secretary where the test took place. We went over there and thought á there was a course. So we went back again I felt ashamed that the á secretary again should see me.
I was out with a friend in a place where it was very, very busy. á When we wanted to go I bumped a person, who dropped his glass á beer I offered a new one but he didn't accept it.
It appeared that I gave correct answers to all questions during á an examination of personality while I thought I performed very á badly. Even now, I don't know how I managed it.
My father was very angry with me, and I locked me up in the á shower. Then my father knocked his fist through the door, I was á scared to death.
My sister borrowed some LP records for a party. She had left them á in the car on curatao. Due to the heat they were crooked, so I á couldn't play them again.
When my grandmother died, her life was heavy and her last hours á were terrible.
We had arranged a beach party with 20 people. There my father got á drunk I felt very ashamed.
When I flew out to my mother and made rude remarks because I felt á so tense (studied too hard for an examination).
Unofficially I was informed about my results of the final á examination of the secondary school. A teacher wrote them up for á me. When I went outside, I started crying with joy.
I am thinking about death, the eternal of it, the unknown, the á sense of being here. Often, laying in bed in the dark and quiet, á the fear makes me feel dizzy.
If they force me to eat something I don't like. For example, my á parents always twaddle and whine, when I don't eat all the food.
I had to leave Den Helder and all friends and acquaintences, á after having spend two weeks there with my friends.
Being on view in a meat-factory. Pigs being cut open, pigs being á suspended from nods, blood everywhere, decompsition.
When I have suffered a terrible fit of eating, that frequently á occurs. Then I eat everything, I act like a glutton I eat big á amounts of food, sometimes even half a loaf.
When my father (physically handicapped) asks me to do something á and I raise several objections. Often I can fix it in few á moments.
When the parents of my girlfriend gave permission to spend our á holiday together.
When the relationship with my first girlfriend broke up and I á realized it too late.
Someone who always took care for the key of the sportshall stayed á away without letting us know. Next time he did as if nothing had á happened.
When my last relation broke up.
When working in a chemical laundry, I saw rats and maggots in the á washing.
When I forgot the birthday of my best friend and I innocently á came to visit her one week later.
When I made love with a girl, which I don't really love. However á I know that she loves me.
When I passed the driving test (on the second try).
I was walking in the wood at night with my boyfriend. Very á romantic. Suddenly I heard a car driving very slowly with the á lights out, it looked as if they were looking for something.
I am a teacher in arts and crafts (boys from 15-16 years). for á them it is obligatory and they dislike it. They tease me. When one of á them cut up some material I flared up.
My sister was in coma for 3 months (due to a train accident). Now á her brainfunctions are disturbed. She will never be able to walk á and she can hardly talk.
I lived together with my boyfriend. One night he stayed away and á next day he told me that he had chat up with another girl.
I talk too much, cannot keep things secret. I promised a friend á not to tell something to anybody. Neverthless, I did, and she got á informed about it. I felt very ashamed.
My parents appreciate very much me and my boyfriend coming and á have dinner with them at Christmas. However we decided to visit á his parents. My mother was rather disappointed.
When I started a relation with a girl, with whom I have fallen in á love already some time ago.
When I was 10 years old I stained our bench with a fountain-pen, á I tried to twin the cushions, but then there were colour nuances. á Then my mother catched me, she saw it and became very angry.

I spend the night with my boyfriend, while there was also a á friend of his. We all lay on the floor to sleep. When my á boyfriend was fallen asleep the other boy and I started petting. á After 15 minutes I felt miserable and awoke my boyfriend to tell á him that.

I liked to see off my aunt (from Zaire) to the airport. That á appeared to be impossible because I had to go to school. For long á time I wasn't sure if I could accompany her. Two days before the á departure they told me I was allowed to miss school.

I went to the ballet lessons with a little friend in the dark. On á a very quiet place a boy approached us from behind and asked at á what time the lesson would be finished. I gave him an avoiding á answer, he took me up and wanted to run away with me.
