I was sleeping nicely until in the middle of the night when I became á awake because a friend called me for some (in my opinion) á nonsens reason.
My boyfriend with whom I had a longlasting relationship, fell in á love with another girl, then he asked me something which implied á that he loved that girl more than he loved me.
On school, during a fancy fair, there was a stand of amnesty á international. There I read (for the first time) a description of á the tortures of a woman, what they did to her.
A friend catched me while masturbating. I am not fully sure á whether she saw it or not.
When I was 4-5 years old my mother gave me some parts of a á chocolate bar and ordered me to bring it to my father working á outside. On my way I could not resist the temptation and ate it á myself.
When I had to undergo the final examination of secondary school, á I lived together with a girlfriend. We both were afraid to fail, á but it appeard that we both had passed.

When I had left my home, my father, under false pretences, got me á in his car and drove home where we were all alone. He was seethed á with rage because I withrew from his authority. He hit me, kicked á me and threatened me.
When my mother found a leaf of my diary where I had written about á my mother's lack of education, especially her poor arithmetical á insight.

Very often I take care for my little sister and oversee her á duties. Most of the time everything went fine, but sometimes she á absolutely didn't want to obey; then I hit her (we frequently á were hit by our father).
Passing my driver's examination (after two failures).
When I was six years old we were on holiday in France. There was á very heavy weather then.
A quarrel with my mother because I thought she said very á unreasonable things about me, that hit me strongly.
The disease and subsequent death of a close acquaintance. Sadness á was accompanied with feelings of powerlessness (I also á experienced sadness in the situation described under guilt).
When I take a look into a slaughter-house and when listening to á stories about torturing people or animals.
Making bloopers: e.g. telling something negative about a certain á person, while that person is standing besides you and hears á everything.
I wanted to finish a relationship after 3 months. Unfortunately á my friend had a different opinion. I could not answer his á feelings this made him unhappy, and me feel guilty.
When a friend of mine had her period, while thinking she was á pregnant.
Fear to come and live in Nijmegen.
When the coach of our team degraded me to the second team.
When a friend died.
When I saw a documentary film about World War II (about Hitler á and his adepts).
When I realised that I had rejected a boy, who was fallen in love á with me, rather bluntly four times.
Spending the nitht with close friends, after being away (out of á Nijmegen) for a while.
Just before I started my study I had to move, I was very afraid á to be left alone and that I could not manage it.
When anybody wants to make me feel guilty. For example: I should á do something for my mother, but things didn't go as she hoped. á Then she threatens: I'll do it myself.
When a close friend took leave of me, because she went to Israel á for one year.
I wanted to take something from under my bed. While doing this I á felt a dead bird laying under my bed.
I stayed at home for a period because I felt depressive and I á neglected my study when people adked me, I told them that I had á freeterm and studied hard. I felt ashamed for my behavior and á lies.
A fellow player, quite unexpectedly, scores a goal, which means a á draw.
In college, I started a discussion with the teacher referring to á a question I posed. I felt very unsure and I was afraid to fail.
While playing indoor-hockey, there always is an older man who á frequently and intentionally plays the ball out of the field. In á my opinion this is very childish, because we play for fun only.
I was together with my family one night, a few days after my á father had died, during that conversation I expressed my á displeasure because nobody understands me.
Salo, a movie film by Pasolini. People were misused and tortured á for the fun of a few elder Italian authorities, during World War á II.
I was jerking me off in my bedroom, when suddenly, my mother came á in. She looked at me and immediately left the room.
My girlfriend and I agreed to go to the cinema. However I á completely forgot our appointment. I remembered it two hours á too late when I went to visit her.
When my boyfriend once again told me that he loved me after a á period in which he felt very depressive.
When, late at night, I discovered that they had stolen my bike.
When a friend, after being free of drugs for half a year, started á using them again.á
In a disco, there was a dirty little chap who punched my bottom.
When a friend who comes visiting me unexpectedly asks for coffee á and I refuse to give him this.
Watching a football game. This remindes me of the time when my á father was still alive and when we watched football games on TV á together.
Seeing someone who has bleeding nose.
Asking someone to give me back the money I once lend him because á I needed it myself.
When I tell someone no. In other words when I refuse to do á something although I could have helped him.
When I got a good grade for an exam in statistics.
One night at three o'clock I was followed by a cardriver, who á tried to molest me.
My father promised me a bicycle for my birthday. Just before my á birthday he forgot he promised this to me.
A younger brother of a good friend of mine died (asthma).
I read a book about torture. The book described exactly how the á torturing was done.
I made a joke about the rat of a boy. I compared his rat with a á sausage. I told the boy he had a delicious sausage.
After a courtship of three months I made an end to it. The boy á was very sad about this.
I had a very pleasant conversation with one of my friends.
I had a dream about my fiancTe leaving me and making an end to á our relation.
My bicycle was demolished.
During the funeral of my grandmother, when I saw my mother and á other family members crying.
A fellow student who seemed very nice later on proved to be a á slimy fellow towards a professor.
My father was very angry with another man in the presence of my á friends.
I once drank too much alcohol and became very ill. This was in the á presence of my friends.
This week I was phoned by an old friend with whom I lost contact á a few years ago.
I was raped by a friend.
Last year I had a friend visiting me for several days. The only á thing he did was sleeping, drinking, taking pills and thinking á only about himself.
My girlfriend does practice and therefore leaves me alone at á night and in the weekend. In addition, she is very busy doing á several things. So we don't see each other often.
My father suddenly fell ill. He stayed for 3 months in the á hospital: the last month on intensive care of the Academic á Hospital, then he died.
Bisshop Ter Schure intoduced himself on TV to the Dutch Nation. á He spoke as if he was God himself, and didn't discuss the way he á had achieved this position.
After having failed my driving test.
When I see that my mother forces my little brother (15 years) to á work very hard for school. I don't agree that she constantly puts á him to work, but I don't tell it to her, so nothing changes.
I thought that someone was angry with me but, by hindsight, that á didn't appear to be the case, he even liked me.
Recently, I left my bag in the car of someone who picked me up á while hitch-hiking. I spent some effort to find out where he á lived (I succeeded).
In Biarritz (the South of France) I met some English students á who, especially for me, went to Paris and gave me food, while I á didn't have any more money.
When I passed the driving test already on the first try, although á I felt more and more uncertain as the day came near.
When my father suffered with dizziness. He had to be á hospitalized, because the physician didn't know what was wrong. á Because his stools were black, I thought it could be cancer.
When I arranged our holiday in Paris, and my girlfriend raised á criticisms all the time.

When it suddenly appeared that our dog was dangerously ill and á probably would die. We had not expected this because he á was always very healthy. Fortunately he survived because we, in turn, á gave him medicines during the night.
When a girl in my class (on the secondary school) appeased the á teacher, resulting in getting a higher grade. This occurred often á with her.
When I arrived too late at a meeting of mentor (the night before á the introduction of novices on the University start).
When my father told me that I should help my mother more often, á because she was so busy. And I realized that he was right.
Passing an examination, although I felt sure I had failed.

I lived in a student-house, where you shared the lavatory and á shower with a fellow student. the shower cubicle formed the á connection between both appartments. My neighbour very often was á drunk and aggressive. One night, I was afraid that he would enter á my room.

I suffer from a disease of my muscles. Therefore, I am only able á to attend lectures for half a day. So, sometimes I miss á obligatory lectures. However, the teachers do not take into á account my disease, and punish me with detention work, resulting in á an overload.
I suffer form a disease of my muscles. However, I cannot talk á about it and my feelings, the consequence with my parents. They á try to repress it.
Going out for dinner, or during one ice-cream and four spoons.

I borrowed a piece of music of someone and I always forgot to á give it back. That person wrote me a letter asking me to give it á back. I did so and I told him an idle story why I kept it for so á long.
When armed robbers broke into our house at night.
When a pick-pocket robbed me of my money (K20) while I  was á buying bathing soap.
When I failed the grade seven examination.
When my friend who was drunk insulted me in public for no reason at á all.
When I tried to steal a book from the bookshop and was caught.
When I was caught with another man's wife.  I had taken the á opportuinty as this man was abroad but he returned that night.
The day I learnt that I had been admitted to the university.

When I had gone for a boxing tournament which ended at 2 o'clock á in the morning.  I was alone on my way back, and I could hear the á barking of the dogs, the nocturnal animals and the sound of my     á own footsteps.  There had been a rumour  circulating that there á were ghosts in that area.

In 1983 a sadist provoked my sister in my presence.  He tried á to force my sister into accompanying him to his place, but my á sister did not agree and so she was kicked and she fell down.  á There was a fight.

When my father passed away in 1978.  I was left alone with my á mother who was very sick so I had to go and live with my aunt, who á is very short tempered, till my mother was discharged from the á hospital.
When I learnt that my best friend had failed the exams.
I broke my friend's badminton racket and she kept quiet about it.
Making an unexpected talk with a professor in the canteen. This á made me shy.
Flirting with other girls while I already had a very good á relationship. When there are problems in my relationship, the á flirting increases as does the feeling of guilt.
Occurs frequently. A recent experience: when going out with many á friends, nice music, after the examinations, I felt so happy I á could have embraced everybody.
I lived alone in a repulsive area in the city of Rotterdam. I was á annoyed, heard a lot of Burglary and assaults. Especially in the evening á and the night I frequently felt anxious.
Being treated unfairly and being hurt by someone I love.
The death of my mother-in-law after a long sick-bed. at the á moment of dying I was with her.
I was looking at a one-man show on television. He told very á disgusting things so that I started to be disgusted with it. á (Later on it proved that this was his intention).
I was drinking a glass of wine and eating something when there á suddenly appeared pictures about the famine in some parts of á Africa.
When I don't go to my parents on Sunday and phone them to tell á them that I have to study. The truth is that I listened to sports á on the radio.
When it appeared that I was not pregnant when I was several weeks á overtime.
The same situation as with sadness. I was afraid about what my á parents would further do to distroy my relationship.
Once again my parents distroyed a relationship.
I had this feeling when my parents distroyed a relationship with á a boy because they thought he was bad and irresponsible.
After the accident which I described in SHAME. I came to myself á and saw how terrible everything looked like. I disgusted myself á and everything I saw.
A sudden end to the relationship with my first girlfriend.
I heard part of a conversation in which one talked very low about á women.
In an important situation for me, my father behaved inadequately.
When I took the car of someone without saying it to him.
I felt joy when I heard that I was accepted for the Free á University in Driebergen.
When a good friend of me told me one evening that she didn't want á to live anymore.
I felt anger when at the end of a telephone call, a good friend á told me that she would go to travel next year with another good á friend. We couldn't talk this out.
I was very sad when I had to leave persons with whom I had a very á intense relationship I also had to leave the environment which á was part of this.
I felt disgust after watching a picture on television about á torturing political prisoners in India (this happened in the á India of Indira Ghandi).
I made a very insulting remark against a person whom I care for á very much. This event was caused by a third person who didn't á like the person I insulted.
I felt guilt towards my mother when I went to live on rooms in á Nijmegen where I study.
When my boyfriend and I went out for a dinner and subsequently á went to his family. We had a very nice evening.
When I walk through streets late at night. This is because I and á my friends were attacked one night without any reason for it.
When I got the feeling that I had to do all the housekeeping á while my boyfriend didn't do anything. This happened in a period á of exams when I had to study very hard.
When my best friend got a boyfriend. Because of this a á relationship of ten years was finished abruptely.
I feel disgust when hearing or seeing other people being treated á inhumanely. For example torturing in chili.
In my opinion guilt is a feeling which goes together with shame. á Here then I refer to the situation of guilt.
When I became angry at my boyfriend without any reason. I know he á cannot bear me being angry at him and that he can't study anymore á then.
The day I heard that I passed the high school exam.
I was living in rooms in a very lonely, quiet neigbourhood. á During the night it was very silent and this frightened me. The á fact of being alone in that house frightened me.
We had to move to a very different city because the company where á my father worked also moved to that place. It was very difficult á for me to make new friends than.
A very close friend of mine died. I read it in the newspaper. I á didn't know what to do and thought about it the whole day.
A girl who also hires a room in the house where I live always á tries to make a quarrel with everyone available she disgusts me.
A teacher spent a lot of time helping me without wanting to be á paid for it. For the exam I didn't got a good grade and I felt á ashamed.
I knew I had to take an exam very soon but yet I couldn't start á studying. I also knew it was very imprtant to succeed the exam á this time.
When Christmas holiday started, I felt very joyful when I á finished my last exam.
I was raped once when I went through a dark alley at the back of á our house. The man pushed me in the bushes. I fought back and á succeeded to escape.
I was very angry at my father when he didn't give me as much á money as my brother to use for studying. Once again my brother á was better off then me.
When my gradmother died.  I felt very sad then ... The feeling á started to be worse after a while.
When I ate a rotten apple.
When I didn't meet an appointment I had made. The person phoned á me but I thought of something (I told I was ill) so that I didn't á have to go.
When I have to take exams I am very excited and have not much á time for the housekeeping. Then my friend has to do everything.
My boyfriend was playing with my cat. He was playing games with her á and telling nice things to her.
When I slept for the first time all alone in the house where I á live now. A man phoned me at 2.00 am. He wanted something from á me. I was afraid.
My boyfriend told me that I had very high demands towards him. In á my opinion this was wrong.
I hadn't been at my parent's place for a long time. When I went to á visit them I had high expectations, but when I was there it was á very different from what I expected.
I read a story in the newspaper about butchers treating their á animals very badly. They disgusted me.

I was eating in a very nice restaurant, when the servant asked á whether I liked the food I told him that I liked it but that á there was one thing which wasn't so good. The servant than worked á very hard to make it good.
A few weeks ago I thought about an exam I had to take soon. I á remembered this just before I had to go to sleep. I felt guilt á because at the beginning of the year I planned to succeed.
During my high school time I succeeded to play a concert of á Mozart on the piano when I gave my first performance I succeeded á to play it very well.
When someone does not listen to me after having asked me to á repeat what I said. This happened more than one time with the á same person.
I felt very sad when I heard that a friend had committed suicide.
One night I saw a man being knocked down by two other men. The á victim was kicked against his head.
When I made acquaintance with the parents of my boyfriend for the á first time. They spoke Limburgian (a dutch dialect) and one of my á first remarks was that I disliked Limburgian dialect.
When I cancelled an appointment with an idle story. Afterwards á it appeared that the person had looked forward to it and reserved á time for it.
For a few days I felt very miserable, distressed and listless, á with crying fits. When this was over I felt very happy, although á there was no special reason.
I was testing my new roller skates in the street, suddenly a dog á ran barking in my direction, very threatening. I was very á startled and terribly upset.

Out on a weekend with a group of people, everybody felt irritated á because at night the music didn't stop in time. And at breakfast á my boyfriend ran away because we didn't agree with him. I felt á angry.
Recently I felt very sad without any reason. It lasted for a few á days. There was nothing I liked in that period.

Someone told me a story of Amnesty International: a boy was á killed and his head was put in the litter of his girlfriend. It á looked as if she was pregnant, then she died. It is disgusting, I á can hardly write it down.
I cried for 3 hours because I felt very miserable. Then I called á my boyfriend and he said lovely things to me. After this feeling á disappeared I felt ashamed.
Yesterday my boyfriend and I wanted to play billiards. However á there were boys playing (5 times). My boyfriend then is fed up á and chagrined. In such case I think it is my fault.
When my boyfriend and I experience something nice or when we have á made a nice walk together.
The weather is very bad (fog and slipperiness) the newcast á reports many traffic accidents and my boyfriend is driving home á and still has 60 kilometers to go.

Someone told me that he would stay at my home for one night. á Therefore I made big efforts to make everything ok (food). One day á before he cancelled the appointment because he had to go to á church with his parents.
We had to take our cat to the vet for mercy killing (an á injection).
When people are eating unsavoury (smacking, belching, speaking á with food in their mouth, etc.).
I made an appointment to pick up someone. However I arrived á too late and she had to wait a quarter of an hour.
One night I had a very good conversation with two friends. I then á realized how worthy they were for me and how happy I was to á have them as friends.
In the morning just before going to the dentist.
When a very close friend with whom I have a very intimate and á bodily relationship (he had a girlfriend) started to avoid me and á didn't want to talk to me any more.
When a good friend with whom I had an intimate relationship made á clear that he didn't want to continue in the same way. He choose á his girlfriend (also a friend of mine).
When I made love with someone who I didn't really love. Sometimes á I even considered him unlikable.
I had a short lasting sexual relationship with someone I didn't á love.
When I realized that I avoided two good friends with whom I á always shared toys and sorrows. I made up idle stories to avoid á telling them what happened to me.
My boyfriend suffered form ill health for some months, this week á the physician told him that he was restored to health.
When going out in the weekend I have to bike 5 kilometers through á lonely and dark polders, then I always have terrifying fantasies.
I made an appointment with a friend to drink coffee togehter. á However, for the third time in that week she arrived an hour too á late.
My dear hamster (called Hannes) died at the age of 2 and 1/2 years. á His shape forced me to mercy killing (an injection).
I read a newspaper report that a little boy was forced to look á while his sister was raped.
We had made an appointment to complete together a piece of work. á It appeared that I was the only one who hadn't prepared anything.
I call my mother at least once a week. However last week I á completely forgot. This morning she called me, she thought I felt á ill.
After the funeral of an acquaintance I felt very depressed. That á feeling turned into joy when I heard that I had achieved a good á grade for an examination.
I had to call someone and make an appointment for a conversation. á I was very afraid to fail.
When, after having cleaned up the kitchen, two hours later I saw á that there was a big mess. It irritated me very much.
One night I was called and told that the father of a close friend á died. When I visited my friend at home and when attending the á funeral I felt very sad.
I cannot remember exactly such a situation. But I know that á once I went to a very dirty lavatory and that disgusted me.
Once by coincidence I clutched a stranger (in a rather intimate á way), thinking it was my boyfriend. When by hindsight I á feel ashamed when thinking about it.
I once torn the inner tube of a bike, that was not mine. Then I á saw it was a brand new one. I felt very guilty then.
When I found out that the girl, with whom I was in love, loved me á too.
When my mother threatened me with thrushing me of the stairs, when á I once more should make a comment.
When being made look a fool by the teacher in front of the class á during a turn.
My mother unjustly became very angry with me and sent me to my á room while my father explained that the way she saw things was á not correct. I had done things with the best intentions.
My mother was very angry with my little sister and told her to á put her hands on the table in order to beat her hands up. She á forced by means of her power.
A friend came for dinner with me at home. His parents are á ordinary people. My mother, however, used the very expensive á porcelain dinner-service and the silver cutlery. I felt very á ashamed.

Once after falling in love, I imagined that particular girl to be á perfect and completely overshadowing my girlfriend. Afterwards I á realized that this image was not objective. I felt guilty against á both girls.

Once a week I work as a volunteer in a biologic garden. this work á in the garden and the contact with other volunteers filled me á with joy. They also gave me support after I failed passing my á driver's test.

My friend and I planned to search for old documents and utensils á in the cellar. It was very late at night when we arrived in the á cellar. He indicated the place where the police (40 years ago) found á two dead bodies. I got very scared when he told me this story.
When someone made me a compliment after an examination just at á the moment I needed it. It was amicable, hearty and sincere.
When I went up the stairs in a high, dark house full of shadows, á passed a door and had the feeling that someone or something was á behind me, although I knew I was alone.

A friend told me it would be better for me not to be on familiar á terms with another friend, although, in my opinion he had no á reason to say such things. He only said so hoping that I á would search support from him (that, however, was not necessary).

I had a good relationship with two friends. Once without reason, á they clearly showed that they thought I was naive, dull and á unable to take care for myself, while I expostulated that I could á manage things.
When I see that some people remain cold and egoistic with regard á to close friends, even in situations that those friends need á them.
When I state things with great positiveness and try to convince á others, and it appears that my statement is not right.

A certain friend evokes positive feelings, when I am with him but á negative feelings when he is not present. I feel the need to á express those negative feelings. However, when I speak about him, á I always think: Why do I like this, he does not deserve this, but á still I do so.

A few days ago, I hitch-hiked to Arnhems with a friend. á Everything went well: they picked us up very quickly, the sun was á shining, I was feeling free and, for the first time after long á time, happy. I really had the feeling that I was living at full á speed.
My grandmother several times has been struck by cerebral á hemorrhages. Until now she recovered well each time, but there is á always the threat to loose her.

I had made an appointment with three friends. We had to go out á together. When I arrived at the place, the other persons weren't á there. I became very angry because I thought they were gone á without me. That, however, didn't appear to be the case.
I finished the relationship with my boyfriend, after having felt á myself very unhappy for a long time.
A few days after I had finished the relationship with my á boyfriend, we had a quarrel. Then he hit me. At that moment I á found him disgusting.
I was taking a shower in a cubicle in France. Then I discovered á that a few children were loking at me from the adjacent cubicle.
I know that a certain person feels very lonely, and that she á always looks forward to seeing me. However, often I am too á busy to visit her, then I feel guilty.
A close relative of mine underwent a difficult operation, and everything á turned out fine.
When I get into the tube or the train without paying for the á ticket.
A class-mate urged me to carry out a particular protest along á with him, and when the time came this fellow drew back while I á had to face the situation.
When I failed the entrance exam to IMEC.
When I saw someone eating live worms.
When I was a child my parents caught me with a pornographic á magazine.
[ I can not remember anything in particular.  What I can remember á is feelings of having done or said something which then had á negative consequences.]
When they told me that I had got a study grant.
When I wore a grotesque figure hanging down my back.
Because I had not studied.
When my father was saved from a severe work accident.
When I was a child I hid under the sheets out of fear of á darkness.
When I first saw a person begging.
When my basket ball team lost the qualification at a final.
When I see rotten meat.
When a person whom I do not want to see is continously present.
When I failed an exam I thought I could pass easily.
When I got to know that I had passed the university entrance á exam.  I thought that I had done one of the exams badly.

When I was very young, one day, I was in the street with my á father and brother.   While my father was talking to some á friends, I saw a dog and began to pat it.  My father told me á sharply to stop doing it because the dog had mange.  Then my á brother told me that I would die and I could not stop crying á after this.

We hitch hiked our way back from a town rather drunk.  We were á dropped in another town which was unknown to us.  I needed to á urinate, so I did it on a wall which turned out to belong to the á military headquarters.  They arrested me and made me pay a fine á of 500 pts.  We had to go home on foot (6 km) since it was too á late for anyone to give us a lift.

I was to meet a girl in a discotheque.  She was very pretty and I á was very happy.  But she did not turn up.  Thank God, there were á some other friends there and I was able to have a more or less á good time.
I had a class-mate who was rather stupid.  I did not like him á but I respected him.  When he tried to talk to someone, they á would not listen to him and I could not bear seeing this.

I met a friend in a discotheque. he was with a girl and he told á me that she was not his girlfriend.  I, to say something, á commented that she must be a viscious woman.  He then told me á that she was his girl.

I went to a pub with a group of friends (not very close) and á I was with one girl most of the time, while the other girls in the á group wanted to be with me.  They stopped talking to the girl I á was with.
The day some friends of mine and I decided to go to Galicia on á holiday.
Before an exam which I, finally did not take.
At home when they lost three pieces of my puzzle.
When I had an argument with a friend.
When I am dirty because I have not had a shower for a few days.
Once I did not have enough money to pay for a coffee.
After an argument with a friend of mine.
A friend of mine told me that I had passed the entrance exam to á the university.
Before taking an exam.
My family told me to leave if I was not willing to accept the á conditions they imposed on me.
A friend of mine called me when I was not at home.  I phoned her á back to know what she wanted and she told me that she had dialled á the wrong number.
I had to change a baby's clothes for the first time.
I fell outside the door of my house.
My younger sister was almost run over by a lorry.
When my brother was born.
When I almost fell down from some rocks because I had been acting á foolishly and playing dangerously.
Once I saw some children hunting a cat to death.
The death of a friend.
When I saw a scene on T.V where a castration was shown.
Once I answered my father rudely.
When my brother ran away from home and I thought it was because á of my continously scolding him.
When I saw that I had passed the university entrance exam.  It á made me forget all my problems.
When I was ten I got shut in the school with a friend.  I had to á jump out of a window and cross a beam 10 metres high.
When I was told that a boy did not want to be my friend without á any apparent reason.
When I learnt that a boy I liked had been with a girl for three á years.
When a very dirty class-mate farted in my  presence.  There was a á terrible smell.
When I realized that I had a hole in my trousers after having gone á for a walk.
When I had an argument with my grandfather the day my younger á brother was born.
When I saw my 16 year old sister at home after having waited for á her all night, not knowing where she was.
While I was waiting for them to give me the marks of the most á difficult subject this year.
I had an argument with my mother because I criticized the rules á she imposes at home, which are too rigid and arbitrary for me.
When I learned that a friend of mine had not been speaking to her á boyfriend for a week after an argument because of unfounded á jealousy.
On seeing a scene of an accident in a magazine.
A few days back I had to ask a professor a ridiculous question á because I had lost at a game of cards and had to pay a forfeit.
When I shouted at my mother when she was nervous and depressed.
After several days delay in my girlfriend's menstration I was á very glad to see that the pregnancy test was negative.
I felt angry when I saw on T.V the last slaughter of negroes in á South Africa.
When I saw the pictures of the draught in Etiopia.
Whenever I see an alcoholic.
On New Year's Eve, when I went to the house of my girlfriend's á parents to meet them.
When I failed an exam for which I knew that I had not studied á hard enough.
The day the Real Madrid team of basket ball qualified for the á final at Athens.
The last time I was face to face with with the monstrous dog á which lives in my street.
During a trivial (friendly) discussion, one of the participants á made an intervention which made me feel uncomfortable.
When I heard the last regulation of the socialist govrenment á concerning pensions.
When I got to know the details if the famine in East Africa.
The last time I had to phone the Registry, after having called á them so many times in the last few days.
When my parents got divorced.
When I was a child, one day while playing, I fell up to my waist á in mud.
When I was dismissed from a job after having been accused of theft.
When I was with a girl who seemed to love me, while I was with á her just to go to bed with her.
When I passed an exam which I had failed last year.
When I go out alone at night.
A murder.
When I failed two subjects last year.
When I see people who have no sentiments.
I think that I am rather shy and do not mix with people as I á would have liked to, out of shyness.
When I triffled with other people.
When I was told that I could take a week off and go for a trip á with my friends.
Every time I went home with my school report.

During an argument between friends, one of them accused me of á taking advantage of some other friends who usually come to the á university in my car, saying that I ask them too much money for á the petrol.
When I learned that two of my friends had had a serious car accident.
A young man was insulting and humiliating a drunken man.
My aunt phoned me to ask me why I had refused the her invitation á to dinner at her home on the New Year's Eve.
I was with a girl one night and then did not call her again, á although she had asked me to do so.
When I saw that I had passed an exam.  It was the last chance and á there was a lot at stake.
On a trip to Santander we wanted to stop at a curve because a á friend was sick, and the car skidded of the gravel.
My cousins were playing at home and one of them broke a decorative á object which was very precious to me.
All my friends arranged to go for an afternoon snack and they did á not tell me.  They told me that they did not have my phone number á but I do not think that this was true.
When I saw a film where a black was rapeing a girl while another one was á filming it for a pornographic movie.
I was swimming in the sea and a wave took the top part of my á bikini away.
I was looking after a child and she fell down because I was not á paying her much attention.  One side of her face got bruised.
When I pass exams, or when a close friend of mine recovered á from an illness,etc.
Fights that I see in the middle of the street, robberies, fear of á darkness when going home.
During a family discussion on my future and my prospects as a á student, they accused me of not bothering about looking for a job to á assume my financial situation.
[ Depressions.]
Some people whom I do not like at all, and one of the reasons is á their physical appearance.
For example, to feel bad because of one's attire, to be among á people who do not belong to the same social class, to give a á wrong answer in class, to be surprised in particular situations.
Some of my friends had an argument.  I had earlier phoned one á of them and that may have influenced him to argue.
When I met a very close friend of mine after one year of á separation.
There was an earthquake for several minutes and I was on the á eight floor.
An argument among several friends because of the irrational á behavior of one of them who fell out with us for no reason and á said that we were to blame.
A class-mate died after being two months in coma, after a car á accident.
Pictures of Nazi extermination camps on a T.V program.
Equivocal situation when filling a security questionnaire on á entering a government building with several people there.
I left a boy with whom I was going around without giving him any á explanations.
When my sister was born.
When they tried to rob me.
When I failed an exam unfairly.
When my grandmother died.
When I see dead dogs on the road.
When I went to see the doctor and had to take my clothes off so á that he could examine me.
When my parents quarelled over something I had done and which was á wrong.
When my little sister was born.
When I was attending an authorized demonstrationand the police á rushed brutally at the demonstrators, without any warning.
When a professor of this faculty laughed at, and was suspicious of á a composition written by a class-mate and me.
The death of a relative, friend, or someone I esteem.
When I saw a very disagreable scene.
When I had to represent my boss at a meeting.
When I inadvertantly made some close friends and relatives feel á bad.
When I passed an exam.
When they threatened me with a knife to take my money.
When I failed an exam I thought I would pass.
When my dog died.
When I saw an accident where the man lost his head.
When I tripped while getting on a bus.
When I hurt a person's feelings.
I had not seen my brother for five years as he was not in Spain.   á When he arrived at the airport, I felt great joy.
When two drug addicts tried to take away my money.
When I saw my brother being attacked and I could not do anything.
When a class-mate died.
When a person saw that I was accused of something I had not done á and did not do anything to defend me.
When inadvertantly I found myself in the ladies room.
When I broke something and a friend of mine was blamed.
I got my driving licence after they had frightened me with it's á difficulty.
When I had to walk over three kms through a field which had wild bulls, á because my car had broken down.
When I saw a man hitting a child of 2 years without any consideration, á simply because the child had been leaning against a window.
A friend of mine who was driving a car ahead of me died in a á car accident.
When I had to dissect a live mouse at school.
When I was a child I had to recite a poem in a show at the end of á the term.
When I saw a program on Ethiopia on T.V, a fews hours earlier I á had thrown away some clothes and food.
When I saw that the mark I had obtained in an exam was a good á one.
We were in the country and I walked away from the others one á night.  Suddenly something moved sharply in front of me and I was á not able to see what it was.
When I was young, I became very angry as I was not allowed to á stay up all night for the fair in my town.
When summer is over and I have to leave the town where I spend my á holidays.
When I saw several people washing their car with water from a á drain.
When I inadvertantly entered the ladies room and met some girls á on my way out.
I was entrusted with an object and while using it I handled it á carelessly and it broke.
When I learned, after the ecography, that my mother was expecting a á baby girl.  That was what I wanted.
One night, walking along a park, I began to think that some á roughnecks would appear suddenly with knives and things like á that.
I had an exam and I had it well prepared.  I did the first part á very well but did not know the second part.
When my parents did not let me go on a study tour.
One day I was going through the street door of my house, when a á man asked me for a doctor.  He then showed me his genitals and á asked me to cure him myself.
Each time the professor asks me a question in class.
I had an argument with my boyfriend.  It was my fault but my á pride would not let me admit it.
An invitation to spend 5 days at the seaside with all expenses á paid.
A film on zombies.
When males in my family try to assign house duties exclusively á with referance to sex.
I had a quarrell with my boyfriend and decided to finish with him á and and my Easter holidays.
When after a storm in the country, I left my shelter and saw a á big, fat, slimy green toad by my side.
When a friend from whom I preferred to hide my private life á discovered that I had relations with a man.
When my brother had to spend all evening repairing a gear-lever á that I had broken.
When I passed the university entrance exam.
When I was walking down the street, some boys showed me a knife á and stole all my money.
When they threw my holder down on the floor, with all my notes for á an exam inside it and they got all mixed up.
When my mother was operated.
When I see pornographic films.
One day I got on the bus without any money or season ticket and á the driver threw me out.
When a friend of mine was beaten for what was my fault.
My father had an operation which lasted for hours.  We were all á very worried but it was successful.
I was walking along a subway when I saw a group of louts.  I was á rather afraid because I was alone.
An old woman was violently thrown down the stairs of the tube by á a group of louts.
A child, 9 years old, died in a stupid way.  He fell from a place á which was 1 metre high.
On the road there was a dead animal with its entrails showing and á its skull crushed.
We were discussing a subject ( I knew very little about it) and I á was holding my ground.  They showed me that I was wrong.
I could have passed the last exam of the public competition, but á I failed as I had not studied.
I was studying in the library and a class-mate told me that she á had obtained a grant to work in the library.
Before knowing my marks I was not sure that I wanted to go to á that class.
I learned that a class-mate had given a list, of peolpe who help á each other in exams, to the professor.
I phoned two friends and was not able to arrange a meeting with á either of them, so I had to change my plans.
I was in the cafeteria at the university and a class-mate told me á that a friend of hers had had all her teeth taken out because of á an infection caused by her eating a rat's nail in her hamburger.
I had to meet a girlfriend to go out for a drink and she arrived á with her aunt, to whom I was introduced.  Then the aunt left.
One night, after having decided to finish our relationship, I á took my girlfriend home.  While driving back home, I felt that I á had not handled the whole thing very well.
The begining of my relations with my current girlfriend.
When I am alone at night after having read horror stories, and á then I heard unexplainable noises.
A typical family argument.
The disqualification of two of my mates in the military service.
The sight of vomit on the street.
When criticizing something about a person and then realizing that á the person whom one is talking to is similar.
Not to have studied enough when exams were near.
When I pass an exam.
Continous fear of a nuclear war.
When you kill yourself with work and see the number of slakers á wandering around, doing nothing.
When someone in my family died.
To loose friends because of them over-estimating themselves.
When people next to me play the fool.
To force someone to do something that suits me.

I thought that I was going to fail a subject and so I began to á study for the final exam, then my friend told me that I had á passed it.  That meant that I could go home, as I do not study in á my hometown.
I was in Sierra Nevada, climbing a peak over 3,000 metres high, á without any light and with many other problems.  I was afraid for á my life.
I was living in a flat where things did not go very well for me.  á Finally, they threw me out and this prejudiced people I esteem a á lot.
When I read the diary of the girl with whom I was living, it was á about another boy with whom she had been going around some time back.
The man who threw me out of the flat disgusted me.
The first time that I caressed a girl, I was about thirteen and á she was eighteen.  I noticed that it did not affect her at all.
I was going around with a girl without loving her.  Not only did á I go around with her, but we did many more things.  In the end I á was not very sincere to her.
I met a girlfriend again after not seeing her for several months. á  I saw her in a discotheque.  We do not like discotheques but we á went there because we knew we would meet there.
I was walking in the countryside alone when I came across two á dogs who began barking at me.  I did not know whether they were á tied up or loose, but I was afraid of them approaching me.

I was angry when my sister began to talk nonsense and to laugh at á the way I swept the room.  My anger grew (I tried to control á myself).  After telling her to leave me alone, I vented my anger á on her as she did not obey me.
My mother was working with a knife and we were all laughing á heartily.  She was not able to control the knife and stuck it á deep into her hand.
I read a book whose plot and expressions were obscene and in very á bad taste.
My mother had just been teaching me how to crochet, which is á thought highly improper for a boy in a town.  Just when we á finished, a neighbour walked in.

It was about midnight and I wanted to go to the countryside (I á was in town) to watch the stars in the sky.  My mother did not á like this, in spite of it I went out for a while.  My mother got á angry.
A friend of mine suggested that I become a film extra.  The idea á seemed very funny to me and my reaction seemed rather outlandish á to the others.
One day I went to the cinema to see a film in which I was á interested.  On arriving there I saw a long queue (which I had á not expected) and went back home without seeing the film.
When I miss the train and I am late, and I have to wait half an á hour for the next one.
When I knew I had to go out with my mother on some errands.
I saw in an ice-cream kiosque a cockroach walking through a á cornet.
One day in class, the professor asked me a question concerning something á he had been explaining.  He was very close to me (beside me) and I á had no idea what to answer.
Once I had some homework to do and I did not do it.
When they phoned me from Great-Britain to tell me that I could go á there, if I wished, in Summer.
When I was operated on the knee and had to go through rehabilitation.
In a very important basket-ball match where a lot was at stake, I á played very badly.
When a friend of mine told me that he was going to commit á suicide.
A TV program on whale-hunting.
Once when I said bad things concerning a friend.
Family discord and uneasiness due to something I did not á communicate on time.
When I passed my driving test, as it was the fifth time that I á had taken this test.
When my mother was robbed in a shop.
I was given an exam which I thought did not measure at all my á ability or my knowledge of the subject.
Some friends and I were having lunch.  Someone said something á funny and one of the guys started laughing and spat his food in a girl's á face.
I was alone in the bus when I tripped and fell, and dropped all á my papers.
As I was not paying attention, my little brother fell off the á table.
When I passed the university entrance exam.
One night, while I was sleeping, I woke up suddenly with the á sensation that there was someone in my room.
When my brother was held up and robbed.
When they told me that my grandfather was rather ill.
When I see someone vomitting.
When I fell head on in a fountain.
I had to undergo an operation in Summer and so my family had to á stay at home during the holidays.  I felt guilty, above all á because of my brothers.
I came across a friend with whom I had lost touch for a long á time.

I had decided to propose to the man I liked to make a trip á together.  One day, during breakfast I told him my idea.  I was á afraid of his not accepting it and that the idea would end up as á a failure.
A person I trusted a lot gave me many false explanations to á justify a wrong action.
I was having breakfast with a classmate and suddenly I began to á cry as I thought of a friend of mine whom I had not seen for a á long time.

During lunch with some classmates, a priest was also there.  He á was eating desperately as if someone was going to take his plate á away.  He did it with gluttony.  He wiped his hands on his suit á several times and it was full of crumbs.
When a professor caught me absent-minded and not paying attention á to what he was saying.
One day, I was alone on duty when a patient choked while eating.  á I ran to her and tried to make her breath, but it was too late.
At a party, on New Year's Eve, I met on old friend whom I had not á seen for some time
Once I failed seven subjects at school and I was terrified to á give my report card to my father.  I left it on the table and went to á bed very early in order to avoid him seeing me.
When, after drinking a glass of water, I found a cockroach walking á out of the glass.

I have a very close friend who lives in another city and we have á been writing to each other for a long time.  The last time I went á to her city, just to see her, I was disappointed to see how great á the distance between us was.
They asked me to throw the rubbish into a dustbin which had some á awful liquid accumulated at the bottom.

The girl with whom I was going around had been forbidden to be á alone with me in the house.  We paid no attention to this á prohibition but one day her parents appeared and I jumped out of á the window.  They saw me.
I was driving a friend's car, and I got close to the pavement to á ask my way and I struck a parked car.
Every time, in the last few days, when my girlfriend told me that á she loves me.
I stayed alone in the dark at night in the mountain, waiting for á my uncle.  I remember that I took a big stone and it calmed me.

We were at school, in the room for audiovisual classes.  We were á watching a film, and just behind me two classmates were bothering á me with their mocking and shoves.  I reacted angrily (I suppose)  á by hitting one of them.
[ During a summer holiday a French girl and I had becoe back á home, I felt very sad.]
Once I had to clean a lavatory which was obstructed.  It was in a á friend's country house and there was nobody there to help me.
In a Mathematics class, the professor asked me a question and I á gave the wrong answer.
When I lost my study grant without having attended any exam in á the career I had started, and it was too late to cancel my registration.
A party I went to last Christmas.
When my mother had a nervous illness.
During my last exam.
When I had to come back from my village last Christmas.
One day I went to see a rather disagreeable film (X).
Once I had to visit a rather special person.
Once, I accidentally injured a boy in the eye and he almost lost á it.
When I knew the feelings of a beloved person.
A fall during a climb, with almost with no previous experience.
On the occasion of assignment of tasks and responsibilities in á which such an assignment, dispropotionately carried with it high á responsibility and low ability of organisation and resolution.
Moving to an unknown place, away from the familiar surroundings á and into a situation of loneliness.
When I had to sleep in a bed at a hostel, which was full of dirt.
While shopping, a person close to us created an uncomfortable á situation for those who were with her.
Incomprehension and repression towards a child's behaviour, á commonly not accepted, and making the child cry.
In a dark street at 4 o'clock in the night and there was á complete silence.
When they broke the artistic work of several weeks.  Changes were á made and it was broken without permission, they had no right to á do this.
When the train taking me to my military service left the station, á on the platform remained relatives, projects and goodtimes.  I á had a hard year ahead.
A situation of overt unfairness, manipulation of people and its á consequences.
A children's film in which I played a clown, with spotlights, á cameras and the director who demanded jumps and guffaws.
When a close classmate failed a year.
I was talking to a friend and he said something which was very á funny.
When I was young I saw a horror film.  Then when I went to sleep, á the film came back too my mind and the characters frighteneed my á imagination.
In a confrontation with a person, he provoked me several times á till I reacted in an angry way.  Fortunately there were no á disastrous consequences.
I was watching a sad film and it affected me deeply.
When I was reading a book.  It had nothing to do with the book á itself but with the disagreable smell of the pages of the book.
In class I had to say something aloud and people reacted  by á laughing.
In an exam I answered the questions rather carelessly and á afterwards I thought that the exam would have been better had I á answered more carefully.
When I knew that there were, at last, no problems in making a á journey that I had been wanting to make for a long time.
It was more that fear - anguish -that I felt before my last exam.
When I had an argument with my best friend and I thought that I á was right and she was not.
When I realized that it was impossible for me to be as free as I á had imagined and that I could not do anythong about it.
The first time I saw a pornographic film, all that in practice is á so beautiful but on the screen appered as something mechanical, á irrational, disgusting and dehumanizing.
When I stated sharply something I was not very sure of and a few á days later I was shown to be wrong.
When I do or say something inappropriate which hurts people close á to me.
When a study tour got confirmed, I was happy all the time till    á the tour began.
I was walking down a road and suddenly a few dogs appeared at a fence á and started barking angrily.  They were jumping and it seemed á that they would come for me any time.
When I knew that they would not give me a transfer from one á university to another.  I began to insult the educatioon á authorities and the government, I ended up at the door.
We went to visit my mother at the residence.  She was crying and á said that she was about to die.  I believed all her complaints á and continously thought of the possibility of loosing her.
My dog had been run over and died near the house.  We had to pick á him up, cold and glassy eyed, to get rid of the corpse.
A professor was going to read aloud in class a composition of á mine in which I had criticized some political attitudes and also á some class-mates.   I was ashamed at having written that.
In an exam when I answered the questions with very little á assurance due to insufficiet preparation.
When I received my report card in C.O.U.  I was afraid of obtaining á low marks, but they were much higher than expected.
I was at the cinema with my sister and her boyfriend.  A man á sitting beside me started to stroke my leg for a while, he left in á the middle of the film.
My father began to say incoherant things concerning my brother's and á my own behaviour towards him.  His biased (authoritarian) and á ridiculous point of view made us angry.
I had failed some subjects in mathematics.
I was at the table at a French friend's house.  They served me a á big dish with roast cauliflower and sauce.  I had to eat it.

This morning I spent a lot of time on my toilet and missed the á train to the university.  My mother told me that I spent more á time than a woman on my toilet.  I felt a mixed emotion of shame á and anger.
I was alone at home when I broke a figure and then mended it.  A á few days later my mother noticed it and asked me about it, I told á her that I had no idea.
When I fell crazily in love with a beautiful girl and she returned á my love.
When I was caught by the police and was kept with a group of á delinquents, which added to my fear of being shut up.  I was á afraid of the people near me and the future consequences.
When I was the target of a great many insults and completely á unfair accusations of a large group of people.
When my best friend died, at the age of 16.
When I entered a brothel and saw two sailors with a young á prostitute who was not older than 18.
When I was in a religious school my teacher showed me up in front á of all my class-mates.  They were very sarcastic and cruel.
Having suffered a not very pretty sight, I reacted by uttering á some very cruel and sharp words.
When I came across an old friend whom I had not seen for a very á long time.
I had an accident in which I hurt my eye.  I was afraid of having á injured it badly.
When I was accused of something I had not done.
A close friend died.
I saw some images of a decapitation in a horror film.
I slipped and fell in to a puddle and people started looking at á me.
I made another person cry for an unjustified cause.
I received an unexpected letter from a friend I had met a short á time before.  He sent me a poem and wished me good luck.  I felt á very happy because I had great esteem for that person.
A certain person started to say dreadful things very calmly, I á felt hurt and disgusted.
A certain person whom I respect and esteem a lot pays me no á attention.  She keeps up appearances but shows almost no interest á in me.
In a bus I fell sick and vomitted in a bag.  The entire situation á was disgusting in itself.
A person (a male) told me that he liked me.  He has a problem, he á is a homosexual.
I rejected a person whom I had always thought to be a friend.  I á told him so and he reacted angrily.  I felt guilty at not having á realized it before and at having hurt him.
When I received some good news : I obtained an amount of money I á needed to buy something I had been planning to buy.
When my relatives and I were in a car going slowly on a frozen á road.
My parents were having a typical family argument.  I came in and á saw the scene and became angry.
I was going away, leaving a dear person behind.
I visited a place in Morocco where they worked the leather.  I á saw the skins emerged in a liquid which ressembled putrification.
At a friend's party there were several allusions to my sexual adventures.
I was in a cafe with another person when, suddenly, several close á friends of my partner appeared.  I did not know what to do and my á partner felt uncomfortable.
When I talk to my friends.
When I am walking on the streets and see a gang of thugs.
When people harrass me I feel oppressed by their behavior.
When I am with a friend and we have to leave each other.
When I saw a film in which the man suffered from an illness and    á his skin came peeling off.
When I was in the toilet and someone came in.
[ When I act thinking that I know everything and I then realize á that there were things I had not thought about, thus hurting á others.]
[ Any situation in everyday life has this emotional sense, in á class, in the street, at home, at the table..........]
On a dark night I felt that there were several people near me á and I did not know who they were.
When I learned that several people had died in the street due to  á the cold weather.
When I saw in the newspapers, on the T.V, and magazines the á chaotic situation caused by the drought and hunger in á Mauritania.
The physical appearance of a meal.
I was with a group of people and everybody told me to do or say á something.  It was a confusing, strong and traumatic situation á for me.
In a situation with my girlfriend I took a decision.  Later when á I thought about it, I realized that it was an erroneous decision.
One night, at a friend's place I realized that I had everything I á most wished, around me.
During a demonstration I climbed up the closed central door of a á bus.  When the bus stopped I had to go back to the same place, á afraid that the police would see me.
When I saw parents punishing their little child for something he á had not done.  In my opinion, even if he had done it he should á not have been punished for it.
A friend of mine was hurt as he thought that our relationship was á not the same as before and something had gone wrong.
When I was young, one day in the car we fell sick and ended up á vomitting on each other.
The parents of a friend of mine surprised us and another couple á sleeping in thier place.
A friend of mine felt bad because of something I had done to á something that belonged to him.
When they told me that I had been admitted to the faculty of á medicine.
Almost always when I go to fetch the results of an exam.
[ No description.]
When I decided not to out any longer with a girl whom I liked á quite a lot.  This made me feel low for a some time.
I saw a program on T.V where they had to saw a skull for an        á operation.
I was watching T.V with my parents and some pornographic scenes á came on, I felt uncomfortable and tried to distract my parents á attention by talking to them.
When I used an adjective for a person without knowing what it á meant.   When I got to know the meaning, I felt guilty as it was á a clear and unfair insult.
When I obtained good marks in a subject I had failed before.
When a friend of mine told me a horror story.
I was with my family and we found some abandoned puppies.  I á wanted to help them but everyone said no.  We then left.
At my grandfather's death.
Seeing a film in which there were several bloody crimes.
At a concert an old man arrived and began to danse, sing and do á silly things.
I had an argument with a friend of mine.  She would not let me á speak and then I began to shout at her.  She got angry and left, á I did not try to prevent her from leaving.
When I was told that they had got tickets for me for a film á marathon I wanted to see.
We were on the road in a car when a lorry bypassed us.  We had to á swerve and we almost got run over.

I had applied for a job and they had assured me that the exams á would take place a few months later.  A week later I went to á obtain some more information and they told me that the exams had á already taken place.
I received a letter from some friends, who do not live in Madrid, á telling me that they would not come on holiday.  I had arranged á everythiing for them.
I found a big, black spider near a bag of food.
I was in a very small class and the professor said something á about me that made everyone look at me at the same time.
I had arranged to meet my friends at a certain place, and I was á with other people.  My friends did not arrive and the people who á were with me began to get tired.  My friends were one hour late.
The man I am going around with gave me a very special present.
I thought that I would be scolded for a comment I had made, which á I should not have made.
My sister came back home and reproached me for not having tidied á up the house, although I had been working all morning and she had á done nothing.
At my grandfather's funeral.  I remembered that the thing he á liked and respected most was earth, I thought that he had á attained what he wanted and was not separated from it any longer.
I had to wash my grandmother because she did not get to the á bathroom on time.
In a very crowded shop I was distracted and missed my turn in the á queue.  A woman who was behind me began to shout at me asking me á either to pay more attention or to leave.
When I was very young, one day, I kicked my grandmother and á caused her an injury which took a long time to heal.
When I saw a friend of mine, whom I had not seen for a long time á and I had lost his address and telephone number.
I was in my village when a bull jumped over a fence and started á chasing my friends and me.  We were very frightened till we á climbed up a tree.
When I saw a car run over a child, out of carelessness.
I failed a subject despite the fact that I had studied quite a á lot for it.
When I was walking in a field which had a lot of manure.
I liked a boy and I would feel shy and then blush.  The more I á wanted to avoid it the more I blushed.
I am not very affectionate and I feel guilty as I do not give as á much affection as I receive.

I was spending the week-end with some friends.  We were waiting á for another friend and we went to the meet him at the bus stop, a  á woman we met there told us that the coach had already left.  I á was afraid that I would not see my friend, but at last we found á him.

I was walking down a little village at night.  There was nobody á in the steet.  A dog began to bark, I felt that it was following á me.  Then I began to run, the other dogs started barking too.  At á last I arrived home.
My parents did not let me go on holidays with my friends.
I was told that a friend of mine was going to Mexico for good.
Finding a hair in the soup.

I was at the University dining room, alone, and at a table next á to mine thre were several professors.  One of them asked me to á join them.  I refused but she insisted.  All the others started á looking at me and I had to move to their table.
I had promised to say goodbye to a person who was going on a á trip, and I did not turn up.
I was on holidays, and I was going to meet a friend whom I had á not seen for six months.  Again I felt very happy.
We were camping in the mountains, and a friend and I went for a á walk.  It was getting darker and darker and we were not sure of á the right way back.
I sent a book to a friend of mine.  The book meant a lot to me á and he lost it.
To say goodbye to dear friends after the holidays.
Ever since I have been a child, the sight of any kind of wound.
At the seaside, when a wave suddenly came and took off my bikini.

One night, I went out with some friends for dinner and I did not á tell my parents that I would come back late.  I thought of á phoning but in the end I did not.  When I arrived home, my á parents were very worried.
My sister in law was about to have a child, and there were some á problems.  They had to do a Caesarean.  After a while, everything  á was all right.
Waiting for my marks in a difficult subject.
I gave some personal information to a friend of mine, and he told á it to some others who were implicated in the affair.
The holidays come to an end, and the next day we had to go back á to University and to the exams.
There was a cat on the street.  It had been run over and its head was á open.  We passed beside it.
At a meeting with over one hundred people, they decided who had to speak á from the stand by drawing lots.
I had a small argument with a relative and some other people got á implicated.  It resulted in a proper row.
Last course, when I passed with good marks three subjects which I had á previously failed.
I was attacked by a man at a bus stop at night.
My mother told me that I could not go to the mountains.  Despite á my age, as long as I am in her house I must do what she says.
When my nephew was taken to hospital with meningitis and we did á not know what would happen.
I was drinking coffee in a cafe and I found a piece of scrubber á in my cup.
When I went to my boyfriend's house for lunch and saw his á parents, I felt that they were watching me all the time.
At school, I did not tell the teacher that it was me who á had laughed, and she punished the entire class by making them á stay behind for one hour.
One evening, I was with a group of friends having a talk.  There á was a very trustful and joyful atmosphere.
We were walking in the park at night.  It was very dark and very á late.  We began to hear foot steps all around us, and we could á not find our way out.
[ One day I arrived home rather tired and found the house..... In á addition I was asked many questions which I did not want to á answer.]
I was selected to do a rest for a foreign ballet but I did not á have the money to do it.
In a film there was a scene in which a rat was sliding on a bed, á leaving a trace of blood behind, finally it entered the mouth of á one of the actors.
I was swimming in the river and I lost the top of my bikini.  I á did not notice it and came out of water.  There was a á disagreeable classmate watching the scene.
At a party, several comments were made about the personal á situation of one of the people present.  She was rather affected á and uncomfortable.
It was Saturday, my duties were over for a few hours and I could á at last be with the people I wanted to see.
One night, I was alone at home.  My fear was caused by some á strange noises which put my imagination to work.
When I got to know about the reaction of a friend of mine in a á certain situation.  I had not expected him to react that way.
I felt alone among a large number of people.  I was sad to see á that nobody cared about what was happening to me.
I saw a sort of black worm being attacked by many ants.
When I met a friend of mine after several months.
When I noticed the negative changes in a friend's behaviour.
I was going to my village, after having been rather oppressed in á Madrid.
I was watching a procession during the Holy week, and a penitent á approached me.
My mother read a letter that a friend of mine had written to me á telling me how she had got drunk the last time.
[ No response.]
I found a cockroach crushed between two folders in my bedroom, I á called my mother.
I ride my motorbike in my village and everyone stares at me as if á I was a rare specimen.
I was spending a few days at my aunt's place.  One night I got á home very late, I had told them I was going to a party but I went á to another place.  They were very worried.
Last Summer I achieved someting that I had been wanting for a á long time.
I was in a camp and went out for a walk at night on my own.  I lost  á my way and spent several hours looking for the camp.
My parents scolded me a lot for something I had not done.  It was á my sister who had done it.
[ No response.]
At the hypocrisy of some of my friends.
I greeted and embraced the wrong person thinking that it was my á friend.
Due to a misunderstanding on my part, two of my best friends á quarelled.
When my brother was born, everything went all right.  It had been á very likely that he would have a deficiency (my sister suffers á from Down's Syndrome) and that my mother would be in danger.
When we got lost in Florence and the coach did not turn up until á midnight.  I had no place to go to and there were strange reports á at the police station.
When an English teacher unfairly made me repeat a semester which á I thought I had passed.  I had to ask my parents for some more á money to carry on studying.
The person whom I liked most left me for a friend of mine, after á several months of mutual help and a profound knowledge of each á other.
In a park near our home, a group of young people who were á strangely dressed were seated in the middle of the street.  They á began to eat while carressing each other.
I feel this emotion very often when I try to express my feelings á in public, because other people do not understand my reactions á and think that I am silly.
A friend of mine said in a group that she felt lonely and á withdrawn from everyone because of mental deficiency.
When I passed the university entrance exam.  I had thus finished á with a difficult period of my life and I was about to begin one á which I had desired a lot.
When I was at home alone, I felt a super-natural force, dangerous á for me and the people close to me.
When my father made my mother go through really terrible á situations, I felt furious, impotent, nervous, upset, ........
When a person whom I loved and admired a lot died.  I felt empty, á lonely, helpless, without support, not knowing what to do.
When I came to know that my father and his parents were : self á interested, dirty, negative, egoist, bad peolpe,......
I think that the only time I really felt shame was when I was á very young and I had to defecate on the street.  I was very á worried in case someone should see me.
When I was young I felt guilty because I thought that I had á commited a grave sin.
On my birthday, when I was given my presents.
We were riding in a friend's car.  He was driving very fast and á suddenly a another car crossed the road in front of us.  My á friend had to turn the car rapidly.
When I found one of my new pullovers wrinkled inside the á wardrobe.  My brother had done it.
When I went to see the result of an exam and saw that I had á failed.
When I was getting up, I found a live cockroach in my bedroom.
The mother of a friend of mine passed by me and saw me sitting á on a boy's lap.  I tried to greet her but could not help á blushing.
A friend of mine had the sleeves of a leather coat stolen from á his car.  It was me who had left them there for everyone to see.

The final marks were to be given in the morning.  I wanted to get á there late because I was very afraid.  When I arrived there, á everybody was very happy and I had also passed.  We had a á wonderful time all day long.
I went to visit a friend in hospital.  He was going to be á operated the next day.  I was afraid that they would not let me á in and I did not know what his reaction would be on seeing me.
A friend of mine played a joke on another friend over the á telephone.  This friend, crying, called me and I got very angry á and made the other person apologize.

A friend of mine told me that my boyfriend had been with another á girl this Summer.  We had been going out together for four years á and we had not done so for the last three months.  I could not á believe it.
I was at a friend's place for lunch and she fell ill and á vomited.
I was dancing in a theatre.  I was not sure whether some frieends á of mine had come to see me.  I was very scared of doing things á wrong.
Classes were over and I wanted to go home.  A friend of mine á asked me to wait for half an hour to take him back home.  I said á no.
On holiday, seeing the lanscape in Gerona.
Travelling by coach on a rather narrow and wet road.
They wanted me to pay for a ticket twice because they said that á the one I had was out of date.
When I came back from my holidays.
When I saw an insect going up my arm.
When I entered a bar looking for a friend.
Arguing with my younger cousin.  She is rather a nuisance but I á felt sorry.
When some friends of mine asked me to go camping with them for a á fortnight.
Once, when I was very young, my mother left me alone in the á house and came back very late.
When my aunt told me angrily that I was a good-for-nothing and á she was fed up with my behaviour.
When my parents and sister went on a trip and I was separated á from them for about three months.
When a person I did not know hurt a friend of mine.
When the literature teacher made me recite a poem in the middle á of the class and I had to gesticulate.
Once, when I arrived home very late, my parents had an argument á because of this; my mother wanted to stand up for me.
I phoned a friend of mine to ask her for news about the marks in á an exam.  She told me that I had passed.

I was spending my summer holidays in a village.  My friend and I á were coming back from a discotheque at night and we heard a noise á from an alley.  We were very scared and we got into my friend's house. á  A moment later, an unknown car picked up a person from this á alley.
My mother and I had an argument over buying some clothes for me.  á She did not accept the fact that I did not like the same things á as her, and we ended up shouting at each other.
One day, I was home and there was a phone call informing me that á some of my relatives had died in an accident.
When I saw a film in which there was a scene where women were cut á to pieces.  Above all, it was the blood and the confusion which á impressed me most.
I was walking to school and I passed by a red cross post where á there were many soldiers.  They began to pass remarks at me.
A friend of mine trusted me to back her in a decision she had á made.  But when the moment came I did not agree with her opinion.
I was told that I had passed the statistics exam.  I had not á expected this so I was very happy.
When my brother hit his head and lost consciousness at the sports á practice.  For some time he could not remember what had happened á but he recovered later.
I get angry with my brothers and sisters when they do something á that I do not like.  They know this and still do it so as to á tease me.
When my grandfather died.
When opened a box of biscuits and found worms inside.
When I was young I was told to to the shop to buy a dozen eggs.  á I went and asked for one egg and the people in the shop laughed á at me and so did my family when I told them what had happened.
When I arrived home late at night.  I know that my mother gets á worried and this made me feel angry.
When I spoke to my daughter and wished her luck for the á examinations she was about to take.
When I was told that my daughter, who is at a boarding school, á was very ill and that they needed me there the same day.
One day in a clinic, the father of a child came in and assaulted á a colleague for something that she had not done deliberately.
When I was told that my uncle had passed away.
The transport to pick us up for lunch was always late and the á driver made the same excuse every day.
One day when I came back home, I found my favourite dish broken.  á I blamed the servant for it, later I found out that it was not á the servant but my daughter who had broken it.
When I did not give back a text book to a friend in time.
When a cousin of mine was discharged from the hospital after       á a long illness.  I had thought that this illness would never end.
When a man who had a knife grabbed me and threatened me with it,   á during my holidays in Monze.á
A certain friend tried to push me off a seat in a very violent á way for no apparent reason.  It may be that he was excited about á something.
When the neighbour of a friend of mine was stabbed to death by á thieves in Kabwe.  They stole his van.
When we were young, a friend of mine tried to dissect a frog while  á we were playing near his home.
The time I shouted at most of my friends at a party.  It was as if á  all my friends had done something wrong, or may be it was the á influence of the beer.
When I blamed my niece for misplacing my book, she denied having á touched or seen it but I carried on insisting that it was her.
After going through much shame, I became a Christian and á something new happened in my heart.  Joy that overflows was á manifest in me.
When I was about six years old, I mistook a cat for a leopard      á when it entered my room at night.
When I lost my father on the 25th of September,1970.  He died of á a sore on the leg.
When I failed the grade 7 twice and only passed it the third á time.
I was going around with a foreigner's wife and my entire family á got to know about it, this was just when I had become a á Christian.
When they found out that I was absent from school, I had gone to á the girl's secondary school.
When I first passed a job interview.
I was almost caught in the girls hostel by the security men, I á would have been expelled from school had I been caught.
When I was accused of having refused to do some hostel work while á I was at school.  Actually I had not been allocated any work.
A friend of mine could not make it back to Unza after having á failed the exams.
I usually come back home early but this day I came home back late á to find some visitors at my place.
