I got pass marks in the H.S.S compulsory courses while most á people performed well.
I destroyed my step-brother's bedsheets by mistake, they were the á only ones he had.
When I heard that I had made it to the second year at UNZA.
When my father's home was to be broken into by thieves who had á guns.
When a friend tried to back bite me on false grounds.  This made á me wonder if he was a really a good friend.
When my girlfriend's nephew passed away.
When someone whom I trusted, disappointed me terribly.
I was with my colleagues and we met an elderly man who was very á drunk, as he approached us he started to undress.
When I lied to my mum, who later came to know that what I had á been teling her was false.
When I hooked a girl in Kitwe.  She was very beautiful for my á standards, a rare bird of this kind accepted me as a boyfriend.
When someone tried to bewitch me and my friends at night.

When I was victimized for running away with a girl who was á somebody else's wife and niece at the same time.  I was very á angry over this issue because I was told to pay him money after á having been punished for it.
1976, Soweto uprising in South Africa and the racist Gout's á reaction to the students demands concerning the educational á system.
When I was found urinating, behind a toilet instead of inside it, á by my class mates and the teachers.  I was told to pick up my own á urine from the wet soil, I did it.
When my uncle found me having sexual intercourse with a distant á relative of mine in the sitting room, on the couch.  I failed to á stop and get up, I carried on.
When I was accepted for further education, here at the á university.
When I was walking at night, I saw fire suspended in the air and á it was split into several segments by something I could not see.  á I suspected that it was witch-craft.
When I was accused by my brother of having stolen a 5 kwatcha á note from my mother's bag.  I was beaten up for this, the money á was found later.
When I received a message that my brother was seriously ill and á was in hospital.
When I was refused a transfer from my school to another, simply á because it was far away from my house.
When I was taking an exam in grade 5.  The examinator found me á with a note-book and accused me of copying, All the students á laughed at me.
When I was caught stealing mangoes in a certain compound.
When I got first division in the exams before leaving school.
When I went to town in a double dekker bus.  The bus was about to á fall on the way when the driver controlled it.  It had almost á fallen.
When I was in form 3, my aunts lied to my daddy telling him that á I had told them that I was pregnant.  My daddy  told my mother á and she asked me if it was true.  I was very angry with my aunts.
When I received a letter telling me that my mother was very ill.
When a drunkard, in town yelled at me saying that I was a á prostitute.
My brother came to see me and found me with a boy friend.  When á my boyfriend greeted him, he did not answer and instead started á shouting at me and scolding me in the prescence of my boyfriend.
When I went to my room-mate's drawer to see if she had an iron  á which I could use, she came in.  I felt guilty as she may have á thought that I had been stealing.
When I had my four children.
When two of my children were critically ill with measles.
When I got a low grade in an administration course.
When I got divorced from my husband after ten years of marriage.
When my mother betrayed me by obtaining money from my husband á when we were separated - pending divorce.
When I gave my boyfriend a brush-off.
When I beat up my son for having beaten up his sister.
This happened when I went to check my first year results, I had  á thought that I would fail and I found that I had a clear pass in á all my courses.
When I woke up at night to find a fire spreading towards the bed á -rooms.  I was very frightened as I realized that I faced death.
When a friend of mine was trying to make a fool out of me.
I experienced this emotion when my friend committed suicide after á we had spent the afternoon playing and discussing life and it's á problems.
When I heard of the assassination of the Indian prime-minister, á Indira Gandhi.
When I got drunk at a party and made a fool of myself by á vomitting all over the place and insulting the people who were á there with me.
When I was caught sneaking back into the house at night after á having  gone to a disco without permission.
When I was told that I had passed the exams.
When a thief broke into my house at night.
When my sister broke my china tea set.
I felt very sad when my son died after a short illness.
I met my best friend's husband with a prostitute.
When I failed to answer a simple question.
My brother wanted money but I refused to give it to him, two days á later he stole it from my father.
When I learnt that I was selected for form I.
When I was nearly beaten up by the brother of my girlfriend.
When I heard that my girlfriend was talking behind my back and á looking down on me.
When a friend, who has been with me at school, failed to make it á to UNZA.
When my girlfriend told me that she was no longer interested in á me.
I choked on a cold drink in front of girls who were strangers.
When I was caught with my girlfriend in the house at night.
When I passed the grade 7 exam.
When I was told by the doctor, after many months of coughing, á that I had tuberculosis.
When a cousin of mine took my bottle of T.B tablets, put water in á it and threw it in the dust-bin.
This happened when one of my uncles died just whan I was á planning to go and visit him during the next holidays.
When I realized that my closest friend had said bad things about á me when I was not around and had betrayed me by making friends á with my boyfriend's other girl.
When five of my friends at the secondary school found out the bad á things that I had been saying about them.
When my mother returned from a holiday, I told her a lie i.e my á father had brought another woman home while she was away.
The time I qualified to enter secondary school.
One evening I saw the old guard-man I knew, change into something á inhuman for about 5-10 seconds, this really frightened me.

When I was mistakenly accused of being a thief when I accidently á gave a fake coin at a counter.  I realized this before I handed á over the coin, but the man called me a thief and called a á witness.
The day I woke up to find that a kitten I had wanted to keep had á been eaten by the neighbour's dogs.  It had been locked out by my á wife who claimed that it had dirtied the sheets.
The day I was forced to use a public convenience place in town.  á It was so filthy that it really made me sick.
My mother caught me stealing some food when I was a young á boy.
When I gave in to what my wife wanted and locked the cat out, it á was killed by the dogs.
I felt joy when I came to know Christ.  That is when I became a á Christian.
When I broke the window pane of my next door neighbour's house.
When my brother did not send me the transport money to resume      á my studies in time at UNZA.
When I heard that my nephew had passed away.
When my father thought that I was an unrelaible son.
When I stole a book in class and the teacher caught me, the rest á of the class laughed at my attempt.
When I insulted an elderly person for no reason.
When I missed the chance of becoming a graduate in mining á engineering, after having prayed one week in the church I was á not even selected.
I watched a very terrfying film in LT2.  This film really pushed á my heart out of my body and I was forced to go out before the á second reel ended.
When I did something wrong in the past and denied having done it á when asked about it later.
The shooting started and we all lay down to protect ourselves á from the flying bullets.  This incident occured on our way to á Feira, during the Zambia army patrols in the Rhodesia war.

I went to the dining hall and found that the cooks were cleaning á the plates and there was no food for me, and the blue birds  á (security guards) were busy eating the food that was supposed to á be for me.

That afternoon I received two messages informing me, one that my á brother was in a coma in the U.T.H suffering (kidney disease) and á two, that my uncle met with an accident on his way to the hospital á  to see my brother.
This happened when I went to visit my friend in Chelston and á found him screwing my girlfriend.
When I walked out of my room with only my pants on and found my á girlfriend and her female friend looking for me outside.
My father caught me having sexual intercourse with my closest á cousin.  There was nothing wrong with it but the female was too á old for me.
When I cheated my father about the book allowance at university.  á He discovered that we were given K150 per year for books.
I experienced joy when I got the results - I had made it to the á second year.
When I was going home, I saw somathing which looked like a snake   á on the road but later I found out that it was only a stick.
This happened recently, I  was in the dining hall and one of my á friends with whom I was eating called me a fool.
I experienced this when my maternal grandmother passed away.  She á was the last of my grand parents to pass away.
This happened when I could not get into the school I had á initially wanted, and ended up doing something I had never á thought I would do.
I insulted the girl to whom I had proposed when she turned me á down.

My mother had sent me to buy a few things.  The change I brought á back was not right as I had given away some money to a friend á thinking that she would not notice it.  However, my mother told á me that the change was not correct.
When my first child was born.
I was walking through a thick forest and there was a big snake at á a distance of about four metres.
When my daughter began staying away from classes - at the age of á nine only.
When my wife died in hospital, she was pregnant and had undergone á an operation.
When my best friend started getting involved in my private á affairs.
I was very drunk at a certain wedding party and I got involved in á a fight.

I send a word to my boss through my servant telling him that I á would not report for work as I was not feeling well and that the   á doctor had refused to give me sick leave.  My intention was á actually to go out of Lusaka for a week-end.  I left the same day á and the following morning my boss found me in Mongu.  I felt á guilty when asked to explain things on my return.
I received a letter of acceptance from UNZA.
We were driving at night and I realized that a car was following á us.
I reachad home to find that my baby had not been bathed and fed.
I saw a dead child which was not covered, it had been knocked á down by a car.
I saw a friend's husband with another woman.
I scolded my sister without waiting for her explanation.
I accused my husband of being late deliberately when he came to á pick me up from work.
When I was appointed by the Ministry of health to join the á teaching staff of one of the medical colleges.
When I took blood from a patient for alcohol estimation and á urine for some other examination, he told me that something bad á would happen to me as he would play magic on me.
When the dean of UNZA asked me to vacate a big flat I was á occupying and take up a smaller one as I was becoming a full time á student at UNZA.
When my close friend was involved in an accident and passed away á instantly.  He had gone to buy a new car and had asked me to á wait at his home so that I could see his new car.
When I was told that the brother who was staying with me would á not go to the training school that year but only the year after.
A patient, to whom I had given a powerful medicine, shouted at me á in front of many people.  I realized that he did so because he á was very ill.
When I broke up my relationship with my former girlfriend as she á would ask me irrelevant quetions about my past.
When I received my promotion letter.
I was sleeping when I heard the neighbours screaming, I peeped á through the window and saw a thief  trying to enter my á neighbour's house.
I was annoyed when a person higher up asked me why a particular á job was not done, it was not my job to do it.

My brother came to tell me about some problems we had in the  á family.  I felt sad because I thought that if my mother had not á gone away when this brother was younger, things would have been á different.

I was in a train when a woman started talking loudly and á attracting everybody's attention.  The worst thing was that she á was discussing something, about which she knew nothing, with another person.

After a jogging session I had severe abdominal cramps and this á lead to my wanting to empty my bladder.  My friends gathered á around me and two of them had to help me to the toilet.  I was á ashamed at having to go to the toilet in the presence of my á friends.

A certain woman had asked me to make something for her and I kept á putting it off.  When I finally made it, I did not see her for á days only to be told one day that she had collapsed and died.  I á felt quite guilty as she had jokingly said that I might not do á what she had requested me to do.
When I was accepted for my third year (G-10) at my former á secondary school.
I had gone for a medical check-up at the U.T.H and failed to make á it back on time for the C119 practical sessions at 1400 hours á last academic year.
When I was mistreated by my step-mother.
When my aunt passed away in early 1982.
When I failed to secure employment after my form 5 in Lusaka despite á my excellent certificate.
When I failed my grade 7 exam at the first attempt in 1975.  My á father and the entire family thought that I was finished in life. á  I really felt like hiding.
When I beat up a first year student at my secondary school in á my capacity as the deputy head boy.  He had woken up late in the  á morning for manual work.
When I heard that someone who is very close to me did very well á in the exams despite having fooled around a lot.
When a drunkard barged into a room where my friend and I had run á in order to get away from him.  We were all alone and all I could á see was this hand coming towards me.

When a friend and me played a joke on our boyfriends.  Her á boyfriend came up and accused me of having planned the whole á thing and said that I did not deserve my boyfriend.  He á embarassed me in front of a crowd.
When my family and I heard of the death of my grandfather.  We had á  seen him a few weeks earlier and it seemed that he had just been á waiting to see us.
When a boy put a handful of cooked potatoes down my dress and á there was no water to clean up.
When a soppy poem that I had written to a boy was found and every á one read it and started teasing me about it.
When my boyfriend asked me to go out with him and I refused á because I wanted to go out with another guy.  I did go out and my á boyfriend found out.
After a long time (of no communication with him, physical á illness and worry) my lover came to see me, when I least expected á to see him.

Birds had made nests in our thatched roof and they were flying á and flapping their wings in the bedroom at night.  It was very á dark and I could not even see my nose.  I did not know that it á was the birds till my mother told me so.
The juniors in our dormitory at school started to complain and á make a lot of noise about the duties assigned to them by the á prefect who was my class-mate and was very cool and dull.
My elder sister scolded me in front of my younger sisters and á cousins.  She said that I was very lazy and I felt so sad that I á cried myself to sleep.
On Christmas day a drunk man came to our house without a shirt á on, he dansed, spoke nonsense and behaved stupidly.
When I wet my bed at boarding school.
My baby sister was 2-3 months old and when I was trying to get á her on my back, she slipped and fell.
My son was registered to get admission in grade one of the         á primary school.  The chances of him getting a place there was 1/10.  á Two weeks later I was informed that he had been enrolled.
When I came back from work one day, the friends of my son told me á that he had not come back from school and that he was lost.
My room-mate locked up our room without specifying where I would á find the keys.  I had to spend several hours in my other friend's á room.
I lost my grandfather whom I loved very much.  I had not known á that he had been ill for a very time, when I received this á message he was already dead.

The teacher of one course gave me 10 questions with sub-questions á going from a to e for each question.  She asked me to do all this á in one and a half hours.  It involved a lot of describing and á explaining and even though I knew all the answers, I could not á finish the work.

I forgot that the course instructor had directed us to go for á special classes after the usual class hours.  I missed this the á first day and when he asked me about it the next day I said that á I had forgotten.

I was to inform the neighbour on my left that a robber had been á spotted the same evening near the house of the neighbour in front.  á I did not do it and the same day the thieves broke into this á neighbour's house.
When my father bought me a suit.
After having taken an exam i feared having failed it.
I was badly beaten up by one of my friends during a wedding á party.
I was very sad at hearing that my grandfather had passed away.
I was disappointed by a girlfriend when I visited her at her home á in Woodlands.
I was ashamed at being the only one to have got a C+ in ED120 á assignment.
I was caught stealing a box of matches in the supermarket and had á to plead guilty.
When I heard that I had achieved a place in form I.
When I first came to the UNZA I did not know the kind of people I á would find here and the kind of behaviour they would have towards á me.
I had gone home for a week-end and when I came back I found that á my clothes and my bedding had been stolen.
When my father passed away.
Someone stole a K10 note and the teacher thought that it was me á when I was not responsible for the theft.
When I failed the grade seven exams.
One day my mother went to visit her friends.  When she came back á she scolded me for not having kept the house in order, so I á decided not to talk to her.
When I saw my family after a separation of one year.
When my little sister was sick at home and I thought that she á would die.
When I found out that my sister had been playing with my á confidential things which she had taken from my hand-bag.
When one of my best friends commited siucide during these á holidays.
I am disgusted at the number of second year students who are á pregnant illegitimately.
When I got very low marks in one of the assignments.
When my aunt went out of her way to help me out with my financial á problems.
When a thunder belt hit the roof top of the building I was in.
When my room-mate locked me out deliberately, before an exam due á at 1400 hours.
When my friends died one after the other.  The first died in a á car accident and the second one recently, due to an illness.
When my cousin put feaces in my washing.  A silly idea which was á meant to be a joke.
Getting drunk and creating a lot of trouble at a place I respect á - my friend's home.
When I took a small boy's share of choclale.  He was our guest á and so had been given a larger share of the sweets.
The day I got a telegram telling me that I had been selected for á a B.A at UNZA.  I felt happy because I had not expected to be á selected.
The day I encountered a queer mamba face to face in a chunk of á leaves behind our house.
When my friends tried to discriminate against my friendship with á certain other friends which they thought was improper.
The day my teacher of Latin and French died.
The day I went to eat dinner in the dinning hall and found a á dead fly in my gravy.
I felt ashamed of myself the first time I drank as nobody in the á family drinks.  I felt that I had let down my parents and my á friends.
The day I came home drunk after having attended a disco party.
I was very happy when I received the year end results as I was á worried about how well I had done.  I was very happy to know that I á had passed.
I was caught doing something I was not supposed to do.  I did á something with the person who caught me (bribe) and even though á he promised not to report me, I am still frightened.

I told my friend something confidential which was supposed to á remain between the two of us.  The next thing that happened was á that a girl who is not even close to us came laughing and askad á me to tell her about it.  I was very angry with my friend as I á had trusted her.
I remember that when my mother died the day was sad and every á time I think of it I am saddened by the loss of my mother.
When thieves broke into our house, I was disgusted by their á behaviour.  They did not find anything so they broke things like á the windows, glasses etc.
When I bribed the person who caught me doing something I was not á supposed to have done.  I was very ashamed of what I had done.
I was caught doing something bad and I bribed the person who á caught me.  Later I felt very bad, maybe I should have paid for á my bad behaviour.
When I received a positive answer from my appeal to withdraw my á registration at UNZA.

I was a passenger in a vehicle when suddenly another vehicle came á from behind to overtake us.  However another one was coming right á in front so the other vehicle changed course and blocked our way á and so we crashed against the side of the road.
I was asked to stop studying economics, a field which interested á me, by my employers.
When I learnt of the death of a friend.
When I learnt that my offer to study at the university had been á withdrawn  and so I would not get hostel accomodation at UNZA, á even though I registered as a student later.
My love proposal was turned down by a lady I really loved.
I came across a blind man sitting in one of the corridors and á asking for money, though I had some money I did not give him á anything.
When I first came to the campus.
When I was confronted by a policeman one night around 11 o'clock. á  I was afraid when they threatened to take me and my girl to the á gallows.
When an argument with a friend of mine over our behaviour towards á another friend turned into a quarrel.   I lost my temper and nearly á knocked him out.
When I lost my father in a car accident.
When I was denied my favourite dish at the dinning hall (shima á with roast chicken), I felt disgusted.
I felt ashamed when a friend, I had always respected, insulted me á in public.  He was drunk.
When my library books were overdue and I did not have the money á to pay for them.
When I got my results - I had passed the form III exams.  I had á not expected to do so well.
When I was an exploration with my friends and almost got lost in á an unfamiliar environment.  It was getting dark and we did not á know how to get back home.
When my father did not get back from Chipata on time, he was thus á holding back progress as everything depended on him.  I felt á angry over his actions.
When my little brother passed away mysteriously, at least from á what I was told about it.
When I saw a woman who had been run over by a train, just off á Kafue.  The woman had been cut to bits, there was blood and        á splinters of bone every where.
When I almost did something awful with a friend of mine and á myself.
When I was accepted at UNZA.
When thieves broke into our neighbour's house and later we heard á gunshots.
When my aunt scolded me for something I was not responsible for.  á A boy had come to our gate asking for me, my aunt went out to see á him.  I had neither met nor known the boy.
When my cousin passed away unexpectedly and tragically (a á murder).
When my mother got a terrible beating from my father.  It was so á bad that she fainted and it was only then that my dad realized á how bad it was.
When my friend had a child out of wedlock.
When I lied at home.   I told them that I was going to a á Christian meeting and I went to see my boyfriend instead.
Receiving my result slip (pass) on my birthday.

When we forced a friend to chew a poisonous herb in primary á school.  His tongue was swollen and he told his mother about it.  á The mother reported it to the headmaster who threatened to expel á us.
At boarding school someone put a lot of tiny thorns on my bed.  á When I complained everybody began teasing me and laughing at my á inability to find out my enemies.  I lost my temper.
When my grandfather died.
My room-mate was drunk, he vomited on the floor and fell face á down on the vomit nearly choking himself to death.  Then he á fainted and so I called the first aid.
As a kid my mother caught me stealing sugar and giving it to a á neighbour.
I got into a bad fight in a bar and my friend received a bad cut á above his left eye while trying to separate us.
I felt vvery happy when I was accepted at UNZA for my studies.  á I had not expected this as I had been ill during the exams.
I felt very frightened when a robber broke into our house and á threatened to shoot my father if he did not part with some money. á  I was looking at the man with his hand on the trigger.
A teacher at my former secondary school forced my darling to á marry him.  The girl tried to refuse but her parents would not á leave her alone.
When my sister died, she was only sixteen when she was put to á rest.
When I witnessed an accident.
When my father found me in bed with a girl, we were deep in actioon á when he entered the room.
I took my grandmother's money without telling her and when asked á if it was me who had taken the money, I denied it.
When I won some coins in a small competion.
I went home late one evening and saw that the security lights á were off.  I got inside the gate and just then I realized that á the dogs may be outside.
My little niece, who is very talkative, suddenly became very á naughty and began wetting her pants.  She did it one afternoon.
This morning during my sleep I had a feeling that someboby was á attacking me.  I started crying in my sleep and then my room-mate á woke me up.
When I learnt that my cousin sister was pregnant.
My cousin and I were at the farm and at night we drunk like fools á and made a lot of noise.  We had drunk two much of wine.
The fridge we had at home had a lock.  One day when I wanted á something, I unscrewed the door but unfortunately I was caught in á the act.
When I was selected for the university.
When I saw an accident, a woman was run over and she died on the á spot.
When my dress and a few other things were stolen from my á wardrobe.
When my grandmother passed away.
While watching a movie, someone who was drunk started vomiting á helplessly.
When I ate my sister's food and then she found out that it was á me.  I felt very ashamed but still refused to admit that it was á me.
When I told a person something that had happened to my friend, á and this person went and told my friend.
When I got myself the kind of girlfriend I had been hunting for a á long time.
When I was told that the form five results were out.
When I saw my younger sister being bothered by a boy she did not á know.
The time I lost a badminton match, that I should have won at the á Zambia closed badminton championships.
When I was taking my girlfriend out, she seemed to have taken á her time.
When my dad caught me with a honey (girlfriend) in my bedroom.
When I beat up a stupid boy who was fond of cracking jokes on me.
When I was selected for higher education, i.e grade 7 to formI.
When I impregnated a certain girl, I thought that I would be á forced to marry her or go to court.
When the university withdrew the accomodation that it had given á me.
When my mother and father separated (it was a brief separation á and they are together now).
When I patronized a certain tavern which had prostitutes, it was á almost a brothel.
When I proposed love to a girl and she turned me down.
When I sided with my mother in a quarrel she had with my father á before they briefly separated.
When I received a letter from a woman I thought had not ever á cared for me.  This was when I needed her and I was overjoyed to á learn that it was me who was delaying things.
Two guys were fighting murderously and I feared that one of them á would be killed.
When I could not reason my friend, it angered me.
I did not like it when a little girl was crying for her dead á mother and was calling her by her name.  I was sad.
I felt very ashamed at having got a book by force from a girl.
I felt guilty of having suspected my room-mate of stealing the á money last term.
Our only elder sister got married and started having pains in her á abdomen and she was told that she could not have children. To our á suprise she had a baby 2 months back.
My uncle was taken to the UTC for an operation as he had cancer.  á There had been a lot of deaths of late - 3 out of every 4 á operated.  I was scared for my uncle's life.

I had planned to go to town with my friend at 1500 hours but she á went for the registration and I waited for a good 1 and a 1/2 hours.  It á was vital for me to go to town but I could not as it was she who á had the money.  Finally I borrowed some money from friends and we á went to town.  I was really angry with my friend.
I dreamt of my father's death while I was at secondary school.  I á was screaming at the top of my voice and was woken up by my á friend.  That day I was really sad.
I had prepared a special meal for my boyfriend but when my á brother came home he ate it all.  I was really disgusted about it.

We were at a party, this guy I liked and me.  I really loved him á and gathered enough courage to ask him to kiss me.  He did not do á it but instead asked me what I would like for my birthday.  I á told him that I would like a kiss more than anything else but he á excused himself and said that it was impossible.  I really felt á embarassed.
We were at secondary school and I was making a lot of noise.  The á teacher came to ask us as to who was making all the noise.  I did á not own up so the  whole class was punished.
I was very happy when my scholarship to continue studying at UNZA á was approved after it had been cancelled.
When I met an elephant in the bush.
When someone took my pen away.
When my cousin passed away during the holidays at home.  He fell á ill at night and the next day he died in the evening.
An officer at the Dean of students office had promised me to give á me a room the next day, but he failed to keep his promise.
I do not have accomodation on the campus so I stay with my á extended family, one young man used bad words while asking me to á leave their home.
I broke a glass of glycerine at the Z.C.B.C store in Ndola.
When I was with someone I love.
When I was walking around all alone at night.
Being made to look like a fool by a girl.
When my dad passed away.
When I was told that I had no right to control my lover.
Getting very low marks in mathematics.
When one of my lovers told me that I was a flirt.
At my sister's wedding.
When I had to walk along a dark road alone.
When I was locked out of my room by my room-mate's friend.
When I failed one of my courses at school - the university of á Zambia.
When I found out that someone close to me was flirting around.
When I swindled money out of someone.
I did not deliver a message on time.
When the lady who is now my wife accepted my proposal to be my á lover and future wife.
When my neighbour's house was broken into and shots could be á heard.
When a thief broke into my house and stole some valuable goods.
The death of my guardian with whom I had stayed when I did my á grade six.
When I was substituted in a play which was to be staged, after I á had learnt all the lines.
When a woman who I respected very much was made pregnant, á unexpectedly by a man of a caliber I never expected.
When I applied for a false travelling claim allowance and later I á thought that I would be found out.
I felt happy when my mother gave birth to a son who is the last á born in the family.
My father had been involved in a car accident two years ago.  I á was then very scared thinking that he would die as he lay á unconscious in hospital for two weeks.
I felt very angry when a mishanga seller robbed me of the á transport money I had to go to school.
I felt very sad when a friend of mine failed the final exam and á she could not be accepted at the institution of learning.
I felt disgusted when a fellow student asked me to marry him.  I á had not expected this from him as he was a mere friend.
I was ashamed when my friend and I were cross with each other á till we apologized to each other.
I felt guilty when I said bad things to my sister, I had not á intended to do so.  She cried a lot and later she fell ill and I á felt responsible for her illness.
When I was selected to study here at UNZA.
In 1960,  I was going to a school which was near my village and I á met a lion on the way, which disappeared suddenly.
When my wife told me that the refrigerator had stopped working.
When I heard of the death of my mother.
When my relatives troubled me so that I would help them á financially.
When I failed one of the first year's courses.
When I was late for work and told my boss that it was due to á transport problem, whereas the truth was that I had woken up á late.  I thus cheated my boss.
I was overwhelmed with joy when I received the acceptance letter á to UNZA.  This happened again when I passed all my first year á courses.

In 1977 when my friend was caught by a crocodile.  We were á swimming in a river on whose banks our primary school was á situated.  When my friend was caught, he was on the banks of the á river and some of us were still in the middle of the river.  I á was very frightened.
In 1982, I was annoyed at an uncle who was drunk and was beating á up his old father.  He claimed that the father was responsible á for his guardian's failure.
Last academic year I received bad news - my grand-uncle had á passed away.  I felt lonely and bad because apart from the         á biological ties, he was a good old friend of mine at home.
Last week a former school (secondary) mate of mine, who is now in á a differentt school came to my room here at UNZA in my absence.  á He was drunk and he vomited in my room.  I was unhappy.
A few years back I had proposed love to a girl who later turned out á to be related to me.  Though we were in love with each other, we á both felt ashamed and withdrew from each other.
Last year I was asked to look after my niece while her mother was á cooking.  Unfortunately the kid fell off the bed, I was confident á that she would not fall and had not been paying much attention.
When I qualified for form I.  I was one of the three pupils who á qualified for form I that year.
When I learnt that the girl I had impregnated was in hospital and á was on the verge of dying as she had refused to accept the á responsibility of her pregnancy and had wanted to commit suicide.
When I got home I found that the electrical supply had been á disconnected despite my having paid ZESCO the full bill a few  á days earlier.
When I lost my grandmother.  She had been my guardian after the á death of my father.

When I told a girl that I could not take her out that night as I á was entertaining my mother who had come from home.  However, I á later met this girl with another girlfriend at a hostel where I á had taken out another girlfriend of mine.

When I told the driver at my workplace to lie and tell the boss á that it was not me who was responsible for the delay.  The boss á was very annoyed and the driver was punished and a day's salary á was taken away from him.
When my wife gave birth to a baby boy - my only son to date.
When burglars with guns forced themselves into my house and á ordered me to give them money or face death.

The emotion came when a certain boy opened my locker without my á knowledge.
The sadness came to me when I heard that my girlfriend whom I á loved so much got married to another man before a rebuff from á her.
The emotion came to me when a certain girl who was not polite to á her mother hit her sister severely.
The shame came when I was beaten by my teacher at school in front á of boys and girls some of whom were my friends and a girlfriend á apart from being classmates.
It was when I discovered that the girl who I had proposed was a á friend's girlfriend.
When I was told that I was selected to attend Medical Assistant á Training.
When I was told to attend an operation in theatre.
This situation happened when my friend John ate my banana which I á kept in the cupboard.
When I was told that my father had passed away.
This situation occurred when I entered into a smelling ward.
This situation happened when I was found kissing a girl who was á my friend's girlfriend.
This situation happened when my friend me with a knife which I á stole from him.
When my father married a certain lady. The reception was held at á Kasungu town Hall.
At night when I was coming from Lingadzi Inn I heard a hyena á crying in the Lingadzi jungle. I was alone.
I felt angry when I was told that I had not been selected to go á to the University.
I felt sad when I was told to walk out of the classroom because I á was within the row of students who were making noise.
I felt disgusted when a certain lady spoke words of sarcasm when á I was trying to propose to her.
When I broke a tea saucer. I felt ashamed. This was during the á birthday of my girlfriend.
I felt guilty when I was given a prize which belonged to someone á else.
My girlfriend who had been very far away from me came to my á place. She saw me and ran after me. I didn't know that she had á come. I couldn't see her. She held my shoulders standing behind á me.
I was given a wristwatch by my first girl and after two days á another girl of mine also gave me a wristwatch.
My girlfriend mentioned a certain girl's name who was my girl á some time back and she is no longer mine that she said she was á still mine.
I had been caught red-handed having stolen some paw-paw. I was á then taken the elders owning the paw-paws.
I was double crossing Mercy and Maria. They one day came to know á each other. I was found by Mercy red-haded when I was with Maria.
I had a girlfriend in the same class I was. I did not do well in á my Exams, but she did satisfactorily well and was taken into á another class leaving me behind.
Our Headmaster came to our hostel. The lights were off but there á was a lot of noise. We shouted at him when he knocked at our á door. We later saw that it was the Headmaster.
This happened when I was selected to go to Secondary school to á start Form I in October 1980.
As I was taking venous blood from another patient I introduced á air into the place of puncturing and there was a swelling which á is dangerous to the patient hence I became afraid.
My lovely girlfriend double-crossed me and so that I found her á chatting with another guy.
I really became sad when mother passed away while I was very á young.
I was disgusted when my brother was arrested because of stealing á money.
I was ashamed when my classmates discovered that I fell in love á with an uneducated girl.
I felt guilty when I lost K43 for my friend when he was arrested.
I felt joy when I passed my Malawi School Certificate of á Education.
When I had crossed Lilongwe forest I heard that there was a rabid á hyena just near the path in the forest.
I was angry when I heard that my only girl was going about with á another man. So I decided to drop her but later the story came to á be untrue.
When I was not selected to go to the University of Malawi I felt á very sad.
When I was presumed to have stolen maize from the school garden.
I once proposed my own niece whom I did not know but I discovered á after she was my girlfriend.
A certain colleague of mine sent me to buy a bag of flour for him, á he gave me K20. Unfortunately I lost it.
When I married my wife and took her home for the first time.
When my friend was involved in a car accident.
When I was charmed by my relatives.
When my mother died in August 1978.
When I entered the wound intensive care at the Central Hospital á in Blantyre which was stinking.
When I first failed my standard 8 exams for the first attempt for á Form I selection.
When I had beaten my auntie.

My friend took me to Civo Stadium to watch and listen to the á music of the International singer Sam Mangwana. I had no hope of á going there since I had no money so he gave me the money for á admission.
I had fear when I was left alone at the bus depot at night. I had á problems of how to move to this place.
I felt angry when I heard that my sister had failed the á Examinations which we hoped she was going to pass with á distinctions.
I felt sad when I heard that my girlfriend was double-crossing me á with the boy who is my best friend.
I felt disgust when I saw a friend walking in stagnant water á without putting on gum boots.
I experienced shame when I failed to keep a promise to meet my á friend at the bus depot. He later came and asked me why I had not á turned up.

I felt guilty of revealing a secret to my in-law. I told her that á my brother and I had gone to disconight which is a thing my á brother didn't want to let her know. Later my brother was accused á of spending a night out.
The joy came when I first proposed a girl at Secondary School.
As I was in a ward one man died and I was instructed to watch the á last offices. But this was my first time to see a dead person - á fear came.
I was very angry when I heard that my brother was beaten by his á friends.á
I was very sad when I heard about the death of my teacher who á taught me in Standard 8.
I was disgusted to see a person vomitting and I was told to clean á the place where the vomit was.
I was ashamed when a certain friend of mine I used to move with á failed to propose to a lady yet we always said to ourselves no á lady can refuse our proposal.
I felt guilty when one of my secondary teacher left me while I á was in Form three, he was the only one who showed love to me.
My sister gave birth to twins, healthy ones.

I was looking after my father's sheen in the forest. One day á while playing with friends from neighbouring villages the flock á escaped me and went into a far place. It became dark and I was á afraid of father. I went home and hid myself.

I planned to travel a distance of 20 kilometres on my bike. I á planned this when I was working in the hospital. When I went to á the house I found that a friend had taken my bike without my á consent.
It was in the evening when I heard that my girl went to Zambia á and that she would never come back.
A sister broke a cup and when mother asked I was reported to have á been responsible.

One day mother slaughtered a chicken for a brother who had come á back for holiday. In everybody's absence I opened the foodstore á and ate all internal organs of the chicken. When mother á discovered, we were all called and I was found with hands stained á with soup. I was ashamed being the eldest of all in the family.
This emotion happened when I passed my primary school examination á and was selected for Secondary School.
At primary school I was accused by some boys of being in love á with a certain girl in their class so they had to shout and beat á the girl and the matter was reported to the headmaster.
I was very angry when one day I went to see my girlfriend I á talked to her and could not answer back. She was depressed for á reasons which were not known to me.
I was very sad when I was shouted at by Uncle and was told that I á was not to be given school fees because I didn't go to work in á the garden since I had gone to escort my sister to the bus depot.
I was disgusted when I was told to dress a big rotten stinky á wound which, coming closer, made me feel like vomitting.
I was ashamed one day when we were found stealing and roasting á maize cobs from Agricultural experimental projects.
I felt guilty when the truth was known about my impregnating the á girl we were staying with.
It was August 30th when I heard on the radio that I passed my á M.C.E. exams and I was really happy and joyous because of the á event.
I was walking alone along the place where people fear that there á are always thieves there and the people who kill their friends á during the night two months ago.
I once was accused of falling in love with someone's girlfriend á which was not true because the girl was just a friend of mine.
It was when I failed standard 8 exams while all my friends á passed and went to secondary school. In class I was always á getting more marks than they did.
My first day to work in hospital, when I was dressing wounds I á was disgusted when I came across one wound with a very bad smell.
One day I was with my girlfriend and other friends were behind á us, I fell down because the place was slippery and I really felt á ashamed.
I felt guilty one day when I was accused of running away from á classes and I was caught.
It was when I was allowed to take my wife away from her parents á after being refused for three times on grounds that she should á first write her examination.
When two hyenas made crying noise on the window of my bedroom at á home when I was preparing for my MCE examination during the á night.
It was when my Instructor awoke me late at night to get prepared á for the training at Military college when he was coming back from á his personal social activities.
I slept in a tent at the Barracks which caught fire at night and á my best possessions got burnt in there.
It was when my father beat my mother while she was ill for three á weeks and now she was recovering.

When parents of a certain girl refused to let me marry their á daughter because I was not fit to do so yet the girl accepted á everything and later she followed what her parents insisted and á she told me never to talk to her again.
The time I was at secondary school during the holiday I appeared á to my father while heavily drunk and I talked nonsense like in á some sort of carefree.

This came in when at one time I met a girl who I didn't expect to á fall in love with me. Fortunately I tried my luck and she accepted á my proposal. At the same time she was giving me a lot of money á which was just like a miracle to me.
When I was travelling at night.

I experienced this when one of my friends reported to the á Headmaster that I had gone out for beer, whilst the information á was not true at all. So I had to fight the friend before the á Headmaster.
When I was at school.
One of those days when I was going to school with my brother and á he annoyed me.
This was when one of the Clinical officers scolded us in the á hospital on how to make beds but we did not deserve to be á scolded.
NO RESPONSE.

That was soon after the results of the interview which nearly á 9,000 people attended in all the three regions of Malawi. My joy á came after hearing on the radio that I was one of the people á selected to undergo the Medical Assistant training at the á L.S.H.S.
Fear came towards the end of May when the P.T.S. results were out á after hearing the failure of my fellow three friends.
I was once this week angry when soemone trying to compress my á mind due to his nonsense speech which himself could not tolerate á at all.
This condition accumulated in my mind when funeral news was á brought to my awareness, that a close relative had passed away.
A condition in which I was disgusted followed when I lost money á on my way home from the college.
I was very ashamed when I was neglected by a certain friend whom á I was thinking loved me very much.
I once felt guilty when a certain passenger in the same (ship, á plane ?) which I boarded when coming from home lost his 10t which á in fact fell into my pocket unknowingly.
It was when I was selected to go to a Secondary school to start á form I.
It was when I stepped on a python (snake) unknowingly while it á was sleeping near a baobab tree.
It was when my friend had stolen my money (K10) and had á disappeared.
It was when my father was taken into detention by the CIDS for á two years for a reason I don't know up to now.
It was when I drunk urine during my childhood thinking it was á water. My friend had urinated in the tin.
It was when my father caught me with a girl in dark corners and á asked me what I was doing there.
It was when I injured a friend accidentally with a stone. It made á a cut on the cheeks which resulted in suturing.

Time had struck 8 o'clock when I heard from the radio that I had á been selected to Robert Blake Secondary School for Form I. I was á very happy for the selection. My parents and I were very happy á and full of joy.
My brother had bowel obstruction, having heard that he was going á for surgery, I was afraid he might not come back to life after á hearing of the General Anaesthesia.
I felt very angry after one driver had run over my beloved niece.

I was away to school (Primary). In my abscence my young brother á at home got sick suddenly. My parents took him to hospital. On á the way he died. It came to me as a sad, sudden and shocking á news and I felt very sad.
I felt disgusted when I went to one of the Central hospitals á where my hope of getting good treatment was turned down by one of á the doctors who said I was alright despite my feeling pain.
I was in my room, I just heard that my Uncle had been caught in á somebody's house with somebody's wife. He had to appear in court. á I went to see what would happen to him.
I felt guilty after hearing that my girlfriend with whom I had á spent most of my time was pregnant.
When I heard that I had passed Primary School Leaving Certificate á and was selected to go for Secondary education.
When I heard that there is teasing and bulling at Secondary á School.
When I heard that I was not to be provided with another pair of á medical uniform.
When I heard that my father had passed away.
When I vomitted a lump of blood.
When a certain girl I believed to be my life partner refused an á engagement.
When I didn't notify someone that he was summoned by a headmaster á and as a result he ended being on a heavy punishment.
I met my girlfriend on the way and she joyfully welcomed me on á the way home.
One time I set up my journey at night going to a certain bar. On á the way I met my friends and they told me that two people had á died because of heavy fighting. I proceeded on but with fear.

An incident occurred to me when I was going home with my á girlfriend. On the way, a man named Banda grabbed my girlfriend á in my presence. I was really angry with him and as a result I á threw stones at him and he ran away.
When I found my baby whipped by my Auntie. I was really sad and á up to this moment my sadness is still on.
I was really disgusted when I saw one of my friends soiling on á his clothes. I thought he was mad.
One day I went for a bath. I took off my clothes and as soon as I á had finished my brother came in. I felt sad and I found no reason á why he came in.
One day I took a packet of sweets from a certain Grocery at á Nathenje. Then later on I started to feel guilty and realised á that I had done a wrong thing to him.
I felt happy when I saw my brother at the bus depot after 3 á months without seing each other.
When we were going to Nkhoma last Saturday the vehicle was moving á very fast, so I feared we might crash since the road was too á rough.
When they put the blame on me when I scored the third goal at the á match.
I felt very sad when I lost my three Kwacha at civo Stadium when á Sam Mangwana was playing some Rumba records. That was not what I á expected, I wanted some Disco records.
In ward 2A there was a patient suffering from Syphilitic á Paraplegia and had pressure sores. The wounds had offensive smell á that only a few people .... the place.
It was when we were beaten or lost the football match by 5-1 and á then I scored the third goal to my own side.
When I scored the third goal to my own side at a football match á against William Murray Secondary School and we were badly á defeated.
On December the 28th I was filled with Joy when I was told by my á bosses that I had been selected to attend a course at the á Lilongwe School for Health Scienced in Lilongwe.
It was last week on Saturday night when I was at Mchesi. I feared á to cross the Lilongwe River Bridge to come back to School due to á darkness - until somebody had to escort me.
It was at Malawi Army, Dormer Squadron, when some of my workmates á got promoted to Seargents (sgts); we were having similar á Ranks.

It was mid May 1985, When we had a Test on Nursing. My classmate á had an answer sheet, so he tried to peep. The Nursing Tutor á caught him. During this time I was turning my question paper and á it made noise. This friend blamed me of causing the whole matter á for him to be caught.
In May somebody blamed me that I made him to be caught while á peeping during the Nursing Test which made me feel disgusted.
In our class we had a test on Nursing, so a friend from the Army á was caught peeping, by using a paper which had already answers á which was written by him. So all of us from the Army got ashamed.
It was on January 1st 1985 when I accidentally broke a Fanta á bottle in a certain bottle store in Zomba.
I felt joy when I heard over the radio that I had been successful á in my Primary School Leaving Certificate Examination and was á selected for Secondary School.
One day I was busy day dreaming along the road and suddenly I á heard the sound of jamming car braked behind me. I woke up from á my dreams and it was about to crash me.

When I was doing my last year at Secondary School I was robbed of á my clothes, wristwatch and my pair of shoes. After investigations á it was found that all the things were stolen by one of the boys á in our hostel.

It was on 9th January 1983 when I received a message from home á telling me that my father passed away on the previous day with a á history of cancer of the oesophagus. This time I was doing my á third year of my Secondary School.
I was stopped from entering a party while I was at School but I á had an Invitation card with me. This was done because they said I á was too young to join elderly people.
In 1972 I failed my Examination because of my own crooky á behaviour of dodging from Examinations.

A child was admitted in hospital with Meningitis. I was asked to á do lumber puncture to obtain Celebral Spinal fluid for diagnostic á purposes. Since the condition was already bad, the child died as á soon as I finished the procedure.
When I had an anticipatory honey-moon with my fiancTe.
When it was found that I had gone out of the school premises á without permisssion and at the wrong time.
When a classmate hit me on my occipital region when I was busy á studying and concentrating on my classnotes.
When my father died.
When somebody made me touch human faeces.
Soiled my short trousers with faeces.
When a crawling child got burnt because of my negligence to keep á the child away from the fire.

When I heard my name being announced on the radio that I had been á successful in an interview for admittance for a medical Assistant á training course. I was really happy and I enjoyed myself by á dancing to music from the Radio cassette.

One time I was injured when I was playing football at School in á Blantyre. I was brought to the hospital while my leg was totally á swollen. The x-rays confirmed there was no fracture but á collection of blood n the muscles. I feared when they started to á incise the swollen part with surgical blade.
One day I was really angry when all my food was eaten by a dog. á My anger was against my mother because she was careless. She á didn't keep the food in a hidden and proper place.

One day I came across a certain boy who was intruding my á friendship as lovers with my girlfriend and I was very sad á because I didn't expect that girl to disappoint me I regarded her á as being very faithful.
One time at the hospital I passed near the intensive care room. á The offensive smell that came out disgusted me in such a way that á I didn't even dare to enter the room.
At one occasion I was ashamed of being refused after a proposal á for a friendship with a certain girl. I was ashamed because she á refused publically in the presence of my fellow friends.
I once stole my father's money and denied having done it. Instead á father threatened my young brother and he was beaten. He was á innocent and I felt guilty.

When I was selected to start Form I at Chilumba Secondary School á out of the 100 pupils I was among the 4 who were successful. á Family History showed that I had done better than all my brothers á who had passed after repeating for several times.
We went fishing some 5 or 8 kilometers off the shore of Lake á Malawi. Before we could settle down the lake became very rough to á the point of threatening our lives.

I was angered by a classmate who poured soup on to my clothes. He á was trying to use a short-cut method in getting his supper. á Coming behind my back, he wasn't noticed by me and as I was á retreating from a hungry congested people I knocked his plate á with my head. He didn't accept being wrong but blamed me for á pouring his soup.
I was sad when my MCE grades were out. I had gone for a football á match a mile away from home. The mail found me there. I was á disappointed and didn't play the other half of the match.

I was dancing Malipenga (traditional dance). I exaggerated the á steps I was supposed to make in the negative way. This happened in á front of spectators. It was bad for our Boma (group) because I á was on the front line where ability is displayed and it is this á ability that counts when choosing the winning side.
News was spread that I had been found doing sexual intercourse á with a small girl. At first this annoyed me but later on I became á ashamed because many people seemed to believe it.
I argued with my father on matters concerning marriage. á Traditionally speaking, I was not supposed to, so I felt guilty á of violating my traditions which I must hold in esteem.
I passed my MCE Examination. at first I was worried but when I á heard my name I had joy in my heart and I arranged for a trip to á attend a wedding ceremony.

I was studying in class at night. I was in Form II by then. There á were rumours about an earthquake. That night dogs were chasing á one another and passed through the window outside the classroom. á Those who saw the dogs thought it was a lion and were terrified. á Trying to run away the desks were dragged and there was a shaking á movement. I thought it was an earthquake and jumped out of the á window.
Someone told a lie that I had stolen his money.
My Uncle was beaten by his troublesome son. He fell unconscious á and gained consciousness after some time. That time I was at á school; this news reached me through someone.
I felt disgust when I received visitors at an odd hour. I was á seriously preparing for Examinations, so I did not appreciate á their coming.
I answered a certain question from Dr. Maqgda wrongly. She asked á something about Femur and my answer was saying something á concerning the brain. So I was very ashamed amongst my friends.
I wrote a bad letter to someone concerning our relationship which á we created ourselves.
I met a certain lady at Mchesi and I proposed a word of love to á her and at the same time she accepted my proposal.
My father gave me money for school fees and I didn't pay school á fees instead I spent it on beer and did not tell him about this.
There was a cup final match between Limbe Leaf Wanderers and á Silver Strikers and someone promised to give me some money for á admission fee to watch this game. Unfortunately he did not give á me.
I had received bad news informing me that grandmother and á grandfather had passed away. The first one to die was my á grandmother and after two days grandfather died too.
It happened that one of my best friends just took my shirt á without my knowledge, I hadn't put it on for many days and I was á short of clothes.
I had high-heeled shoes one time, but a certain girl who saw the á shoes told me that they were out of fashion and I looked as an á old man when I was in those shoes.
I happened to have met one of my teachers in town during working á hours. The badness was I didn't ask for permission to go out and á I was guilty-conscious.
Passing a very difficult examination which I didn't expect - MCE.
As we were going to Area 10 a dog chased me. I was afraid it á might bite me.
Brother took my money to use for his own purposes.
After hearing the news about the death of my sister, I felt very á sad.
After buying a ticket, I lost it before I reached my destination á and the bus Inspector dropped me at a place I didn't know.
I was very much ashamed after a friend beat me at school and I á was defeated.
I hit my cousin badly after she threw away my dresses in a á pit-latrine that the little girl fainted.
When I was selected to a University College of Nursing.

When one of my relatives went out at night leaving me and my á friend alone, I cheated my parents that she didn't go out, after á they had heard that she was out, I was afraid that she might have á beaten me.
When someone took my writing materials yet I was to write á Examinations in a few minutes.
When I failed my Standard 8 Examination for the first time.
When a boy whom I refused to be my lover told all his friends á that I was his girl he has refused me because I was not faithful á to him.
When someone pointed out that I was proud, yet I didn't dress up á properly. This was when I and my friend went for a dnce one á Saturday.
After I had cheated my parents that I had lost my textbooks so á they had to send me money.
I felt joy when I heard my name being called on the radio as one á of the students who had passed the interview of Nursing and was á selected to start Nursing.
I felt fear when one night my aunt and Uncle left me alone at á their house to look after the baby when they went to a party.
I felt angry at one time when I was chatting with friends and á suddenly another friend joined us and started opposing any á comment I added to our chatting.
I felt sad when a thief stole all the clothes from my friend's á cupboard at school (boarding).
I felt disgusted when I was not given money for lunch at school á by my father as a punishment for beating my little brother.
I felt shame when I was asked by my cousin that I promised to buy á her a birthday present but I didn't buy it for her in front of á friends.
I felt guilt when my friends were punished to slash grass at the á gound because of making noise in class. I was in the group of á noise-makers but I denied having done any noise.
When I passed my MSCE Exams and was selected to go to college.
I was with my boyfriend forgetting that I had left the house á unlocked. Unfortunatly a thief came and stole all the kitchen á utensils. Thereafter I was afraid of the consequences.
My best friend started moving out with my boyfriend. When I heard á this my heart sank because I didn't expect that my own good á friend could do such a thing, so I got angry.
I was sad when I heard that my cousin died because of being á bewitched by her husband's second wife.
My friend promised to take me out for a movie but he didn't turn á up.
I met a woman who was looking for our house. She stopped me but I á ran away. When I arrived at home I found the same woman and she á told my parents what had happened so I felt ashamed.

I went to my boyfrien's house. There I found clothes of a certain á girl. Without asking whose clothes they were I started tearing á them only to realise that they were his sister's and so I felt á guilty.
When I was selected to come here.
Somebody told her friend that she would hit me wherever we would á meet.
This was when my boyfriend told me that I was double-crossing him á with a certain boy.
When I heard that my friend had started drinking beer.
I went to a party and there were some cakes which weren't good á and had a bad smell.
One day I was supposed to go to a movie with my boyfriend. In the á morning I went to see my Auntie and I didn't come back up to á evening.
I slapped my sister's daughter and after several hours, she had a á high temperature and she ended up being admitted in hospital.
When the church choir came one Sunday after being away for some á weeks.
When I came home late one day. I was afraid I would be shouted at á by my parents.
When a little brother of mine damaged a cassette.
I was watching T.V with my parents and some pornographic scenes á came on, I felt uncomfortable and tried to distract my parents á attention by talking to them.
I saw a program on T.V where they had to saw a skull for an        á operation.
When I decided not to out any longer with a girl whom I liked á quite a lot.  This made me feel low for a some time.
[ No description.]
When I had my first boyfriend.
I and my cousin went to a filmshow at night. We went without á making it known to my mother. While we were there at interval, I á came across my mother just close to where we sat.

During the Xmas holiday, I and my best friend at Secondary School á had planned to meet at a Cultural afternoon at the Mt. Soche á Hotel after missing each other for such a long time. When I asked á my mother for permission, she told me not to go for no good á reason. I felt very angry with her.

When I was transferred from Chichiri Secondary School to St. á Mary's Sec. School. I was happy at Chichiri as a day scholer and á had made a lot of friends. I was going to a boarding and that á meant parting with my friends as well as my boyfriend for the á first time.
I felt disgusted when my cousin decided that she would stop á going to school saying she wanted to get married. She was only 14 á years by then and she didn't understand what she was thinking.
When I failed my Primary school leaving Examinations. I never á thought I would fail. When I heard I had failed I really felt á ashamed of myself.
One time I felt guilty when I told one of my previous boyfriends á we were through just because I never felt like having one at that á particular time.
I was filled with joy when I heard that I had been selected for a á University course.
Sometime back, my boyfriend and I were having a walk nearby my á parent's house. Suddenly we met my grandfather and I was á afraid that he would report to my parents.
One day I was angry with my friend who went into my drawer and á took a piece of paper on which I wanted to write a letter and á used it for her business without my knowledge.

It was shocking news to me when I received a telegram from home á telling me that my grandmother had passed away. I had to go home to attend á the funeral but unfortunately I found that the burial had already á taken place.
I was disgusted with my brother's behaviour when he kept throwing á things away because of his anger, after mum had shouted at him.
I was ashamed with my biology lecturer when he asked me a á question and I could not answer it.

One day I was chatting with children at home. Then I took a lump á of soap and gave to one of them pretending that it was a sweet. I á thought the child would realise that it was not. Unfortunately he á did not and he put it in his mouth.
I wrote a difficult Exam at one time while in my Secodary School. á When the results were announced on the radio, I came second out á of 80 students hence I felt joy.
When the week for Exams came. I got afraid as to how I would á tackle the questions.
Last week a friend of mine called on me and said I was moody and á difficult to persuade. With this I got angry with her.
I experienced this emotion when my grandfather passed away.
In my village there was this tax collector who used to cheat á people and collected more than was wanted, the surplus was for á his family and himself.
I felt ashamed when my lecturer said in class that I á happened to be the dullest of all.
I felt guilty when I was found to be the chief leader of making á noise in class.
When I received a beautiful birthday gift form my parents.
When I was called for an Interview at Kamuzu College of Nursing.
When I damaged my wristwatch which I liked very much.
When my cousin passed away.
When my fellow classmates were involved in a quarrel.
When I failed Psychology examination when most of the students á passed.
When I promised to visit my boyfriend and I didn't fulfil the á promise.
I had stayed for months without seeing mother because our á holidays were short and my home is far. Some times, mother came to á see me at school, I was very joyful, and I didn't want her to go.

One day during our clinical practices, we had a very ill patient. á Unfortunately the patient passed away. I had seen him dying and á it was the first experience. During the night I became afraid á fearing the dead body.

Talkiing about the past happy hours with two friends at night in á a camp a few months ago.  We shared our feelings, notions and á every hidden anxiety.  I thought that they cared for me and I á was very happy and satified.
